Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1963A\n| Granahan || Fowler || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1969\n| [[Dorothy Andrews Elston Kabis|Elston]] || [[David M. Kennedy|Kennedy]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1969A\n| [[Dorothy Andrews Elston Kabis|Kabis]] || [[John Connally|Connally]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1969B\n| [[Romana Acosta Ba\u00f1uelos|Ba\u00f1uelos]] || Connally || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1969C\n| Ba\u00f1uelos || [[George Shultz|Shultz]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1974\n| [[Francine Irving Neff|Neff]] || [[William E. Simon|Simon]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1977\n| [[Azie Taylor Morton|Morton]] || [[W. Michael Blumenthal|Blumenthal]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1977A\n| Morton || [[G. William Miller|Miller]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1981\n| [[Angela Marie Buchanan|Buchanan]] || [[Donald Regan|Regan]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1981A\n| [[Katherine D. Ortega|Ortega]] || Regan || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1985\n| Ortega || [[James Baker|Baker]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1988\n| Ortega || [[Nicholas F. Brady|Brady]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1988A\n| [[Catalina Vasquez Villalpando|Villalpando]] || Brady || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1993\n| [[Mary Ellen Withrow|Withrow]] || [[Lloyd Bentsen|Bentsen]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1995\n| Withrow || [[Robert E. Rubin|Rubin]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 1999\n| Withrow || [[Lawrence Summers|Summers]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 2001\n| [[Rosario Marin|Marin]] || [[Paul H. O'Neill|O'Neill]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 2003\n| Marin || [[John W. Snow|Snow]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 2003A\n| [[Anna Escobedo Cabral|Cabral]] || Snow || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 2006\n| Cabral || [[Henry Paulson|Paulson]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 2009\n| [[Rosa Gumataotao Rios|Rios]] || [[Timothy Geithner|Geithner]] || Green\n|-\n| Federal Reserve Note\n| 2013\n| Rios || [[Jack Lew|Lew]] || Green\n|-\n|Federal Reserve Note\n| 2017A\n| [[Jovita Carranza|Carranza]] || [[Steven T. Mnuchin|Mnuchin]] || Green\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Where's George?]]\n\n==References==\n{{Portal|Money|Numismatics|United States}}\n{{Reflist}}\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{cite book\n  | last = Wilhite\n  | first = Robert\n  | title = Standard Catalog of United States Paper Money (17th ed)\n  | publisher = Krause Pubns Inc\n  | year = 1998\n  | isbn = 0-87341-653-8\n  | url-access = registration\n  | url = https://archive.org/details/standardcatalogo0000krau\n  }}\n*{{cite book\n  | last = Hudgeons\n  | first = Thomas\n  | title = The Official Blackbook Price Guide to U.S. Paper Money 2006, Edition #38\n  | publisher = House of Collectibles\n  | year = 2005\n  | isbn = 1-4000-4845-1\n  | url-access = registration\n  | url = https://archive.org/details/officialblackboo00thom_2\n  }}\n*{{cite book\n  | last = Friedberg\n  | first = Arthur\n  |author2=Ira Friedberg |author3=David Bowers\n   | title = A Guide Book Of United States Paper Money: Complete Source for History, Grading, and Prices (Official Red Book)\n  | publisher = Whitman Publishing\n  | year= 2005\n  | isbn = 0-7948-1786-6 }}\n* [http://federalnewsradio.com/index.php?nid=78&pid=&sid=835259 Honest Abe to Get Makeover on $5 Bill (AP via Federal News Radio)]\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.portfolio.com/interactive-features/2008/02/New-Five Interactive graphic] from Portfolio.com. Shows the design features and history of the $5 bill. Also, compares security features to that of the Euro.\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/19970530190833/http://www.bep.treas.gov/ Bureau of Engraving and Printing]\n*[http://www.federalreserve.gov/ Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve]\n*[http://www.secretservice.gov/ U.S. Secret Service]\n\n{{US currency and coinage|state=expanded}}\n{{Abraham Lincoln}}\n\n[[Category:1861 establi