ica | volume = 35 | issue = I | pages = 8\u201319 | date = September 1960 | pmid = 13765069 | doi = 10.1530/acta.0.XXXV0008 }}</ref><ref name=\"McKinnonSquires2011\">{{cite book| first1 = Angus O. | last1 = McKinnon | first2 = Edward L. | last2 = Squires | first3 = Wendy E. | last3 = Vaala | first4 = Dickson D. | last4 = Varner | name-list-format = vanc |title=Equine Reproduction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QPJQT6-g-YMC&pg=PT4462|date=5 July 2011|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-0-470-96187-2|pages=4462\u2013}}</ref><ref name=\"ProgramResources2013\">{{cite book|author1=Committee to Review the Bureau of Land Management Wild Horse and Burro Management Program|author2=Board on Agriculture and Natural Resources|author3=Division on Earth and Life Studies|author4=National Research Council|title=Using Science to Improve the BLM Wild Horse and Burro Program: A Way Forward|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0T5eAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA120|date=4 October 2013|publisher=National Academies Press|isbn=978-0-309-26494-5|pages=120\u2013}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Steroidal antiandrogen]]\n* [[List of steroidal antiandrogens]]\n* [[Allylnortestosterone]]\n* [[Ethinyltestosterone]]\n* [[Vinyltestosterone]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|32em}}\n\n{{Androgen receptor modulators}}\n\n[[Category:Abandoned drugs]]\n[[Category:Tertiary alcohols]]\n[[Category:Allyl compounds]]\n[[Category:Androstanes]]\n[[Category:Enones]]\n[[Category:Steroidal antiandrogens]]\n\n{{Steroid-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Fswitzer4", "label": "safe", "comment": "added FDA UNII to drug box", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allyltestosterone"}
{"title_page": "Kate Nicholson", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist\n| name          = Kate Nicholson\n| image         =\n| imagesize     =\n| caption       =\n| birth_name     =\n| birth_date     = 1929\n| birth_place      = Bankshead, Brampton\n| death_date     = April 2019\n| death_place    =\n| nationality   = [[England|English]]\n| field         = [[Painting]]\n| training      = [[Bath Academy of Art]]\n| movement      = [[Penwith Society of Arts]]\n| works         =\n| patrons       =\n| awards        =\n}}\n'''Kate Nicholson''' (1929-2019) was an English painter and the daughter of artist [[Ben Nicholson]] and his first wife, the artist [[Winifred Nicholson]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn at Bankshead, Cumbria in 1929,<ref>http://www.cornwall.gov.uk/index.cfm?articleid=29071 {{dead link|date=July 2016}}</ref> Kate Nicholson studied at the [[Bath Academy of Art]] from 1949 to 1954 where she was a pupil of Peter Lanyon,<ref>http://www.kettlesyard.co.uk/collection/biog.php?w_artist=Kate+Nicholson&Search=-+submit+- {{dead link|date=July 2016}}</ref> a St Ives artist and friend of her father and stepmother [[Barbara Hepworth]]. She taught art at Totnes High School for two years before she moved to St Ives herself in 1957 and became a member of the [[Penwith Society of Arts]].<ref name=\"Spalding\">{{cite book|author=[[Frances Spalding]]|publisher=Antique Collectors' Club|year=1990|title=20th Century Painters and Sculptors |ISBN=1 85149 106 6}}</ref>  She painted alongside her mother in the 1960s and 1970s, the two often visiting Greece together, as well as North Africa, and to the Isle of Eigg in the Hebrides in 1980. \nIn addition to Kate and her parents, the Nicholson family also produced several other artists, including her grandparents, [[William Nicholson (artist)|William Nicholson]] and [[Mabel Pryde]], aunt [[Nancy Nicholson]] and half-brother [[Simon Nicholson]], and half sister Painter Rachel Nicholson.\n\nShe died in 2019, aged 89. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2019/may/07/kate-nicholson-obituary|title=Kate Nicholson obituary|first=Jovan|last=Nicholson|date=May 7, 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n=Solo Exhibitions=\n\n* 1959 Waddington Gallery\n* 1962 Waddington Gallery\n* 1966 Marjorie Parr Gallery\n* 1968 Marjorie Parr Gallery\n* 1970 Marjorie Parr Gallery\n* 1972 Mignon Gallery, Bath\n* 1974 Northern Arts Gallery, Newcastle\n* 1975 LYC Museum and Art Gallery\n* 1981 LYC Museum and Art Gallery\n* 1985 Wills Lane Gallery, St Ives\n* 2013 Belgrave Gallery, St Ives\n* 2016 Belgrave Gallery, St Ives\n* 2019 Falmouth Art Gallery \n\n=Further Reading=\n* David Brown ''St Ives 1939-64: Twenty Five Years of Painting, Sculpture and Pottery'', The Tate Gallery, 1985 {{ISBN|0946590206}}\n* Christopher Andreae ''Kate Nicholson'', Belgrave Gallery, St Ives, 2013 {{ISBN|9780956890627}}\n* Jovan Nicholson ''Kate Nicholson'', Philip Wilson Publishers, 2019 {{ISBN|9781781300879}}\n\n=See Also=\n* [[List of St. Ives artists]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Art UK bio}}\n* [https://www.kettlesyard.co.uk/collection/collection-database/?artist=4782&title=&type= Kate Nicholson, paintings in Kettle's Yard collection]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nicholson, Kate}}\n[[Category:1929 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:English women painters]]\n[[Category:Nicholson arts family|Kate]]\n[[Category:21st-century British women artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist\n| name          = Kate Nicholson\n| image         =\n| imagesize     =\n| caption       =\n| birth_name     =\n| birth_date     = 1929\n| birth_place      = Bankshead, Brampton\n| death_date     = April 2019\n| death_place    =\n| nationality   = [[England|English]]\n| field         = [[Painting]]\n| training      = [[Bath Academy of Art]]\n| movement      = [[Penwith Society of Arts]]\n| works         =\n| patrons       =\n| awards        =\n}}\n'''Kate Nicholson''' (1929-2019) was an English painter and the daughter of artist [[Ben Nicholson]] and his first wife, the artist [[Winifred Nicholson]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn at Bankshead, Cumbria in 1929,<ref>http://www.cornwall.gov.uk/index.cfm?articleid=29071 {{dead link|date=July 2016}}</ref> Kate Nicholson studied at the [[Bath Academy of Art]] from 1949 to 1954 where she was a pupil of Peter Lanyon,<ref>http://www.kettlesyard.co.uk/collection/biog.php?w_artist=Kate+Nicholson&Search=-+submit+- {{dead link|date=July 2016}}</ref> a St Ives artist and friend of her father and stepmother [[Barbara Hepworth]]. She taught art at Totnes High School for two years before she moved to St Ives herself in 1957 and became a member of the [[Penwith Society of Arts]].<ref name=\"Spalding\">{{cite book|author=[[Frances Spalding]]|publisher=Antique Collectors' Club|year=1990|title=20th Century Painters and Sculptors |ISBN=1 85149 106 6}}</ref>  She painted alongside her mother in the 1960s and 1970s, the two often visiting Greece together, as well as North Africa. \nIn addition to Kate and her parents, the Nicholson family also produced several other artists, including her grandparents, [[William Nicholson (artist)|William Nicholson]] and [[Mabel Pryde]], aunt [[Nancy Nicholson]] and half-brother [[Simon Nicholson]], and half sister Painter Rachel Nicholson.\n\nShe died in 2019, aged 89. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2019/may/07/kate-nicholson-obituary|title=Kate Nicholson obituary|first=Jovan|last=Nicholson|date=May 7, 2019|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n=Solo Exhibitions=\n\n* 1959 Waddington Gallery\n* 1962 Waddington Gallery\n* 1966 Marjorie Parr Gallery\n* 1968 Marjorie Parr Gallery\n* 1970 Marjorie Parr Gallery\n* 1972 Mignon Gallery, Bath\n* 1974 Northern Arts Gallery, Newcastle\n* 1975 LYC Museum and Art Gallery\n* 1981 LYC Museum and Art Gallery\n* 1985 Wills Lane Gallery, St Ives\n* 2013 Belgrave Gallery, St Ives\n* 2016 Belgrave Gallery, St Ives\n* 2019 Falmouth Art Gallery \n\n=Further Reading=\n* David Brown ''St Ives 1939-64: Twenty Five Years of Painting, Sculpture and Pottery'', The Tate Gallery, 1985 {{ISBN|0946590206}}\n* Christopher Andreae ''Kate Nicholson'', Belgrave Gallery, St Ives, 2013 {{ISBN|9780956890627}}\n* Jovan Nicholson ''Kate Nicholson'', Philip Wilson Publishers, 2019 {{ISBN|9781781300879}}\n\n=See Also=\n* [[List of St. Ives artists]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Art UK bio}}\n* [https://www.kettlesyard.co.uk/collection/collection-database/?artist=4782&title=&type= Kate Nicholson, paintings in Kettle's Yard collection]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nicholson, Kate}}\n[[Category:1929 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:English women painters]]\n[[Category:Nicholson arts family|Kate]]\n[[Category:21st-century British women artists]]\n", "name_user": "Northernarthistorian", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kate_Nicholson"}
{"title_page": "Administrative divisions of Ukraine", "text_new": "{{Ukraine subdivisions sidebar}}\n\n[[Ukraine]] is divided into several levels of [[territorial entities]]. On the first level there are 27 regions:<ref>[http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 Regions of Ukraine and their composition] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |date=2011-12-26 }}. [[Verkhovna Rada]] website.</ref> [[Oblasts of Ukraine|24 oblasts]], one [[Autonomous Republic of Crimea|autonomous republic]] and two \"[[City with special status|cities with special status]]\".<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=zm0WAQAAIAAJ&q=Ukraine+27+regions:+24+oblasts,+autonomous+republic+cities+with+special+status&dq=Ukraine+27+regions:+24+oblasts,+autonomous+republic+cities+with+special+status&hl=nl&sa=X&ei=Rr_VUrrHGKSr0QXB-4HgDg&ved=0CIEBEOgBMAk Politics and society in Ukraine] by [[Paul D'Anieri]], [[Robert Kravchuk]], and [[Taras Kuzio]], [[Westview Press]], 1999, {{ISBN|0-8133-3538-8}} (page 292)</ref> Following the [[2014 Crimean crisis]], [[Autonomous Republic of Crimea|Crimea]] and [[Sevastopol]] became ''[[de facto]]'' administrated by the [[Russian Federation]], which [[Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation|claims them]] as the [[Republic of Crimea]] and the [[Federal cities of Russia|federal city]] of [[Sevastopol]]. Most states have not recognised them as being Russian territory.\n\nThe administrative division in Ukraine was [[Administrative divisions of the Ukrainian SSR|directly inherited]] (grandfathered) from the [[Republics of the Soviet Union|local republican]] administration of the [[Soviet Union]], the [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic]], and has not changed significantly since the middle of the 20th century. It is somewhat complex, as beside having several levels of a territorial subdivision it also has a classification for various [[Populated places in Ukraine|populated places]], particularly [[Cities of Ukraine|cities]].\n\n==Overview==\n{{confusing|date=December 2014}}\n{{refimprove section|date=December 2014}}\n{{See also|Local government in Ukraine}}\n[[File:Administrative divisions of Ukraine improved.jpg|thumb|400px|Simple flow chart of administrative divisions of Ukraine]]\n\nAccording to the Article 133 of [[Constitution of Ukraine]], \"the system of the administrative and territorial structure of Ukraine is composed of the Autonomous Republic of Crimea, oblasts, districts, cities, districts in city, settlements, and villages.\" Note, that although certain types of subdivision are not mentioned in Constitution of Ukraine (i.e. rural settlements), they are mentioned for regional composition. Also, for disambiguation regular raions (districts) are sometimes denoted as rural to distinguish them from raions in city.<ref name=regions/>\n\nUkraine's administrative divisions are divided as follows:\n*By geographical characteristics the units are divided on regions (such as autonomous republic, oblasts, districts, cities with special status) and places of settlement (cities, towns, villages).\n*By their status they can be administrative-territorial units (oblasts and districts), self-governed territorial units (cities, towns, villages). Also the autonomous republic has a unique status of territorial autonomy, while districts in cities combine both characteristics of administrative territorial as well as self-governed territorial units.\n*By position in the system of administrative division of Ukraine, the units divided into territorial units of ''prime level'' (cities w/o district division, districts in cities, towns, villages), of ''middle level'' (districts, cities with district division), and of ''higher level'' (autonomous republic, oblasts, cities with special status).\n*Administrative division has changed because some territories are not under the control of the government. For example, Sievierodonetsk has become the new central regional center.\n\nRegions, cities, districts are governed by a state administration, a chief of which is appointed by the president after a nomination by the [[Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine|cabinet of ministers]].<ref>[http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/382028.html Poroshenko to sign Saakashvili\u2019s resignation if Cabinet submits motion], [[Interfax-Ukraine]] (7 November 2016)</ref> Crimea has its own cabinet of ministers, however the state administration is represented by the office of the Presidential Representative of Ukraine. A basic and the lowest level of administrative division is a settlement that is governed by a local council (rada). Cities as a settlement always carry a special status within a region and have their own form of self-administration (municipality \u2013 ''vykonkom'') and some may consist of their own city's districts (raions). City municipalities are governed by a mayor and a city council (miskrada). Some smaller cities, towns, and rural localities may be under control of city municipalities based on larger cities. Towns as well as villages are not controlled by state administration and are self-governed by either a town council (selyshchna rada) or a village council (silrada) within the limits of the Constitution and the laws of Ukraine (article 140 of the Constitution of Ukraine). Village councils may carry a combined jurisdiction which may include several villages and hamlets (selyshche). Unlike villages, each town council always has a separate jurisdiction which may be part of bigger city's council. Hamlet (selyshche) is a non-governed rural locality and is governed by a village council of nearby village.\n\n===Table===\nUkraine is divided into 3 main administrative divisions: [[oblast]] (region), [[raion]] (district), and council (city, settlement, and village). Note, settlements such as cities do not necessary constitute the basic level of the Ukrainian administrative territorial system. For that purpose cities are categorized into own three categories that correspond to each level of subdivisions. Cities with special status and regional significance beside being divided into special districts in city may also include smaller cities (district significance), settlements, and/or villages. Please, note that the settlement's population size is not the only factor for its status. The final decision on status change is carried out by the [[Ukrainian parliament]]. The following table is based on the [[Ukrainian Census (2001)|2001 Ukrainian Census]].<ref name=\"cen2001\"/>\n\n<!-- Please, do not update the table to current statistical data! -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Level of division<ref name=regions>[http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 Regions of Ukraine and their composition] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |date=2011-12-26 }}. [[Ukrainian parliament]] website.</ref> !! Territory !! Total !! Corresponding settlements !! Total !! [[Populated places in Ukraine|Total urban/rural]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1 (''regions'') || [[Autonomous Republic of Crimea|autonomous republic]] || 1 || rowspan=\"2\"| [[cities with special status]]{{efn|group=1|City municipalities that are administrated as a separate region.}} || rowspan=\"2\"| 2 || rowspan=\"6\"| 1,344\n|-\n| [[Oblasts of Ukraine|oblasts]]{{efn|group=1|Often translated as [[province]]}} || 24\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2 (''regional subdivisions'') || [rural] [[Raions of Ukraine|districts]]{{efn|group=1|Normally identification of rural is not used with raions, while for disambiguation districts in cities are identified with those cities.}} || 490 || rowspan=\"2\"| [[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|cities of regional significance]]{{efn|group=1|Regional municipalities may include cities of oblast or republican (in case of Crimea) significance.}} || rowspan=\"2\"| 178\n|-\n| [urban] [[Urban districts of Ukraine|districts in cities]] || 118\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 3 (''communities''){{efn|group=1|small municipalities (councils)}} || city councils || 454 || [[City of district significance (Ukraine)|cities of district significance]] || 274\n|-\n| [[Settlement council (Ukraine)|settlement councils]]{{efn|group=1|Often times, the identification of \"urban\" with \"settlement\" is not used and raises some ambiguity with smaller rural settlements.}} || 783 || individual urban-type settlements{{efn|group=1|Also referred to as towns.}} || 890\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Rural council (Ukraine)|village councils]] || rowspan=\"2\" | 10,278 || individual villages || 27,190 || rowspan=\"2\" | 28,621\n|-\n| [rural] settlements{{efn|group=1|Normally identification of rural is not used.}} || 1,266\n|}\n\n===List===\nThe following numbers are based on the [[Ukrainian Census (2001)|2001 Ukrainian Census]].<ref name=cen2001>[http://2001.ukrcensus.gov.ua/regions/ Administrative division of Ukraine in 2001]</ref>\n\n*Top level (Regions, 27):<ref name=regions/>\n**[[Autonomous Republic of Crimea]]\n**[[Oblasts of Ukraine]] (24)\n**[[Cities with special status]]: [[Kiev|Kyiv]] and [[Sevastopol]]\n*Middle level (Regional subdivision, 786):\n**Raions (490)\n**[[Cities of oblast significance (Ukraine)|Cities of oblast significance]] (178)\n**[[Raions of cities in Ukraine|City districts]] (\u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0438 \u0443 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0445) (118)\n*Primary level (Local communities, 11,515):\n**Cities of raion significance (276)\n**Urban-type settlements (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0430 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0438\u043f\u0443) (885)\n**Villages (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0430) (27,190)\n**Rural-type settlements (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0430) (1,266)\nTotal cities: 454, an increase of 20 compared with the 1989 census.<ref name=cen2001/>\n\n==History==\n{{Main|Administrative divisions development in Ukraine|Ukrainian historical regions}}\n\nBefore the introduction of oblasts in 1932, Ukraine comprised 40 [[Okruhas of Ukriane|okruha]]s, which had replaced the former [[Russian Empire|Russian Imperial]] [[guberniya]] (governorate) subdivisions.\n\nIn 1932 the territory of the Ukrainian SSR was re-established based on oblasts. Excluded in the administrative changes was [[Western Ukraine]], which at that time formed part of the [[Second Polish Republic]] and shared in the Polish form of administrative division based on [[Voivodeships of Poland|voivodeships]].\n\nIn the post-[[World War II]] period, the [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic]] consisted of [[Administrative divisions of the Ukrainian SSR|25 oblasts and two cities with special status]].\n\nAfter the fall of the Soviet Union in 1991, Crimea obtained the status of an autonomous republic with its own government instead of a regional state administration.\n\n==Regions==\n{{Ukraine Labelled Map|float=right}}\n\n===Autonomous republic===\n{{Main|Autonomous Republic of Crimea}}\n\nThe Autonomous Republic of Crimea, formerly the Crimean Oblast of the Ukrainian SSR, geographically encompasses the major portion of the Crimean peninsula in southern [[Ukraine]]. Its capital is [[Simferopol]]. The Autonomous Republic of Crimea is the only region within Ukraine that possesses its own constitution.\n\nOn March 16, 2014, after the occupation of Crimea by the Russian military, a referendum on joining the Russian Federation was conducted. A majority of votes supported the measure. On March 21, 2014, the Russian Duma voted to annex Crimea as a [[Republic of Crimea|subject]] into the Russian Federation. The Ukrainian government does not recognize the referendum or annexation of Crimea as legitimate. On March 27, the UN General Assembly passed [[United Nations General Assembly Resolution 68/262|Resolution 68/262]] by 100 to 11 votes, recognizing the referendum as invalid and denying any legal change in the status of Crimea and Sevastopol.\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n! Autonomous Republic of Crimea\n! [[Representatives of the President of Ukraine]]\n! Area (km<sup>2</sup>)\n! Population (2010)\n! Pop. density\n! Administrative centre\n! Raions/Districts\n! Cities of regional significance {{#tag:ref|\"[[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|cities of regional significance]]\" is a translation of {{lang-uk|\u041c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f}}.|group=\"nb\"}}\n|-\n|{{flag|Crimea}}\n|Nataliya Popovych\n|26,100\n|1,966,801\n|75\n|[[Simferopol]]<ref>temporarily in [[Kherson]]</ref>\n|14\n|11\n|-\n|}\n\n===Oblasts===\n{{Main|Oblasts of Ukraine}}\n\nOblasts are on the first (top) level of the administrative division of Ukraine.\n \nAlmost every oblast is named after its administrative center, except for four oblasts. Volyn' and Zakarpattia, whose respective capitals are Lutsk and Uzhhorod, are named after historic regions [[Volhynia]] and [[Carpathian Ruthenia|Transcarpathia]]. The administrative centers of the Dnipropetrovsk Oblast and the Kirovohrad Oblast were renamed to Dnipro and Kropyvnytskyi in 2016, however as of 2017 the oblasts still officially bear the old soviet names as their change must be reflected in an amendment to the Ukrainian Constitution. \n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n! Region\n! Area (km<sup>2</sup>)\n! Population (2010)\n! Pop. density\n! Administrative center\n! Raions/Districts\n! Cities of regional significance {{#tag:ref|\"[[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|cities of regional significance]]\" is a translation of {{lang-uk|\u041c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f}}.|group=\"nb\"}}\n|-\n|{{flag|Cherkasy Oblast}}\n|20,891\n|1,291,135\n|61.80\n|[[Cherkasy]]\n|20\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Chernihiv Oblast}}\n|31,851.3\n|1,104,241\n|34.67\n|[[Chernihiv]]\n|22\n|3\n|-\n|{{flag|Chernivtsi Oblast}}\n|8,093.6\n|903,782\n|111.67\n|[[Chernivtsi]]\n|11\n|2\n|-\n|{{flag|Dnipropetrovsk Oblast}}\n|31,900.5\n|3,344,073\n|104.83\n|[[Dnipro]]\n|22\n|13\n|-\n|{{flag|Donetsk Oblast}}\n|26,505.7\n|4,448,031\n|167.81\n|[[Donetsk]]\n|18\n|28\n|-\n|{{flag|Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast}}\n|13,894.0\n|1,380,770\n|99.38\n|[[Ivano-Frankivsk]]\n|14\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Kharkiv Oblast}}\n|31,401.6\n|2,755,177\n|87.74\n|[[Kharkiv]]\n|27\n|7\n|-\n|{{flag|Kherson Oblast}}\n|28,449\n|1,091,151\n|38.35\n|[[Kherson]]\n|18\n|3\n|-\n|{{flag|Khmelnytskyi Oblast}}\n|20,636.2\n|1,331,534\n|64.52\n|[[Khmelnytskyi, Ukraine|Khmelnytskyi]]\n|20\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Kyiv Oblast}}\n|28,118.9\n|1,719,602\n|61.15\n|[[Kiev|Kyiv]]\n|25\n|13\n|-\n|{{flag|Kirovohrad Oblast}}\n|24,577.5\n|1,014,809\n|41.29\n|[[Kropyvnytskyi]]\n|21\n|4\n|-\n|{{flag|Luhansk Oblast}}\n|26,672.5\n|2,300,412\n|86.25\n|[[Luhansk]]\n|18\n|14\n|-\n|{{flag|Lviv Oblast}}\n|21,823.7\n|2,545,634\n|116.65\n|[[Lviv]]\n|20\n|9\n|-\n|{{flag|Mykolaiv Oblast}}\n|24,587.4\n|1,186,452\n|48.25\n|[[Mykolaiv]]\n|19\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Odessa Oblast|Odesa Oblast}}\n|33,295.9\n|2,387,636\n|71.71\n|[[Odessa]]\n|26\n|7\n|-\n|{{flag|Poltava Oblast}}\n|28,735.8\n|1,493,668\n|51.98\n|[[Poltava]]\n|25\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Rivne Oblast}}\n|20,038.5\n|1,152,576\n|57.52\n|[[Rivne]]\n|16\n|4\n|-\n|{{flag|Sumy Oblast}}\n|23,823.9\n|1,166,765\n|48.97\n|[[Sumy]]\n|18\n|7\n|-\n|{{flag|Ternopil Oblast}}\n|13,817.1\n|1,086,694\n|78.65\n|[[Ternopil]]\n|17\n|1\n|-\n|{{flag|Vinnytsia Oblast}}\n|26,501.6\n|1,646,250\n|62.12\n|[[Vinnytsia]]\n|27\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Volyn Oblast}} \n|20,135.3\n|1,038,223\n|51.56\n|[[Lutsk]]\n|16\n|4\n|-\n|{{flag|Zakarpattia Oblast}} \n|12,771.5\n|1,246,323\n|97.59\n|[[Uzhhorod]]\n|13\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Zaporizhia Oblast}}\n|27,168.5\n|1,805,431\n|66.45\n|[[Zaporizhia]]\n|20\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Zhytomyr Oblast}}\n|29,819.2\n|1,283,201\n|43.03\n|[[Zhytomyr]]\n|23\n|5\n|}\n\n===Cities with special status===\n{{Main|Cities with special status}}\n\nTwo cities carry special status: the city of [[Kyiv]] which is the capital of Ukraine and the city of [[Sevastopol]]. Following the [[2014 Crimean crisis]], Sevastopol is controlled by Russia and is incorporated as a [[Federal subjects of Russia|federal subject of Russia]]. It is recognized as a part of Ukraine by most of the international community.\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n!City\n! [[Chief of Local State Administration (Ukraine)|Governor]]{{#tag:ref|Chairman of the Regional (or City) State Administration.|group=\"nb\"}}\n! Area\n! Population (2010)\n|-\n|{{flag|Kyiv}}\n|[[Vitali Klitschko]]{{#tag:ref|[[Vitaliy Klychko]] serves both as a mayor and a governor for the city of Kiev since 25 June 2014 (see [[Mayor of Kyiv]]).|group=\"nb\"}}\n|{{convert|323.9|sqmi|km2|order=flip|abbr=on}}\n|2,782,016\n|-\n|{{flag|Sevastopol}}\n|''[[Governor of Sevastopol (Ukraine)|vacant]]''\n|{{convert|416.6|sqmi|km2|order=flip|abbr=on}}\n|380,301\n|-\n|}\n\n==Second-level subdivision units==\n\n===Cities of regional significance (regional cities)===\n{{Main|City of regional significance (Ukraine)}}\n\n===Raions===\n{{Main|Raions of Ukraine}}\n[[Raions of Ukraine|Raions]] are smaller territorial units of subdivision in Ukraine. There are 490 raions.\n\n===Urban districts===\n{{Main|Urban districts of Ukraine}}\n\n==Councils==\n{{details|Populated places in Ukraine}}\n[[File:Dniepr river in Kyiv.jpg|thumb|The [[Dnieper River]] plays an important part in Ukrainian territorial division, with many large cities settled on its banks. Here, the capital city of [[Kiev|Kyiv]] which was founded on the Dnieper's right bank but for now expanded over the river significantly.]]\n\n{| border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=2 style=\"text-align:left; border:1px solid #ddd; font-size:90%;\" summary=\"\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2 | Status<ref>{{cite web|title=Regions of Ukraine and their composition |url=http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |work=[[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]] |accessdate=25 December 2011 |language=Ukrainian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |archivedate=26 December 2011 }}</ref>\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | Status (in [[Ukrainian Language|Ukrainian]])\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{nowrap|Total Number (in 2006)}}\n|- style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"\n|colspan=2|'''[[city|misto / city]]''' || \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e || style=\"text-align:right;\" | '''457'''\n|-\n|&nbsp; || municipality|| \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0437\u0456 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u0446\u0456\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 2\n|-\n|&nbsp; || misto \u043eblastnoho znachennia || \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 176\n|-\n|&nbsp; || misto raionnoho znachennia || \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 279\n|- style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"\n|colspan=2|'''[[urban-type settlement|selyshche miskoho typu / town]]''' || \u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0438\u043f\u0443 || style=\"text-align:right;\" | '''886'''\n|- style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"\n|colspan=2|'''[[village|selo / village]]''' || \u0441\u0456\u043b\u044c\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442 || style=\"text-align:right;\" | '''28,552'''\n|-\n|&nbsp; || selysche || \u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 1,364\n|-\n|&nbsp; || selo || \u0441\u0435\u043b\u043e || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 27,188\n|}\n\nUkraine has two types of settlements: rural and urban. Rural populated areas (\u0441\u0456\u043b\u044c\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442) can be either a village (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u043e, [[Village#Slavic countries|selo]]) or a rural settlement (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435). Urban populated areas (\u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442) can be either a city (\u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442o) or an [[urban-type settlement]] (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0438\u043f\u0443). For the sake of brevity, urbanized settlements are sometimes classified as towns in the [[English language]].\n\nChanges to a settlement's status can be made only by the [[Verkhovna Rada]]. Please note that the size of a settlement does not ultimately define its status, although is a major factor. For example, the city of [[Prypiat (city)|Prypiat]] still retains its status, while having a population of zero, due to its infrastructure, including buildings, roads, and utility networks.\n\nThe typical Ukrainian ''misto'' ought to be considered a [[city]], not a [[town]] (compare to [[City status in the United Kingdom]]). However, the city's subordination to either an oblast or raion also should be taken into account, especially in the [[political]] sense. Some of urbanized settlements may be cities of raion subordination, although it could seem confusing, a type of settlement should be considered first as its status is given for administrative purposes.\n\n===Cities===\n{{see also|List of cities in Ukraine}}\n[[File:Kyiv province location map.svg|thumb|left|[[Kiev Oblast]] for instance, has several regional city municipalities such as [[Pereiaslav]], for example, that are under direct subordination to the regional authorities. They are officially known as cities of regional significance.]]\n[[File:Drohobycz ulica stryjska 2008.jpg|thumb|[[Drohobych]], is a city of oblast subordinance, subordinate to the [[Lviv Oblast]] authorities rather than to the local [[Drohobych Raion]] administration.]]\nAccording to Ukrainian law a city (\u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e) in Ukraine is a locality of at least 10,000 people.<ref name=UCSMBS>[https://books.google.com/books?id=QcoodEOmnMUC&pg=PA151&dq=Ukraine+city+10,000+people&hl=nl&sa=X&ei=v1fvU5b8LcSIOMPDgfgO&ved=0CCcQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Ukraine%20city%2010%2C000%20people&f=false A Geography of Russia and Its Neighbors] by Mikhail S. Blinnikov, [[Guilford Press]], 2010, {{ISBN|1606239201}} (page 151)</ref> Cities may carry various status. Some may be of national importance, others of [[city of regional significance (Ukraine)|regional (oblast) importance]], and the rest of district (raion) importance. For example, the cities of ''Kiev'' and of ''Sevastopol'' have special status of national significance and each is officially classified as a ''city with a special status'', which administratively is equivalent to an oblast. Mayors of those cities, in general, as are governors of oblasts, are appointed by the [[President of Ukraine]]. However, the status of the mayor of Kiev is somewhat more complex, and for further information see [[Legal status and local government of Kiev]]. The status of Sevastopol is also unique.\n\nAlmost every oblast has at least one city of regional subordination (importance), which is the administrative center (capital) of that oblast. However, some other big cities within the oblast may have such status as well. The cities of oblast subordination have the same importance of a raion, and often are the administrative centers of such. In addition to regular raions, several Ukrainian cities with national or oblast status are further divided into ''city raions'' which may include other cities, towns, and/or villages. In 2010, Ukraine had 23 such cities with their own city raions.\n\nMany '''raions''' also have city municipalities of its level of subordination (importance). Those are usually the administrative centers (capitals). Notice that not all raions have a city as their administrative center; however all the raion centers are at least urban-like (urbanized). All administrative centers have their own form of self-administration. The municipalities of a raion subordination may administer several adjacent local councils (municipalities), usually rural. If a raion has several cities of raion (district) level, they may share administrative power for the raion.\n\n===Other municipalities===\nIn addition to city municipalities, Ukraine has urban-like municipalities. The lowest form of self-administration are the rural municipalities and villages. A rural municipality may consist of a single village, usually big, or a combination of other rural villages or localities. Note that some villages also have some additional, very small settlements. Those settlements, together with the home village, combine a local (rural) municipality (silrada). For simplicity's sake, a silrada (rural municipality) is usually referred to as a village and is the lowest level of administrative division. The status of any settlement is granted by the [[Verkhovna Rada]].\n\n===Amalgamated hromadas (AHs)===\nIn his draft [[Ukraine's constitution|constitutional]] amendments of June 2014 [[Ukrainian President]] [[Petro Poroshenko]] proposed changing the administrative divisions of Ukraine, which should include regions, districts and \"hromadas\".<ref>[http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/211043.html Poroshenko suggests granting status of regions to Crimea, Kyiv, Sevastopol, creating new political subdivision of 'community'] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701043549/http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/211043.html |date=2014-07-01 }}, [[Interfax-Ukraine]] (26 June 2014)</ref>\n\nOn February 5, 2015, the law \"On voluntary association of territorial communities\" was adopted creating ''Amalgamated hromadas (communities)'' meaning [[Settlement council (Ukraine)|settlement councils]], [[Rural council (Ukraine)|rural councils]] and a [[City of district significance (Ukraine)|city of district significance]] can create a new administrative unit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://reformsguide.org.ua/reforms/decentralizationreform/|title=Decentralization|date=2017-02-10|website=The Reforms Guide|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-28}}</ref> Any amalgamated hromada with a city as an administrative centre is an urban hromada, any amalgamated hromada with an urban-type settlement as an administrative centre is a settlement hromada, and any amalgamated hromada with a village as an administrative centre is a rural hromada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://decentralization.gov.ua/en/glossary|title=Glossary|date=|website=Decentralization Reform|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref> New local [[elections in Ukraine|elections]] in these united territorial communities were then held.<ref>[http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/472770.html Batkivschyna party says it gets most votes at local elections], [[Interfax Ukraine]] (25 December 2017)<br>[https://www.unian.info/politics/2316594-police-investigate-voter-bribing-cases-as-local-elections-held-in-51-territorial-communities.html Police investigate voter bribing cases as local elections held in 51 territorial communities], [[UNIAN]] (25 December 2017)</ref> 226 will be holding elections in 2018 and 2019.<ref>[http://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/ukrainealert/elections-are-around-the-corner-and-ukraine-s-political-parties-are-not-ready-2 Elections Are Around the Corner, and Ukraine\u2019s Political Parties Are Not Ready], [[Atlantic Council]] (6 December 2017)</ref> The first 252 were held in 2017.<ref>[https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45055-interim-report-on-observation-results-of-the-first-local-elections-in-united-territorial-communities-on-29-october-2017-19102017-26102017 INTERIM REPORT ON OBSERVATION RESULTS OF THE FIRST LOCAL ELECTIONS IN UNITED TERRITORIAL COMMUNITIES ON 29 October 2017 (19.10.2017 26.10.2017)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228223135/https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45055-interim-report-on-observation-results-of-the-first-local-elections-in-united-territorial-communities-on-29-october-2017-19102017-26102017 |date=28 December 2018 }}, [[PORA#OPORA|OPORA]] (31 October 2017)<br>[https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45165-ukraine-holds-elections-in-51-utcs-today Ukraine holds elections in 51 UTCs today] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171226020921/https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45165-ukraine-holds-elections-in-51-utcs-today |date=2017-12-26 }}, [[PORA#OPORA|OPORA]] (24 December 2017)</ref> \n\nThe Law \"On Local Self-Government in Ukraine\" stipulates that local budgets should have enough money to be administered by local self-government bodies.<ref name=\"Espresogr\"/> Because many of the small rural councils and cities of district significance could never hope to do this the new administrative unit ''Amalgamated hromada'' ([https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%9E%D0%B1%27%D1%94%D0%B4%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B0_%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80%D1%96%D0%B0%D0%BB%D1%8C%D0%BD%D0%B0_%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B0%D0%B4%D0%B0]{{lang-uk|\u041e\u0431'\u0454\u0434\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0456\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0433\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0434\u0430}}, ''Obyednana terytorial\u02b9na hromada'') was created.<ref name=\"Espresogr\">{{in lang|uk}} [https://espreso.tv/article/2017/10/30/vybory_v_obyednanykh_terytorialnykh_gromadakh_scho_ce_i_dlya_chogo_potribne Elections in the united territorial communities. What is this and what you need], [[Espreso TV]] (31 October 2017)</ref>\n\n==Other administrations==\n\nUkraine also has several settlements known as ''viiskove mistechko'' which were former military installations. Since the fall of the Soviet Union, the secrecy of such settlements has been unveiled, however, the towns are subordinated directly to the Ministry of Defense and do not have their own civil administrations. Such military installations are like ghost towns that are not even identified on a map. One of them, on the border of the [[Kiev Oblast|Kiev]] and [[Zhytomyr Oblast]]s is Makarov-1.<ref>{{cite news|title=In Kiev region a military installation cannot vote|url=http://podrobnosti.ua/video/podrobnosti/2010/10/31/727577.html|accessdate=8 February 2012|newspaper=[[Podrobnosti.ua]]|language=Russian|date=31 October 2012|format=Video|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120404114906/http://podrobnosti.ua/video/podrobnosti/2010/10/31/727577.html|archive-date=2012-04-04|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nA special territory known as the ''[[zone of alienation]]'' falls under the jurisdiction of the Ministry of Emergencies and was the most severely affected territory by the [[Chernobyl disaster]]. Additionally, various restricted nature preserves known as ''[[Zapovednik]]'' fall under the jurisdiction of the Ministry of Ecology. \n\nDue to the [[War in Donbass]], the status of [[Civil\u2013military administrations (Ukraine)|civil\u2013military administrations]] was created in territories of [[Donetsk Oblast|Donetsk]] and [[Luhansk Oblast|Luhansk]] oblasts where the respective local government units cannot exercise their constitutionally guaranteed powers.<ref name=pravda>{{cite news|title=Poroshenko gave the green light to create civil-military administrations|url=http://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2015/02/26/7059870/|accessdate=26 February 2015|work=[[Ukrayinska Pravda]]|date=26 February 2015|location=Ukrainian}}</ref>\n\n[[File:1201044 original (1).jpg|thumb|A mix of modern and old buildings in [[Dnipro]], located in [[Dnipropetrovsk Oblast]]. Dnipro's metropolitan area includes cities such as [[Kamianske]] and [[Novomoskovsk, Ukraine|Novomoskovsk]].]]\n\nCurrently, Ukraine has the following 3 enclaves:\n*The city of [[Slavutych]] which is administratively subordinated directly to [[Kiev Oblast]] while being completely surrounded by neighboring [[Chernihiv Oblast]].\n*The settlement of Bile which is located on [[Snake Island (Black Sea)|Snake Island]] and is fully surrounded by the [[Black Sea]] was established in 2007 and is part of [[Vylkove]], [[Odessa Oblast]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Selysche Bile, Odessa Oblast, Kiliya Raion, city Vylkove|url=http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/A005?rdat1=08.02.2012&rf7571=42441|work=Regions of Ukraine and their Structure|publisher=[[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]]|accessdate=8 February 2012|language=Ukrainian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303033059/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/A005?rdat1=08.02.2012&rf7571=42441|archive-date=2014-03-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*The town of [[Kotsiubynske]] which is part of the Kiev Oblast and is completely surrounded by the city of Kiev.\n\n===Metropolitan areas===\nUkraine has five major agglomerated metropolitan areas ([[conurbation]]s). These conurbation areas are not officially recognized and remain to be administered according to official [[oblast]]-[[raion]] system of subdivision.\n*[[Kiev metropolitan area|Kiev]] includes towns such as [[Irpin]], [[Boryspil]], and [[Fastiv]]\n*Kharkiv includes towns such as [[Chuhuiv]], [[Merefa]], and numerous other settlements\n*Donetsk includes towns such as [[Makiivka]], [[Khartsyzk]], and others\n*Dnipro with [[Kamianske]] and [[Novomoskovsk, Ukraine|Novomoskovsk]]\n*Odessa with [[Chornomorsk]] and [[Ovidiopol]]\n\n==Other divisions==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2016}} \n[[File:Ukraine KIIS-Regional-division2.png|thumb|Kiev International Institute of Sociology (KIIS) geographic division of Ukraine used in their polls.]]\nBeside the administrative divisions, geographical divisions are at times used for reference or statistical purposes. The division splits Ukraine into 4 to 6 geographic areas: [[Western Ukraine]], [[Eastern Ukraine]], [[Southern Ukraine]], [[Central Ukraine]], [[Northern Ukraine]] (occasionally used).\n\nThe neighboring countries such as Russia, Poland, Hungary and Romania sometimes identify certain parts of Ukraine. For example, Russia has territorial claims to Ukraine stating that the Southeastern Ukraine is part of Russia,{{fact|date=March 2017}} certain political or public figures in Poland lay territorial claims to [[western Ukraine]] identifying them as ''Borderlands'' or ''Kreis'' (Kresy),{{fact|date=March 2017}} the same goes for Hungary that calls [[Zakarpattia Oblast]] as K\u00e1rp\u00e1talja.{{fact|date=March 2017}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Ukraine}}\n* [[Geography of Ukraine]]\n* [[ISO 3166-2:UA]]\n* [[List_of_places_named_after_people#Ukraine|List of places named after people (Ukraine)]]\n* [[Local government in Ukraine]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|Atlas of Ukraine}}\n*{{cite web|title=Regions of Ukraine and their composition |url=http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |work=[[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]] |accessdate=25 December 2011 |language=Ukrainian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |archivedate=26 December 2011 }}\n*{{cite web|title=Ukraine Raions|url=http://www.statoids.com/yua.html|work=Statoids|accessdate=8 February 2012}}\n*{{cite web|title=Ukrainian cities and regions in alphabetical order|url=http://ukrainetrek.com/regions-by-alphabet|work=UkraineTrek|accessdate=10 February 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=Administrative territorial composition of Ukraine|url=http://www.minregion.gov.ua/attachments/content-attachments/1659/ATU.pdf|work=Ministry of Regional Development, Construction, and Communal Living|accessdate=5 April 2015}}{{Dead link|date=October 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Ukraine topics}}\n{{Administrative divisions of Ukraine}}\n{{Administrative divisions of Ukraine's regions}}\n{{Articles on first-level administrative divisions of European countries}}\n\n[[Category:Subdivisions of Ukraine| ]]\n[[Category:Country subdivisions in Europe|Ukraine]]\n", "text_old": "{{Ukraine subdivisions sidebar}}\n\n[[Ukraine]] is divided into several levels of [[territorial entities]]. On the first level there are 27 regions:<ref>[http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 Regions of Ukraine and their composition] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |date=2011-12-26 }}. [[Verkhovna Rada]] website.</ref> [[Oblasts of Ukraine|24 oblasts]], one [[Autonomous Republic of Crimea|autonomous republic]] and two \"[[City with special status|cities with special status]]\".<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=zm0WAQAAIAAJ&q=Ukraine+27+regions:+24+oblasts,+autonomous+republic+cities+with+special+status&dq=Ukraine+27+regions:+24+oblasts,+autonomous+republic+cities+with+special+status&hl=nl&sa=X&ei=Rr_VUrrHGKSr0QXB-4HgDg&ved=0CIEBEOgBMAk Politics and society in Ukraine] by [[Paul D'Anieri]], [[Robert Kravchuk]], and [[Taras Kuzio]], [[Westview Press]], 1999, {{ISBN|0-8133-3538-8}} (page 292)</ref> Following the [[2014 Crimean crisis]], [[Autonomous Republic of Crimea|Crimea]] and [[Sevastopol]] became ''[[de facto]]'' administrated by the [[Russian Federation]], which [[Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation|claims them]] as the [[Republic of Crimea]] and the [[Federal cities of Russia|federal city]] of [[Sevastopol]]. Most states have not recognised them as being Russian territory.\n\nThe administrative division in Ukraine was [[Administrative divisions of the Ukrainian SSR|directly inherited]] (grandfathered) from the [[Republics of the Soviet Union|local republican]] administration of the [[Soviet Union]], the [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic]], and has not changed significantly since the middle of the 20th century. It is somewhat complex, as beside having several levels of a territorial subdivision it also has a classification for various [[Populated places in Ukraine|populated places]], particularly [[Cities of Ukraine|cities]].\n\n==Overview==\n{{confusing|date=December 2014}}\n{{refimprove section|date=December 2014}}\n{{See also|Local government in Ukraine}}\n[[File:Administrative divisions of Ukraine improved.jpg|thumb|400px|Simple flow chart of administrative divisions of Ukraine]]\n\nAccording to the Article 133 of [[Constitution of Ukraine]], \"the system of the administrative and territorial structure of Ukraine is composed of the Autonomous Republic of Crimea, oblasts, districts, cities, districts in city, settlements, and villages.\" Note, that although certain types of subdivision are not mentioned in Constitution of Ukraine (i.e. rural settlements), they are mentioned for regional composition. Also, for disambiguation regular raions (districts) are sometimes denoted as rural to distinguish them from raions in city.<ref name=regions/>\n\nUkraine's administrative divisions are divided as follows:\n*By geographical characteristics the units are divided on regions (such as autonomous republic, oblasts, districts, cities with special status) and places of settlement (cities, towns, villages).\n*By their status they can be administrative-territorial units (oblasts and districts), self-governed territorial units (cities, towns, villages). Also the autonomous republic has a unique status of territorial autonomy, while districts in cities combine both characteristics of administrative territorial as well as self-governed territorial units.\n*By position in the system of administrative division of Ukraine, the units divided into territorial units of ''prime level'' (cities w/o district division, districts in cities, towns, villages), of ''middle level'' (districts, cities with district division), and of ''higher level'' (autonomous republic, oblasts, cities with special status).\n*Administrative division has changed because some territories are not under the control of the government. For example, Sievierodonetsk has become the new central regional center.\n\nRegions, cities, districts are governed by a state administration, a chief of which is appointed by the president after a nomination by the [[Cabinet of Ministers of Ukraine|cabinet of ministers]].<ref>[http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/382028.html Poroshenko to sign Saakashvili\u2019s resignation if Cabinet submits motion], [[Interfax-Ukraine]] (7 November 2016)</ref> Crimea has its own cabinet of ministers, however the state administration is represented by the office of the Presidential Representative of Ukraine. A basic and the lowest level of administrative division is a settlement that is governed by a local council (rada). Cities as a settlement always carry a special status within a region and have their own form of self-administration (municipality \u2013 ''vykonkom'') and some may consist of their own city's districts (raions). City municipalities are governed by a mayor and a city council (miskrada). Some smaller cities, towns, and rural localities may be under control of city municipalities based on larger cities. Towns as well as villages are not controlled by state administration and are self-governed by either a town council (selyshchna rada) or a village council (silrada) within the limits of the Constitution and the laws of Ukraine (article 140 of the Constitution of Ukraine). Village councils may carry a combined jurisdiction which may include several villages and hamlets (selyshche). Unlike villages, each town council always has a separate jurisdiction which may be part of bigger city's council. Hamlet (selyshche) is a non-governed rural locality and is governed by a village council of nearby village.\n\n===Table===\nUkraine is divided into 3 main administrative divisions: [[oblast]] (region), [[raion]] (district), and council (city, settlement, and village). Note, settlements such as cities do not necessary constitute the basic level of the Ukrainian administrative territorial system. For that purpose cities are categorized into own three categories that correspond to each level of subdivisions. Cities with special status and regional significance beside being divided into special districts in city may also include smaller cities (district significance), settlements, and/or villages. Please, note that the settlement's population size is not the only factor for its status. The final decision on status change is carried out by the [[Ukrainian parliament]]. The following table is based on the [[Ukrainian Census (2001)|2001 Ukrainian Census]].<ref name=\"cen2001\"/>\n\n<!-- Please, do not update the table to current statistical data! -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Level of division<ref name=regions>[http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 Regions of Ukraine and their composition] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |date=2011-12-26 }}. [[Ukrainian parliament]] website.</ref> !! Territory !! Total !! Corresponding settlements !! Total !! [[Populated places in Ukraine|Total urban/rural]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1 (''regions'') || [[Autonomous Republic of Crimea|autonomous republic]] || 1 || rowspan=\"2\"| [[cities with special status]]{{efn|group=1|City municipalities that are administrated as a separate region.}} || rowspan=\"2\"| 2 || rowspan=\"6\"| 1,344\n|-\n| [[Oblasts of Ukraine|oblasts]]{{efn|group=1|Often translated as [[province]]}} || 24\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2 (''regional subdivisions'') || [rural] [[Raions of Ukraine|districts]]{{efn|group=1|Normally identification of rural is not used with raions, while for disambiguation districts in cities are identified with those cities.}} || 490 || rowspan=\"2\"| [[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|cities of regional significance]]{{efn|group=1|Regional municipalities may include cities of oblast or republican (in case of Crimea) significance.}} || rowspan=\"2\"| 178\n|-\n| [urban] [[Urban districts of Ukraine|districts in cities]] || 118\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 3 (''communities''){{efn|group=1|small municipalities (councils)}} || city councils || 454 || [[City of district significance (Ukraine)|cities of district significance]] || 274\n|-\n| [[Settlement council (Ukraine)|settlement councils]]{{efn|group=1|Often times, the identification of \"urban\" with \"settlement\" is not used and raises some ambiguity with smaller rural settlements.}} || 783 || individual urban-type settlements{{efn|group=1|Also referred to as towns.}} || 890\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Rural council (Ukraine)|village councils]] || rowspan=\"2\" | 10,278 || individual villages || 27,190 || rowspan=\"2\" | 28,621\n|-\n| [rural] settlements{{efn|group=1|Normally identification of rural is not used.}} || 1,266\n|}\n\n===List===\nThe following numbers are based on the [[Ukrainian Census (2001)|2001 Ukrainian Census]].<ref name=cen2001>[http://2001.ukrcensus.gov.ua/regions/ Administrative division of Ukraine in 2001]</ref>\n\n*Top level (Regions, 27):<ref name=regions/>\n**[[Autonomous Republic of Crimea]]\n**[[Oblasts of Ukraine]] (24)\n**[[Cities with special status]]: [[Kiev|Kyiv]] and [[Sevastopol]]\n*Middle level (Regional subdivision, 786):\n**Raions (490)\n**[[Cities of oblast significance (Ukraine)|Cities of oblast significance]] (178)\n**[[Raions of cities in Ukraine|City districts]] (\u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0438 \u0443 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0445) (118)\n*Primary level (Local communities, 11,515):\n**Cities of raion significance (276)\n**Urban-type settlements (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0430 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0438\u043f\u0443) (885)\n**Villages (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0430) (27,190)\n**Rural-type settlements (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0430) (1,266)\nTotal cities: 454, an increase of 20 compared with the 1989 census.<ref name=cen2001/>\n\n==History==\n{{Main|Administrative divisions development in Ukraine|Ukrainian historical regions}}\n\nBefore the introduction of oblasts in 1932, Ukraine comprised 40 [[Okruhas of Ukriane|okruha]]s, which had replaced the former [[Russian Empire|Russian Imperial]] [[guberniya]] (governorate) subdivisions.\n\nIn 1932 the territory of the Ukrainian SSR was re-established based on oblasts. Excluded in the administrative changes was [[Western Ukraine]], which at that time formed part of the [[Second Polish Republic]] and shared in the Polish form of administrative division based on [[Voivodeships of Poland|voivodeships]].\n\nIn the post-[[World War II]] period, the [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic]] consisted of [[Administrative divisions of the Ukrainian SSR|25 oblasts and two cities with special status]].\n\nAfter the fall of the Soviet Union in 1991, Crimea obtained the status of an autonomous republic with its own government instead of a regional state administration.\n\n==Regions==\n{{Ukraine Labelled Map|float=right}}\n\n===Autonomous republic===\n{{Main|Autonomous Republic of Crimea}}\n\nThe Autonomous Republic of Crimea, formerly the Crimean Oblast of the Ukrainian SSR, geographically encompasses the major portion of the Crimean peninsula in southern [[Ukraine]]. Its capital is [[Simferopol]]. The Autonomous Republic of Crimea is the only region within Ukraine that possesses its own constitution.\n\nOn March 16, 2014, after the occupation of Crimea by the Russian military, a referendum on joining the Russian Federation was conducted. A majority of votes supported the measure. On March 21, 2014, the Russian Duma voted to annex Crimea as a [[Republic of Crimea|subject]] into the Russian Federation. The Ukrainian government does not recognize the referendum or annexation of Crimea as legitimate. On March 27, the UN General Assembly passed [[United Nations General Assembly Resolution 68/262|Resolution 68/262]] by 100 to 11 votes, recognizing the referendum as invalid and denying any legal change in the status of Crimea and Sevastopol.\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n! Autonomous Republic of Crimea\n! [[Representatives of the President of Ukraine]]\n! Area (km<sup>2</sup>)\n! Population (2010)\n! Pop. density\n! Administrative centre\n! Raions/Districts\n! Cities of regional significance {{#tag:ref|\"[[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|cities of regional significance]]\" is a translation of {{lang-uk|\u041c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f}}.|group=\"nb\"}}\n|-\n|{{flag|Crimea}}\n|Nataliya Popovych\n|26,100\n|1,966,801\n|75\n|[[Simferopol]]<ref>temporarily in [[Kherson]]</ref>\n|14\n|11\n|-\n|}\n\n===Oblasts===\n{{Main|Oblasts of Ukraine}}\n\nOblasts are on the first (top) level of the administrative division of Ukraine.\n \nAlmost every oblast is named after its administrative center, except for four oblasts. Volyn' and Zakarpattia, whose respective capitals are Lutsk and Uzhhorod, are named after historic regions [[Volhynia]] and [[Carpathian Ruthenia|Transcarpathia]]. The administrative centers of the Dnipropetrovsk Oblast and the Kirovohrad Oblast were renamed to Dnipro and Kropyvnytskyi in 2016, however as of 2017 the oblasts still officially bear the old soviet names as their change must be reflected in an amendment to the Ukrainian Constitution. \n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n! Region\n! Area (km<sup>2</sup>)\n! Population (2010)\n! Pop. density\n! Administrative center\n! Raions/Districts\n! Cities of regional significance {{#tag:ref|\"[[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|cities of regional significance]]\" is a translation of {{lang-uk|\u041c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f}}.|group=\"nb\"}}\n|-\n|{{flag|Cherkasy Oblast}}\n|20,891\n|1,291,135\n|61.80\n|[[Cherkasy]]\n|20\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Chernihiv Oblast}}\n|31,851.3\n|1,104,241\n|34.67\n|[[Chernihiv]]\n|22\n|3\n|-\n|{{flag|Chernivtsi Oblast}}\n|8,093.6\n|903,782\n|111.67\n|[[Chernivtsi]]\n|11\n|2\n|-\n|{{flag|Dnipropetrovsk Oblast}}\n|31,900.5\n|3,344,073\n|104.83\n|[[Dnipro]]\n|22\n|13\n|-\n|{{flag|Donetsk Oblast}}\n|26,505.7\n|4,448,031\n|167.81\n|[[Donetsk]]\n|18\n|28\n|-\n|{{flag|Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast}}\n|13,894.0\n|1,380,770\n|99.38\n|[[Ivano-Frankivsk]]\n|14\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Kharkiv Oblast}}\n|31,401.6\n|2,755,177\n|87.74\n|[[Kharkiv]]\n|27\n|7\n|-\n|{{flag|Kherson Oblast}}\n|28,449\n|1,091,151\n|38.35\n|[[Kherson]]\n|18\n|3\n|-\n|{{flag|Khmelnytskyi Oblast}}\n|20,636.2\n|1,331,534\n|64.52\n|[[Khmelnytskyi, Ukraine|Khmelnytskyi]]\n|20\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Kyiv Oblast}}\n|28,118.9\n|1,719,602\n|61.15\n|[[Kiev|Kyiv]]\n|25\n|13\n|-\n|{{flag|Kirovohrad Oblast}}\n|24,577.5\n|1,014,809\n|41.29\n|[[Kropyvnytskyi]]\n|21\n|4\n|-\n|{{flag|Luhansk Oblast}}\n|26,672.5\n|2,300,412\n|86.25\n|[[Luhansk]]\n|18\n|14\n|-\n|{{flag|Lviv Oblast}}\n|21,823.7\n|2,545,634\n|116.65\n|[[Lviv]]\n|20\n|9\n|-\n|{{flag|Mykolaiv Oblast}}\n|24,587.4\n|1,186,452\n|48.25\n|[[Mykolaiv]]\n|19\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Odessa Oblast|Odesa Oblast}}\n|33,295.9\n|2,387,636\n|71.71\n|[[Odessa]]\n|26\n|7\n|-\n|{{flag|Poltava Oblast}}\n|28,735.8\n|1,493,668\n|51.98\n|[[Poltava]]\n|25\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Rivne Oblast}}\n|20,038.5\n|1,152,576\n|57.52\n|[[Rivne]]\n|16\n|4\n|-\n|{{flag|Sumy Oblast}}\n|23,823.9\n|1,166,765\n|48.97\n|[[Sumy]]\n|18\n|7\n|-\n|{{flag|Ternopil Oblast}}\n|13,817.1\n|1,086,694\n|78.65\n|[[Ternopil]]\n|17\n|1\n|-\n|{{flag|Vinnytsia Oblast}}\n|26,501.6\n|1,646,250\n|62.12\n|[[Vinnytsia]]\n|27\n|6\n|-\n|{{flag|Volyn Oblast}} \n|20,135.3\n|1,038,223\n|51.56\n|[[Lutsk]]\n|16\n|4\n|-\n|{{flag|Zakarpattia Oblast}} \n|12,771.5\n|1,246,323\n|97.59\n|[[Uzhhorod]]\n|13\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Zaporizhia Oblast}}\n|27,168.5\n|1,805,431\n|66.45\n|[[Zaporizhia]]\n|20\n|5\n|-\n|{{flag|Zhytomyr Oblast}}\n|29,819.2\n|1,283,201\n|43.03\n|[[Zhytomyr]]\n|23\n|5\n|}\n\n===Cities with special status===\n{{Main|Cities with special status}}\n\nTwo cities carry special status: the city of [[Kyiv]] which is the capital of Ukraine and the city of [[Sevastopol]]. Following the [[2014 Crimean crisis]], Sevastopol is controlled by Russia and is incorporated as a [[Federal subjects of Russia|federal subject of Russia]]. It is recognized as a part of Ukraine by most of the international community.\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n!City\n! [[Chief of Local State Administration (Ukraine)|Governor]]{{#tag:ref|Chairman of the Regional (or City) State Administration.|group=\"nb\"}}\n! Area\n! Population (2010)\n|-\n|{{flag|Kyiv}}\n|[[Vitali Klitschko]]{{#tag:ref|[[Vitaliy Klychko]] serves both as a mayor and a governor for the city of Kiev since 25 June 2014 (see [[Mayor of Kyiv]]).|group=\"nb\"}}\n|{{convert|323.9|sqmi|km2|order=flip|abbr=on}}\n|2,782,016\n|-\n|{{flag|Sevastopol}}\n|''[[Governor of Sevastopol (Ukraine)|vacant]]''\n|{{convert|416.6|sqmi|km2|order=flip|abbr=on}}\n|380,301\n|-\n|}\n\n==Second-level subdivision units==\n\n===Cities of regional significance (regional cities)===\n{{Main|City of regional significance (Ukraine)}}\n\n===Raions===\n{{Main|Raions of Ukraine}}\n[[Raions of Ukraine|Raions]] are smaller territorial units of subdivision in Ukraine. There are 490 raions.\n\n===Urban districts===\n{{Main|Urban districts of Ukraine}}\n\n==Councils==\n{{details|Populated places in Ukraine}}\n[[File:Dniepr river in Kyiv.jpg|thumb|The [[Dnieper River]] plays an important part in Ukrainian territorial division, with many large cities settled on its banks. Here, the capital city of [[Kiev]] which was founded on the Dnieper's right bank but for now expanded over the river significantly.]]\n\n{| border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=2 style=\"text-align:left; border:1px solid #ddd; font-size:90%;\" summary=\"\"\n|- style=\"background:#ddd; vertical-align:top;\"\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=2 | Status<ref>{{cite web|title=Regions of Ukraine and their composition |url=http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |work=[[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]] |accessdate=25 December 2011 |language=Ukrainian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |archivedate=26 December 2011 }}</ref>\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | Status (in [[Ukrainian Language|Ukrainian]])\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{nowrap|Total Number (in 2006)}}\n|- style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"\n|colspan=2|'''[[city|misto / city]]''' || \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e || style=\"text-align:right;\" | '''457'''\n|-\n|&nbsp; || municipality|| \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0437\u0456 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u0446\u0456\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u043c \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 2\n|-\n|&nbsp; || misto \u043eblastnoho znachennia || \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 176\n|-\n|&nbsp; || misto raionnoho znachennia || \u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044f || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 279\n|- style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"\n|colspan=2|'''[[urban-type settlement|selyshche miskoho typu / town]]''' || \u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0438\u043f\u0443 || style=\"text-align:right;\" | '''886'''\n|- style=\"background:#f0f0f0;\"\n|colspan=2|'''[[village|selo / village]]''' || \u0441\u0456\u043b\u044c\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442 || style=\"text-align:right;\" | '''28,552'''\n|-\n|&nbsp; || selysche || \u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 1,364\n|-\n|&nbsp; || selo || \u0441\u0435\u043b\u043e || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 27,188\n|}\n\nUkraine has two types of settlements: rural and urban. Rural populated areas (\u0441\u0456\u043b\u044c\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442) can be either a village (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u043e, [[Village#Slavic countries|selo]]) or a rural settlement (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435). Urban populated areas (\u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442) can be either a city (\u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442o) or an [[urban-type settlement]] (\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0449\u0435 \u043c\u0456\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0442\u0438\u043f\u0443). For the sake of brevity, urbanized settlements are sometimes classified as towns in the [[English language]].\n\nChanges to a settlement's status can be made only by the [[Verkhovna Rada]]. Please note that the size of a settlement does not ultimately define its status, although is a major factor. For example, the city of [[Prypiat (city)|Prypiat]] still retains its status, while having a population of zero, due to its infrastructure, including buildings, roads, and utility networks.\n\nThe typical Ukrainian ''misto'' ought to be considered a [[city]], not a [[town]] (compare to [[City status in the United Kingdom]]). However, the city's subordination to either an oblast or raion also should be taken into account, especially in the [[political]] sense. Some of urbanized settlements may be cities of raion subordination, although it could seem confusing, a type of settlement should be considered first as its status is given for administrative purposes.\n\n===Cities===\n{{see also|List of cities in Ukraine}}\n[[File:Kyiv province location map.svg|thumb|left|[[Kiev Oblast]] for instance, has several regional city municipalities such as [[Pereiaslav]], for example, that are under direct subordination to the regional authorities. They are officially known as cities of regional significance.]]\n[[File:Drohobycz ulica stryjska 2008.jpg|thumb|[[Drohobych]], is a city of oblast subordinance, subordinate to the [[Lviv Oblast]] authorities rather than to the local [[Drohobych Raion]] administration.]]\nAccording to Ukrainian law a city (\u043c\u0456\u0441\u0442\u043e) in Ukraine is a locality of at least 10,000 people.<ref name=UCSMBS>[https://books.google.com/books?id=QcoodEOmnMUC&pg=PA151&dq=Ukraine+city+10,000+people&hl=nl&sa=X&ei=v1fvU5b8LcSIOMPDgfgO&ved=0CCcQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Ukraine%20city%2010%2C000%20people&f=false A Geography of Russia and Its Neighbors] by Mikhail S. Blinnikov, [[Guilford Press]], 2010, {{ISBN|1606239201}} (page 151)</ref> Cities may carry various status. Some may be of national importance, others of [[city of regional significance (Ukraine)|regional (oblast) importance]], and the rest of district (raion) importance. For example, the cities of ''Kiev'' and of ''Sevastopol'' have special status of national significance and each is officially classified as a ''city with a special status'', which administratively is equivalent to an oblast. Mayors of those cities, in general, as are governors of oblasts, are appointed by the [[President of Ukraine]]. However, the status of the mayor of Kiev is somewhat more complex, and for further information see [[Legal status and local government of Kiev]]. The status of Sevastopol is also unique.\n\nAlmost every oblast has at least one city of regional subordination (importance), which is the administrative center (capital) of that oblast. However, some other big cities within the oblast may have such status as well. The cities of oblast subordination have the same importance of a raion, and often are the administrative centers of such. In addition to regular raions, several Ukrainian cities with national or oblast status are further divided into ''city raions'' which may include other cities, towns, and/or villages. In 2010, Ukraine had 23 such cities with their own city raions.\n\nMany '''raions''' also have city municipalities of its level of subordination (importance). Those are usually the administrative centers (capitals). Notice that not all raions have a city as their administrative center; however all the raion centers are at least urban-like (urbanized). All administrative centers have their own form of self-administration. The municipalities of a raion subordination may administer several adjacent local councils (municipalities), usually rural. If a raion has several cities of raion (district) level, they may share administrative power for the raion.\n\n===Other municipalities===\nIn addition to city municipalities, Ukraine has urban-like municipalities. The lowest form of self-administration are the rural municipalities and villages. A rural municipality may consist of a single village, usually big, or a combination of other rural villages or localities. Note that some villages also have some additional, very small settlements. Those settlements, together with the home village, combine a local (rural) municipality (silrada). For simplicity's sake, a silrada (rural municipality) is usually referred to as a village and is the lowest level of administrative division. The status of any settlement is granted by the [[Verkhovna Rada]].\n\n===Amalgamated hromadas (AHs)===\nIn his draft [[Ukraine's constitution|constitutional]] amendments of June 2014 [[Ukrainian President]] [[Petro Poroshenko]] proposed changing the administrative divisions of Ukraine, which should include regions, districts and \"hromadas\".<ref>[http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/211043.html Poroshenko suggests granting status of regions to Crimea, Kyiv, Sevastopol, creating new political subdivision of 'community'] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701043549/http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/211043.html |date=2014-07-01 }}, [[Interfax-Ukraine]] (26 June 2014)</ref>\n\nOn February 5, 2015, the law \"On voluntary association of territorial communities\" was adopted creating ''Amalgamated hromadas (communities)'' meaning [[Settlement council (Ukraine)|settlement councils]], [[Rural council (Ukraine)|rural councils]] and a [[City of district significance (Ukraine)|city of district significance]] can create a new administrative unit.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://reformsguide.org.ua/reforms/decentralizationreform/|title=Decentralization|date=2017-02-10|website=The Reforms Guide|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-28}}</ref> Any amalgamated hromada with a city as an administrative centre is an urban hromada, any amalgamated hromada with an urban-type settlement as an administrative centre is a settlement hromada, and any amalgamated hromada with a village as an administrative centre is a rural hromada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://decentralization.gov.ua/en/glossary|title=Glossary|date=|website=Decentralization Reform|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref> New local [[elections in Ukraine|elections]] in these united territorial communities were then held.<ref>[http://en.interfax.com.ua/news/general/472770.html Batkivschyna party says it gets most votes at local elections], [[Interfax Ukraine]] (25 December 2017)<br>[https://www.unian.info/politics/2316594-police-investigate-voter-bribing-cases-as-local-elections-held-in-51-territorial-communities.html Police investigate voter bribing cases as local elections held in 51 territorial communities], [[UNIAN]] (25 December 2017)</ref> 226 will be holding elections in 2018 and 2019.<ref>[http://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/ukrainealert/elections-are-around-the-corner-and-ukraine-s-political-parties-are-not-ready-2 Elections Are Around the Corner, and Ukraine\u2019s Political Parties Are Not Ready], [[Atlantic Council]] (6 December 2017)</ref> The first 252 were held in 2017.<ref>[https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45055-interim-report-on-observation-results-of-the-first-local-elections-in-united-territorial-communities-on-29-october-2017-19102017-26102017 INTERIM REPORT ON OBSERVATION RESULTS OF THE FIRST LOCAL ELECTIONS IN UNITED TERRITORIAL COMMUNITIES ON 29 October 2017 (19.10.2017 26.10.2017)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228223135/https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45055-interim-report-on-observation-results-of-the-first-local-elections-in-united-territorial-communities-on-29-october-2017-19102017-26102017 |date=28 December 2018 }}, [[PORA#OPORA|OPORA]] (31 October 2017)<br>[https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45165-ukraine-holds-elections-in-51-utcs-today Ukraine holds elections in 51 UTCs today] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171226020921/https://www.oporaua.org/en/elections/45165-ukraine-holds-elections-in-51-utcs-today |date=2017-12-26 }}, [[PORA#OPORA|OPORA]] (24 December 2017)</ref> \n\nThe Law \"On Local Self-Government in Ukraine\" stipulates that local budgets should have enough money to be administered by local self-government bodies.<ref name=\"Espresogr\"/> Because many of the small rural councils and cities of district significance could never hope to do this the new administrative unit ''Amalgamated hromada'' ([https://uk.wikipedia.org/wiki/%D0%9E%D0%B1%27%D1%94%D0%B4%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%BD%D0%B0_%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%80%D1%96%D0%B0%D0%BB%D1%8C%D0%BD%D0%B0_%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B0%D0%B4%D0%B0]{{lang-uk|\u041e\u0431'\u0454\u0434\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0456\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430 \u0433\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0434\u0430}}, ''Obyednana terytorial\u02b9na hromada'') was created.<ref name=\"Espresogr\">{{in lang|uk}} [https://espreso.tv/article/2017/10/30/vybory_v_obyednanykh_terytorialnykh_gromadakh_scho_ce_i_dlya_chogo_potribne Elections in the united territorial communities. What is this and what you need], [[Espreso TV]] (31 October 2017)</ref>\n\n==Other administrations==\n\nUkraine also has several settlements known as ''viiskove mistechko'' which were former military installations. Since the fall of the Soviet Union, the secrecy of such settlements has been unveiled, however, the towns are subordinated directly to the Ministry of Defense and do not have their own civil administrations. Such military installations are like ghost towns that are not even identified on a map. One of them, on the border of the [[Kiev Oblast|Kiev]] and [[Zhytomyr Oblast]]s is Makarov-1.<ref>{{cite news|title=In Kiev region a military installation cannot vote|url=http://podrobnosti.ua/video/podrobnosti/2010/10/31/727577.html|accessdate=8 February 2012|newspaper=[[Podrobnosti.ua]]|language=Russian|date=31 October 2012|format=Video|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120404114906/http://podrobnosti.ua/video/podrobnosti/2010/10/31/727577.html|archive-date=2012-04-04|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nA special territory known as the ''[[zone of alienation]]'' falls under the jurisdiction of the Ministry of Emergencies and was the most severely affected territory by the [[Chernobyl disaster]]. Additionally, various restricted nature preserves known as ''[[Zapovednik]]'' fall under the jurisdiction of the Ministry of Ecology. \n\nDue to the [[War in Donbass]], the status of [[Civil\u2013military administrations (Ukraine)|civil\u2013military administrations]] was created in territories of [[Donetsk Oblast|Donetsk]] and [[Luhansk Oblast|Luhansk]] oblasts where the respective local government units cannot exercise their constitutionally guaranteed powers.<ref name=pravda>{{cite news|title=Poroshenko gave the green light to create civil-military administrations|url=http://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2015/02/26/7059870/|accessdate=26 February 2015|work=[[Ukrayinska Pravda]]|date=26 February 2015|location=Ukrainian}}</ref>\n\n[[File:1201044 original (1).jpg|thumb|A mix of modern and old buildings in [[Dnipro]], located in [[Dnipropetrovsk Oblast]]. Dnipro's metropolitan area includes cities such as [[Kamianske]] and [[Novomoskovsk, Ukraine|Novomoskovsk]].]]\n\nCurrently, Ukraine has the following 3 enclaves:\n*The city of [[Slavutych]] which is administratively subordinated directly to [[Kiev Oblast]] while being completely surrounded by neighboring [[Chernihiv Oblast]].\n*The settlement of Bile which is located on [[Snake Island (Black Sea)|Snake Island]] and is fully surrounded by the [[Black Sea]] was established in 2007 and is part of [[Vylkove]], [[Odessa Oblast]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Selysche Bile, Odessa Oblast, Kiliya Raion, city Vylkove|url=http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/A005?rdat1=08.02.2012&rf7571=42441|work=Regions of Ukraine and their Structure|publisher=[[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]]|accessdate=8 February 2012|language=Ukrainian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303033059/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/A005?rdat1=08.02.2012&rf7571=42441|archive-date=2014-03-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*The town of [[Kotsiubynske]] which is part of the Kiev Oblast and is completely surrounded by the city of Kiev.\n\n===Metropolitan areas===\nUkraine has five major agglomerated metropolitan areas ([[conurbation]]s). These conurbation areas are not officially recognized and remain to be administered according to official [[oblast]]-[[raion]] system of subdivision.\n*[[Kiev metropolitan area|Kiev]] includes towns such as [[Irpin]], [[Boryspil]], and [[Fastiv]]\n*Kharkiv includes towns such as [[Chuhuiv]], [[Merefa]], and numerous other settlements\n*Donetsk includes towns such as [[Makiivka]], [[Khartsyzk]], and others\n*Dnipro with [[Kamianske]] and [[Novomoskovsk, Ukraine|Novomoskovsk]]\n*Odessa with [[Chornomorsk]] and [[Ovidiopol]]\n\n==Other divisions==\n{{Unreferenced section|date=May 2016}} \n[[File:Ukraine KIIS-Regional-division2.png|thumb|Kiev International Institute of Sociology (KIIS) geographic division of Ukraine used in their polls.]]\nBeside the administrative divisions, geographical divisions are at times used for reference or statistical purposes. The division splits Ukraine into 4 to 6 geographic areas: [[Western Ukraine]], [[Eastern Ukraine]], [[Southern Ukraine]], [[Central Ukraine]], [[Northern Ukraine]] (occasionally used).\n\nThe neighboring countries such as Russia, Poland, Hungary and Romania sometimes identify certain parts of Ukraine. For example, Russia has territorial claims to Ukraine stating that the Southeastern Ukraine is part of Russia,{{fact|date=March 2017}} certain political or public figures in Poland lay territorial claims to [[western Ukraine]] identifying them as ''Borderlands'' or ''Kreis'' (Kresy),{{fact|date=March 2017}} the same goes for Hungary that calls [[Zakarpattia Oblast]] as K\u00e1rp\u00e1talja.{{fact|date=March 2017}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Ukraine}}\n* [[Geography of Ukraine]]\n* [[ISO 3166-2:UA]]\n* [[List_of_places_named_after_people#Ukraine|List of places named after people (Ukraine)]]\n* [[Local government in Ukraine]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|Atlas of Ukraine}}\n*{{cite web|title=Regions of Ukraine and their composition |url=http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |work=[[Verkhovna Rada|Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine]] |accessdate=25 December 2011 |language=Ukrainian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111226134808/http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/z7502/a002 |archivedate=26 December 2011 }}\n*{{cite web|title=Ukraine Raions|url=http://www.statoids.com/yua.html|work=Statoids|accessdate=8 February 2012}}\n*{{cite web|title=Ukrainian cities and regions in alphabetical order|url=http://ukrainetrek.com/regions-by-alphabet|work=UkraineTrek|accessdate=10 February 2012}}\n* {{cite web|title=Administrative territorial composition of Ukraine|url=http://www.minregion.gov.ua/attachments/content-attachments/1659/ATU.pdf|work=Ministry of Regional Development, Construction, and Communal Living|accessdate=5 April 2015}}{{Dead link|date=October 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Ukraine topics}}\n{{Administrative divisions of Ukraine}}\n{{Administrative divisions of Ukraine's regions}}\n{{Articles on first-level administrative divisions of European countries}}\n\n[[Category:Subdivisions of Ukraine| ]]\n[[Category:Country subdivisions in Europe|Ukraine]]\n", "name_user": "XTOC6", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updated spelling (per official UA government site: rada.gov.ua/en)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Administrative_divisions_of_Ukraine"}
{"title_page": "Iori Yagami", "text_new": "{{short description|Fictional character}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox character\n|image=IoriYagamiXIII.png\n|name= Iori Yagami\n|caption=Iori Yagami in ''[[The King of Fighters XIII]]'' illustrated by Ogura\n|firstgame=''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' (1995)\n|series=[[The King of Fighters]]\n|designer=\n|voice=[[Kunihiko Yasui]]<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters '95 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 25, 1995 |platform=Neo Geo |level=Credits}}</ref> (''KOF '95'' - ''KOF XIII'')<br/>[[Takanori Hoshino]] (''KOF XIV'' onwards)<br/>Chisa Horii (female; ''SNKH: TTF'')<ref name=chisa>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=MTEP7NIwD3w|title=SNK\u30d2\u30ed\u30a4\u30f3\u30ba - DLC\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\u300c\u30df\u30b9X\u300d|via=YouTube|date=October 25, 2018|accessdate=October 25, 2018}}</ref><br/>Sho Sudo (Japanese dub of the King of Fighters movie)\n|portrayer  = [[Will Yun Lee]] (2010 film)\n|origin = Japan<br />United States <small>(2010 film)</small> \n|nationality = Japanese<br />[[Japanese Americans|Japanese-American]] <small>(2010 film)</small> \n|fighting_style=Yagami style of ancient martial arts + Pure instinct\n}} \n{{nihongo|'''Iori Yagami'''|\u516b\u795e \u5eb5|Yagami Iori|lead=yes}} is a character from [[SNK]]'s ''[[The King of Fighters]]'' [[video game]] series. The character first appeared in ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' as the leader of the Rivals Team, as the initial enemy and later rival of [[Kyo Kusanagi]]. Iori is the heir of the Yagami clan, who use [[pyrokinesis|pyrokinetic]] powers and sealed the [[Orochi (King of Fighters)|Orochi]] devil along with the Kusanagi and Yata clans. Iori suffers from a curse&nbsp;\u2013&#32;{{nihongo|\"The Riot of the Blood\"|\u8840\u306e\u66b4\u8d70|Chi no B\u014dso}}&nbsp;\u2013&#32;under which he becomes faster, stronger and wilder, exhibiting a deadly tendency to indiscriminately attack everyone in close proximity. In this state, Iori is commonly called \"Wild Iori\" or {{nihongo|\"Orochi Iori\"|\u6708\u306e\u591c\u5927\u86c7\u306e\u8840\u306b\u72c2\u3046\u5eb5|Tsuki no Yoru Orochi no Chi ni Kuruu Iori|lit. Insane Iori with Blood of Orochi Under the Night of the Moon}}.<ref name=curse/> Aside from the main series, Iori appears in several other media series, including [[Spin-off (media)|spin-offs]], crossover video games, and comic adaptations of the series.\n\nIori was created as Kyo's rival; his name and abilities were designed to relate him with the legend of ''[[Yamata no Orochi]]''. The designers ended up liking him so much they are careful of the character's [[Characterisation|development]] as the series expands. \nAs a result, Iori sometimes helps Kyo to have the opportunity to fight him. Finding his design appealing, new outfits presented the SNK staff with difficulties as they devised new appearances for the character that would retain his popularity.\n\nVideo game journalists have praised Iori Yagami as one of the most powerful characters in the series. Reviewers have also cited Iori as one of the best characters from the games, labeling him as a veteran character and praising his appearance as one of SNK's best creations. \"Miss X\", Iori's crossdressing form from ''[[SNK Gals' Fighters]]'' and the additional female one of ''[[SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy]]'', also received attention for its humor. A series of collectible items based on Iori's likeness, including key chains and figurines, have been manufactured.\n\n==Conception and creation==\n===Origins===\nIori's name is losely based on the Japanese mythological creature [[Yamata no Orochi]].<ref>{{cite book|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba\u201997\u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30b3\u30ec\u30af\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3 (\u30b2\u30fc\u30e1\u30b9\u30c8\u30e0\u30c3\u30af Vol. 93) \u30e0\u30c3\u30af \u2013 |year=1997|isbn=978-4881993811|publisher=Shinshosha|page=18}}</ref> In contrast to Kyo's life, SNK decided to keep Iori's life as private despite some related material mentioning the fact that Iori has relatives.<ref>{{cite cd|title=Snk Characters Sounds Collection Vol.11 \u516b\u795e\u5eb5|id=PCCB-00378|publisher=Scitron, Pony Canyon|year=1999}}</ref>  One of the planned objectives for ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' was to properly introduce Iori as Kyo Kusanagi's rival. According to his creators, Iori's personality and other aspects of his character such as his phrases and unique moves \"broke the mold for characters in fighting games at that time\".<ref name=kofaniviori/>  Like Kyo, several aspects of Iori, including his surname and abilities, were designed to relate him to the Japanese legend Yamata no Orochi, which was the inspiration for the plot.<ref name=kofaniviori>{{cite web | url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=iori | title=Iori Yagami Official Profile | quote=When you think of Iori Yagami, his intense personality most likely comes to mind. His moves are unique, and his dives choice of hairstyle, wardrobe, and manner of speaking was certainly a personality that broke the mold of former characters in fighting games at that time. During the initial location tests to determine the popularity of the game, Iori was the character who stood out most. His hair and his lines to provoke his opponents (\"You think I'm scary, do you?\") excited his fans to no end. | website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=March 24, 2008 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080410074739/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=iori | archive-date=April 10, 2008 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> After watching fan reactions at initial location testing for ''King of Fighters '95'', several staff members predicted Iori would be popular.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=8| title=Remembrances of KOF: An Interview with C.A.C Yamazaki | website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=March 24, 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080418040428/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=8|archivedate=April 18, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=11 |title=Remembrances of KOF: An Interview with Mr. Marito |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=March 24, 2008 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fvxXUUWS?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=8 |archivedate=April 10, 2009 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> One staff member was happy that at an event for ''[[The King of Fighters XIII]]'' on March 25, 2010, several fans reminded him that day is Iori's birthday according to his official profile.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://news.dengeki.com/elem/000/000/279/279862/| title=\u65e9\u304f\u904a\u3093\u3067\u307b\u3057\u3044\uff01 \u300eKOF XIII\u300f\u958b\u767a\u30b9\u30bf\u30c3\u30d52\u4eba\u304c\u7a3c\u50cd\u76f4\u524d\u306e\u6c17\u6301\u3061\u3092\u544a\u767d\uff01| publisher=ASCII Media Works| date=July 13, 2011| accessdate=August 1, 2011| language=Japanese| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110812040226/http://news.dengeki.com/elem/000/000/279/279862/| archive-date=August 12, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> The pixel art of Iori was made by Yuichiro Hiraki who, despite leaving SNK to work in another project a few years later, was asked by [[Capcom]]'s Kaname Fujioka to once again work on the character's design for the crossover fighting game ''[[Capcom vs. SNK: Millennium Fight 2000]]''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Devil May Cry: 3142 Graphic Arts|publisher=Capcom, Udon Entertainment|year=2015|isbn=978-1927925485|pages=198}}</ref>\n\nIori was originally introduced in ''The King of Fighters '95'' as the leader of a team composed of [[Billy Kane]], [[Eiji Kisaragi]] and himself. Each member shares a rivalry with another character in the game. Although the staff members worked hard to impress their superiors at SNK, Iori's characterization caused them to discard the team in the next game in the series. In the rival team's ending, Iori betrays Billy and Eiji, generating anger from the ''[[Art of Fighting]]'' developers for what Iori did to their character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kofaniv.snk-corp.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=billy |title=Billy Kane|publisher=SNK|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kofaniv.snk-corp.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=eiji|title=Eiji Kisaragi|publisher=SNK|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref>  Iori is a [[berserker]] due to the Orochi demon blood within him. This version of the character, officially named \"Orochi Iori\", is hinted to have existed before his debut in ''[[The King of Fighters '97]]'' as one of the game's [[mid-boss]]es. This form of Iori was designed to easily overpower other characters.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=orochi-iori| title=Orochi Iori Official Profile| website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website| accessdate=March 24, 2008| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207201041/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=orochi-iori| archive-date=February 7, 2009| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> Series' flagship director Toyohisa Tanabe states that the staff were initially reluctant to add this version of Iori to the series' roster; they were worried about fans' reactions but did so to add more impact to the Orochi saga's climax. Tanabe was particularly pleased to see surprised reactions from female fans to this form during ''KOF '97''{{'}}s location testing. Another minor development of the character was his change of \"most valued possession/valued treasure\" information. A girlfriend was also listed in ''The King of Fighters '95'', ''The King of Fighters '99'', and ''The King of Fighters 2000''. Starting with ''The King of Fighters 2001'' and every entry after that, however, the space is listed as \"None\". The SNK staff commented that it is curious that he does not have a girlfriend anymore.<ref>{{Cite book | year=2005 | editor=Akihiko Ureshino | title=The King of Fighters Perfect Reader | pages=144 | language=Japanese | publisher=Nikkei Business Publications, Inc. | isbn= 4-8222-1711-6}}</ref>\n\n===Development===\n[[File:IoriYagamiXIV.png|thumb|Iori's redesign for ''The King of Fighters XIV'' by Ogura.]]\nDuring the early development stages of ''[[The King of Fighters '99]]'', SNK planned to exclude Iori and Kyo from the game because the company wanted to focus the story on the new protagonist, [[K']]. They reversed this decision because of the characters' popularity.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=kyo-1| title=Kyo Kusanagi-1 Official Profile| website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website| accessdate=March 24, 2008| archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6c0SZaTay?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=kyo-1| archive-date=October 3, 2015| url-status=dead| df=mdy-all}}</ref> The repeated appearance of Iori, Kyo, and other SNK regular characters in the series is at the insistence of the marketers and main planners, making it a challenge to decide the story for each title.<ref>{{Cite book | year=2005 | editor=Akihiko Ureshino | title=The King of Fighters Perfect Reader | pages=136~139 | language=Japanese | publisher=Nikkei Business Publications, Inc. |isbn= 4-8222-1711-6}}</ref> Because of his popularity among fans, some of the series' main designers have said Iori is \"difficult to draw for\". Illustrator Shinkiro said he thought Iori was one of the series' wildest characters because of his hairstyle; similar sentiments were expressed by ''[[Last Blade]]'' illustrator Tonko.<ref name=kofanivmanhua/> ''[[KOF: Maximum Impact]]'' producer [[Falcoon]] stated that attempting to change an \"untouchable\" design such as Iori's put him under severe pressure. He stated that creating Iori's alternative design that appears in the ''Maximum Impact'' series almost felt \"unforgivable\" because he felt unsure of fans' reaction to the change.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.snkplaymore.jp/blog/falcoon/archives/2006/02/post_7.html| title=\u30a2\u30ca\u30b6\u30fc\u30b3\u30b9\u30c1\u30e5\u30fc\u30e0\u306e\u3053\u3068\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\uff08\u4e00\u56de\u76ee\uff09| publisher=Falcoon official blog| accessdate=January 21, 2009| url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060501213857/http://www.snkplaymore.jp/blog/falcoon/archives/2006/02/post_7.html | archivedate=May 1, 2006| df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nFor the ''Maximum Impact'' spin-off games, Iori's characteristic hairstyle was changed dramatically. Throughout the series, his normal costume consists of a short jacket and [[bondage pants]]; without changing his design and adjusting only his coloring, a diverse number of image variations can be brought about.<ref>{{Cite book | date=June 17, 2006  |page=50|  title=The King of Fighters Maximum Impact Artbook| language=Japanese | publisher=SNK Playmore | isbn=978-4-7973-3543-9 }}</ref> During the making of ''The King of Fighters XIV'', Nobuyuki Kuroki wanted Iori, except the character's hair, to be redesigned. Character designer Eisuke Ogura created a new outfit for Iori and asked the modeler to focus on his masculinity and to pay close attention to the way the design of the character's eyes.<ref>{{Cite book | year= 2016 | title=The King of Fighters XIV artbook| page=45| language= | publisher=Atlus|isbn=}}</ref> This new design, alongside Kyo's, provoked controversy when it was revealed. ''KOF XIV'' director Yasuyuki Oda said the team wanted the characters to have new looks because the game is set in another story arc.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://xw.qq.com/games/20151017000037| script-title=zh:\u5c0f\u7530\u6cf0\u4e4b\uff1a\u5bf9\u62f3\u76879OL\u6ee1\u610f| publisher=QQ| accessdate=February 4, 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205001207/https://xw.qq.com/games/20151017000037| archive-date=February 5, 2018| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> \n\nIn an interview with Iori's [[Seiy\u016b|Japanese voice actor]], [[Kunihiko Yasui]] comments that he feels responsible as a voice actor for his performances as Iori, taking care to sound different in each installment as a means of developing and protecting his character's humanity.<ref>{{Cite book | date=September 20, 2005 | editor=Akihiko Ureshino | title=The King of Fighters Perfect Reader | pages=160 | language=Japanese | publisher=Nikkei Business Publications, Inc. | isbn=4-8222-1711-6}}</ref> Yasui was replaced by [[Takanori Hoshino]] starting in ''The King of Fighters XIV''; Hoshino said he was delighted to be the new voice actor of the character, thanking SNK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/shockhearts777/status/764027299977056256|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=September 22, 2018|date=August 12, 2016|title=\u516b\u795e\u5eb5\u306e\u58f0\u3092\u62c5\u5f53\u3055\u305b\u3066\u3044\u305f\u3060\u3051\u308b\u4e8b\u306b\u306a\u308a\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01\u69d8\u3005\u306a\u60f3\u3044\u306f\u3042\u308b\u304b\u3068\u601d\u3044\u307e\u3059\u304c\u3001\u8aa0\u5fc3\u8aa0\u610f\u5411\u304d\u5408\u3044\u305f\u3044\u3068\u601d\u3044\u307e\u3059\uff01\u5b9c\u3057\u304f\u304a\u9858\u3044\u81f4\u3057\u307e\u3059\uff01|language=Japanese}}</ref> Chisa Horii voices Iori's female incarnation in ''SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy''.<ref name=chisa/>\n\n===Fighting style===\nWhen fighting, Iori employs the \"Yagami style of ancient martial arts\" as well as an art labelled as \"Pure instinct\" which involves the usage of blue flames. His strongest technique is known as {{nihongo|Kin 1211 Shiki: Yaotome|\u7981\u5343\u5f10\u767e\u62fe\u58f1\u5f0f\u30fb\u516b\u7a1a\u5973||lit. \"Forbidden Style 1211: Eight Maidens\"}} In ''The King of Fighters XIII'', Iori's gameplay mechanics were modified to become a close-range fighter. Despite losing his flaming techniques, he was given brutal moves using his nails to emphasize his ferociousness. Iori's strongest technique is {{nihongo|\"Forbidden 1218 Shiki: Yatagarasu\"|\u7981\u5343\u5f10\u767e\u62fe\u516b\u5f0f\u30fb\u516b\u54ab\u70cf}}, a new move that focuses on violent combinations and serves as a reference to the character's ending from ''The King of Fighters '96'', in which he murders his teammates. Iori's 10th color scheme in the game matches that of his classic outfit. During development of the game, details were added to increase the similarities.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2010/06/post_17.html| script-title=ja:\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u7d39\u4ecb \u516b\u795e\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0| publisher=SNK Playmore| date=June 24, 2011| accessdate=August 9, 2011| language=Japanese| title={title}| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110709093131/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2010/06/post_17.html| archive-date=July 9, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> This version, featuring his classic techniques, was designed to avoid surpassing the current Iori so players could choose the fighting style they prefer in the game.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_45.html| script-title=ja:\u708e\u3092\u53d6\u308a\u623b\u3057\u305f\u5eb5\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066| publisher=SNK Playmore| date=October 6, 2011| accessdate=October 6, 2011| language=Japanese| title={title}| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007115734/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_45.html| archive-date=October 7, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> This was further emphasized in the console version of ''The King of Fighters XIII'', in which Iori had his moveset were adjusted for better balance by not using flaming techniques.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_47.html| script-title=ja:\u7b2c\uff12\u56de\uff1a\u65e2\u5b58\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u306e\u8abf\u6574\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066| publisher=SNK Playmore| date=October 20, 2011| accessdate=October 24, 2011| language=Japanese| title={title}| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111025075455/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_47.html| archive-date=October 25, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAs downloadable content for ''The King of Fighters XIII'', SNK added the original Iori Yagami who can wield flames for his fighting style. This version was meant to be innovative similar rather than make him look like his classic ''The King of Fighters '95'' persona. Despite being the same person, the playstyle of Iori's flames is highly different from the regular Iori whose attacks involve hand-to-hand combat. Nevertheless, he was balanaced by SNK in order to avoid making the character be overpowered when exploring his special moves. Some distinguishable moves were given to him in order to give the player multiple options of tactics. This Neo Max was created with the idea of impressing gamers so that they would be attracted to use this version of the character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://game.snk-corp.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_45.html|title=\u708e\u3092\u53d6\u308a\u623b\u3057\u305f\u5eb5\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|publisher=SNK|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> In ''XIV'' The commands for Iori's moves were also affected; one of his strongest attacks, the {{nihongo|Ura 316 Shiki Saia|\u88cf316\u88cf\u53c2}}, would require high skill for regular players because SNK attempted to balance the characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/317/G031749/20160613002/index_2.html|title=\u65b0\u751fSNK\u306e\u30e2\u30ce\u4f5c\u308a\u306f\u3053\u3053\u304b\u3089\u59cb\u307e\u308b\u3002\u300c\u9913\u72fcMOW2\u300d\u306e\u8a71\u984c\u3082\u98db\u3073\u51fa\u3057\u305f\uff0c\u300cTHE KING OF FIGHTERS XIV\u300d\u958b\u767a\u9663\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30fc|publisher=4Gamer|accessdate=October 31, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n==Appearances==\n\n===In video games===\n====In main ''The King of Fighters'' games====\nIori is a violent, sadistic person who suffers from trauma because of his clan's past. In ancient times, the Yagami clan was known as the Yasakani who, With the help of the Yata and Kusanagi clans, sealed the demon Orochi. As time passed, the Yasakani tired of living in the shadow of the Kusanagi and made a blood pact with Orochi that gave them greater powers but cursed them and their descendants forever. They renamed their clan the Yagami and set out to destroy the Kusanagi with their new powers.<ref name=clanquote2/><ref name=clanquote2>{{cite video game|quote='''Spirit represented by purple flame:''' All is from the Orochi blood! From our blood allegiance. With the Orochi clan!/'''Kyo:''' Our clan? Yagami? The Yasakani clan?/'''Spirit represented by purple flame:''' A 660 year old error... It can't be corrected!|title=The King of Fighters '97 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 28, 1997 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Chizuru:''' The crimson flame of Yagami came from a part of your long-repressed true essence./'''Iori:''' Nonsense! I don't by [sic] that Freudian garbage!/'''Chizuru:''' The blue flames you control come from the Orochi power flowing within you. |title=The King of Fighters '96 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 30, 1996 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> The curse also causes each heir to die young and each mother to die in childbirth. Ior becomes obsessed with killing his heir Kyo, disregarding their clans' past. This sometimes results in Iori helping Kyo to defeat his enemies and to finish their battles.<ref name=enemy/> To find Kyo, Iori sometimes enters the King of Fighters tournaments and uses his teammates as tools to reach him.<ref name=tool/>\n\nIori Yagami first appeared in ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'', in which he enters an annual tournament as the leader of the Rival Team with Billy Kane and [[Eiji Kisaragi]]. Iori learns that the heir of the Kusanagi clan, [[Kyo Kusanagi|Kyo]], is expected to be there.<ref name=tool>{{cite web|title=Rival Team Official Story ~ KOF 95 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof95_story/index.php?num=rival |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509140115/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof95_story/index.php?num=rival|archivedate=May 9, 2016 }}</ref> After the team fails to defeat Kyo's team, Iori betrays his teammates.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Iori:''' What a fool! Such power can only by mine! Well, shall we wrap this up?/'''Eiji:''' What?/'''Billy:''' Hey! You're... you're Geese!/'''Iori:''' Just wait, Kyo. You're next for extermination. You and all Kusanagis! Yah, hah, hah|title=The King of Fighters '95 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 25, 1995 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> In the [[The King of Fighters '96|next video game]], Iori teams up with two women, [[Vice (King of Fighters)|Vice and Mature]], servants of the Orochi demon.<ref>{{cite web|title=The King of Fighters '98 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof98 |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=January 16, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fhEsGSDp?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof98 |archivedate=March 31, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=KOF 2002 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof2002 |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=January 29, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fhEwAHar?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof2002 |archivedate=March 31, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/neowave/|title=The King of Fighters Neowave official website|publisher=[[SNK Playmore]]|accessdate=August 8, 2008|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5ff9Ydd3i?url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/neowave/character/index.html|archive-date=March 30, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> During the '96 competition, Iori meets [[Chizuru Kagura]], the heir of the Yata clan who wants to gather Kyo and Iori on her team to seal Orochi. They defeat the Orochi follower [[Goenitz]] but neither Iori nor Kyo agree with the idea.<ref name=curse>{{cite video game|quote='''Mature:''' Are you shaking?/'''Vice:''' Yeah, he ain't normal. But, that guy... I mean... He's really tough./'''Iori:''' W, what? I can't see! Yaaah! Unnhhh! Gya... GWAAAAH!/'''Vice:''' Hey, Yagami, take it easy!/'''Mature:''' Oh, my God.../'''Iori:''' I, it's the... Riot of the Blood!/'''Vice:''' Gah. You mean there's nothing we can do?/'''Mature:''' Ooowaaaaah! Ya, Yagami!/'''Iori:''' GOOOWAAAAH!|title=The King of Fighters '96 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 30, 1996 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> When Iori leaves with his teammates, he cannot control his surge of Orochi power, resulting in their deaths.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Goenitz:''' I guess I understimated you. I never thought... but this isn't the end for you./'''Iori:''' Hah! \"ONE-FOR-THE-ROAD\" BLAST!/'''Goenitz:''' AHHHHH!/'''Kyo:''' Hah! Eat this, pal! SERPENT WAVE!/'''Goenitz:'''GYAAAH! Why? Why is there no wind? GYAAAAAH!|title=The King of Fighters '96 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 30, 1996 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> Iori continues to suffer from multiple outbreaks; during ''[[The King of Fighters '97]]'' he attacks other team members and appears as a [[Boss (video games)|sub-boss character]] in the game, depending on the characters the player uses.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iori Team Official Story ~ KOF 97 |url=http://kof.confusticated.com/frames.html |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705051310/http://kof.confusticated.com/frames.html |archivedate=July 5, 2008 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> He later joins Chizuru and Kyo to confront and seal Orochi.<ref name=enemy>{{cite video game|quote='''Iori:''' Aaaaah!! /'''Orochi:''' Kill Kusanagi and Yata! Break the Shingi troica! Fight, my Orochi son! Listen, Yagami! /'''Iori:'''Ahhhhhhh!!!/'''Orochi:''' Ah?!|title=The King of Fighters '97 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 28, 1997 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Kyo:''' Finish it, Kagura! Can you do it? /'''Chizuru:''' As a mirror keeper... I must do it! /'''Orochi:''' Fools! A waste of time! If I release my remaining power.../'''Iori:''' Waahh!/'''Chizuru:''' His power... too strong! Kusanagi! Quickly... /'''Kyo:''' Heeaahhh! Woooohh!|title=The King of Fighters '97 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 28, 1997 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref>\n\nIn most version of ''[[The King of Fighters '99]]'' Iori is a secret character that can be faced as a bonus fight at the end of the game if the player scores enough points. In the story, Iori discovers the creation of Kyo clones and enters the annual tournament, where he finds those responsible, an organization named [[List of The King of Fighters characters#The NESTS cartel|NESTS]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Iori Team Official Story ~ KOF 99 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof99_story/index.php?num=yagami |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080528113043/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof99_story/index.php?num=yagami |archive-date=May 28, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Iori follows the battles in secret and fights against the NESTS' agents to continue his fight against Kyo.<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters 2000 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 26, 2000 |platform=Neo Geo |quote='''Kyo:''' Consider that payback for the way you used us!/'''Zero:''' \"'Used' you?  The strength of your Mushiki move... was used to power the Zero Cannon. It's the ultimate compliment!/'''Kyo:''' In your sick fantasies! You conceited freak!.../'''Zero:''' Chill out. I'll soon be dead. Instead of me, think... of the one who awaits you.../'''Kyo:'''...Someone awaits me?/'''Iori:''' Enough prattle..../'''Kyo:''' Don't you think?  Here's \"someone\"! Let's rumble, dude!}}</ref> An assistant version of his character named Striker also appears for Iori in ''[[The King of Fighters 2000]]'' wearing an outfit based on illustrations in artbooks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof2000/kof2000_top.html |title=Another Striker |publisher=[[SNK Playmore]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=March 17, 2009 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fldpiXfv?url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof2000/kof2000_top.html |archivedate=April 3, 2009 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In ''[[The King of Fighters 2001]]'', an agent named [[Seth (King of Fighters)|Seth]] invites Iori to join his team for the next ''King of Fighters'' tournament, assuming he would get his shot against Kyo.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iori Team Official Story ~ KOF 2002 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2001_story/index.php?num=iori |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080528175725/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2001_story/index.php?num=iori |archive-date=May 28, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> While his regular form appears in ''KOF 2002'', his Orochi form is also featured in the PlayStation 2 port of the game and the remake of ''KOF '98''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/xbox/action/thekingoffighters2002/hints.html?tag=tabs;cheats|title=The King of Fighters 2002 Hints & Cheats|website=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=February 26, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/action/the-king-of-fighters-98-ultimate-match/cheats.html?tag=tabs%253Bcheats|title=The King of Fighters '98 Ultimate Match Hints & Cheats|website=[[GameSpot]]|accessdate=August 5, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110812003410/http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/action/the-king-of-fighters-98-ultimate-match/cheats.html?tag=tabs%253Bcheats|archive-date=August 12, 2011|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In ''[[The King of Fighters 2003]]'', Chizuru appears to both Kyo and Iori, asking them to form a team and investigate suspicious activities concerning the Orochi seal.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sacred Team Official Story ~ KOF 2003 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2003_story/index.php?num=3sacred |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080528193022/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2003_story/index.php?num=3sacred |archive-date=May 28, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> During the investigation, the team is ambushed by the fighter [[Ash Crimson]], who plans to get the power from the descendants of the clans who sealed Orochi and steals the ones from Chizuru.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Ash:''' Where... is... it... now?/'''Chizuru:''' Ah.. ah.../'''Ash:''' Oh, oh, oh, here we are. With this my objective has come to fruition.|title=The King of Fighters 2003 |developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=SNK Playmore |date=December 12, 2003 |platform=PlayStation 2 }}</ref>\n\nIn the [[The King of Fighters XI|following video game]], Iori and Kyo form a team with Kyo's student Shingo Yabuki to fill Chizuru's spot to stop Ash.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kyo & Iori Team Official Story in KOF XI |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/history/kofxi_story/index.php?num=kyo_iori |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 3, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218130024/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/history/kofxi_story/index.php?num=kyo_iori |archive-date=December 18, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> At the end of the tournament, the strengthening presence of Orochi causes Iori to enter the Riot of Blood state, in which he attacks his comrades. Ash appears afterward and defeats Iori, stealing his powers.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Iori:''' Oooh... I'll kill you... Kyo.../'''Shingo:''' Damn, damn, my body... Must save... Gagh, Mr. K-Kusanagi... He's going to be killed.../'''Ash:''' Well, well, what's going on here? And without any protection, either?/'''Shingo:''' Uh, Ash... Yagami just went crazy all of a sudden./'''Ash:''' Well, well, well. You're in a tough spot, aren't you?/'''Shingo:''' W-watch out. H-he's not like he usually is./'''Iori:''' K... Kill.../'''Ash:''' (So that's the look... Now I see. If he's gotten this far, it can only mean...) Heh, heh. Talk about pressure!/'''Iori:''' Ga, ga, ga, gaaaaah... |title=The King of Fighters XI |developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=SNK Playmore |date=November 13, 2007 |platform=PlayStation 2 }}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Ash:''' Holy moley, you're scary as ever. But that's not how it'll work out. And why? It's because I... am not the same old Ash./'''Elizabeth:''' That color! Iori Yagami's? No, it can't be, can it? The Orochi?!|title=The King of Fighters XI |developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=Igniton Entertainment |date=November 13, 2007 |platform=PlayStation 2 }}</ref> Iori is a playable character in ''[[The King of Fighters XII]]'', in which he is featured with a different outfit and a new moveset that does not use purple flames. He does not have a team.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xii/character/index.html| title=\u300e\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30baXII\u300f\u7a3c\u52d5\u6642\u671f\u304c\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01| publisher=Official The King of Fighters XII Homepage| accessdate=September 17, 2008| language=Japanese| archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5ff9Pj4uz?url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xii/character/index.html| archive-date=March 30, 2009| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> Iori's appearance in ''[[The King of Fighters XIII]]'' sees him teamed with Mature and Vice, his teammates from the 1996 tournament who return as spirits.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/character/index.html | title=CHARACTER THE KING OF FIGHTERS XIII | date=April 22, 2010 | accessdate=April 22, 2010 | publisher=SNK Playmore | language=Japanese | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100428035643/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/character/index.html | archive-date=April 28, 2010 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Following Ash's disappearance, Iori recovers his flames at the end and appears as downloadable content in this form.<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters XIII|developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=Atlus|year=2011|platform=PlayStation 4 |level=Team Yagami's ending}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2012-01-11/the-king-of-fighters-xiii-gets-two-new-dlc-characters/nests-style-kyo-and-mr-karate|title=The King of Fighters XIII Gets Two New DLC Characters: Nests Style Kyo and Mr. Karate|publisher=Anime News Network|date=January 11, 2012|accessdate=August 21, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925010311/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2012-01-11/the-king-of-fighters-xiii-gets-two-new-dlc-characters/nests-style-kyo-and-mr-karate|archive-date=September 25, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He returns in ''[[The King of Fighters XIV]]'', in which he tracks Orochi's weakened body in central Hungary after the tournament is over. He seals the weakened snake with the help of Kyo and Chizuru.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-09-16/on-with-the-show/.92999|title=The X Button On With the Show|publisher=Anime News Network|date=September 16, 2015|accessdate=September 16, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917175726/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-09-16/on-with-the-show/.92999|archive-date=September 17, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Iori wears a new costume in the game and his classic one appears as [[downloadable content]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.snk-corp.co.jp/us/games/kof-xiv/news/news06.php|title=DLC Costumes|publisher=SNK|accessdate=January 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180127071150/http://www.snk-corp.co.jp/us/games/kof-xiv/news/news06.php|archive-date=January 27, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters XIV |developer=SNK |publisher=Atlus|year=2016|platform=PlayStation 4 |level=Team Yagami's ending}}</ref>\n\n====Other games====\n[[File:MissXSNKHeroines.png|thumb|right|300px|The three looks of Miss X from ''SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy''.]]\n\nIn ''The King of Fighters: Kyo'', a [[role-playing video game]] set before the events of ''KOF '97'', Iori appears as Kyo's antagonist in his journey around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/consumer/psp.php | title=PSP\u5bb6\u5ead\u7528\u30bd\u30d5\u30c8\uff1aSNK\u30d7\u30ec\u30a4\u30e2\u30a2 \u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u60c5\u5831\u7dcf\u5408\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\u3000NEOGEO WORLD| website= SNK Playmore Official Homepage | accessdate=March 26, 2008 | language=Japanese |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071026051919/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/consumer/psp.php |archivedate = October 26, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba \u4eac |url=http://www.jp.playstation.com/ps3/psn/ac_title/0706-06.html?keepThis=true&TB_iframe=true&height=330&width=560 |website=Playstation.com |accessdate=March 26, 2008 |language=Japanese |title={title} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081222103843/http://www.jp.playstation.com/ps3/psn/ac_title/0706-06.html?keepThis=true&TB_iframe=true&height=330&width=560 |archive-date=December 22, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Both ''[[King of Fighters R-1]]'' and ''[[King of Fighters R-2]]'' feature the regular Iori and his berserker form as playable characters; the latter game features him as a teamless character.<ref>{{cite video game|title=King of Fighters R-1|developer=SNK|publisher=SNK|date=1998 |platform=Neo Geo Pocket|level=Savior Team Ending}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=King of Fighters R-2|developer=SNK|publisher=SNK|date=1998 |platform=Neo Geo Pocket|level=Edit Team Ending}}</ref> Iori appears in the spin-off video games [[The King of Fighters: Maximum Impact|''Maximum Impact'' series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snkplaymoreusa.com/game_kof2006.php|title=The King of Fighters: Maximum Impact 2 official website|publisher=[[SNK Playmore]]|accessdate=August 8, 2008 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080504022832/http://www.snkplaymoreusa.com/game_kof2006.php |archivedate = May 4, 2008}}</ref> In the North American editions of ''Maximum Impact'', Iori is voiced by Eric Summerer.<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters 2006 |developer=SNK Playmore|publisher=SNK Playmore|year=2006 |platform=PlayStation 2|level=Credits}}</ref> Iori appears as a sub-boss in ''The King of Fighters Ex: Neo Blood'', which is set after his fight against Orochi. Although Iori enters the tournament to fight Kyo, [[Geese Howard]], the organizer of the tournament, tries but fails to make him awaken his Riot of the Blood to absorb his powers. In ''[[The King of Fighters EX2: Howling Blood]]'', Iori enters another tournament and is joined by two women who want to find a man controlled by the Orochi power.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atlus.com/kofex2/teams_yagami.html|title=The King of Fighters EX2: Howling Blood official website|publisher=[[Atlus]]|accessdate=January 16, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090107033125/http://www.atlus.com/kofex2/teams_yagami.html|archive-date=January 7, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The shooter game ''KOF: Sky Stage'' also features Iori as a boss, while ''Neo Geo Heroes: Ultimate Shooting'' makes him playable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2009-11-04|author=Ciolek, Todd|title=The X Button Strange Days|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 4, 2009|accessdate=November 4, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091107045214/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2009-11-04|archive-date=November 7, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snk-corp.co.jp/official/neogeo_heroes/character/iori.html|title=Characters|publisher=SNK|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> He is also featured in ''KOF X Arena Masters'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nexon.co.jp/news/132611|title=\u3010\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9\u30ea\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u3011\u300eArena Masters\uff08\u30a2\u30ea\u30fc\u30ca\u30de\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba\uff09\u300f\u304c\u300eTHE KING OF FIGHTERS\u300f\u3068\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\uff01 \u4eac\u30fb\u30a2\u30c6\u30ca\u30fb\u5eb5\u304c\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u30d2\u30fc\u30ed\u30fc\u3068\u306a\u3063\u3066\u53c2\u6226\uff01|publisher=Nexon|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> ''Game of Dice''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kongbakpao.com/kof-98-characters-visiting-game-of-dice/|title=KOF '98 Characters Visiting Game of Dice!|publisher=Kongbakpao|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The King of Fighters All Star]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://altema.jp/kofallstar/charamatome/12|title=\u516b\u795e\u5eb5\u306e\u5168\u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba\u8a55\u4fa1\u3068\u30b9\u30ad\u30eb\u4e00\u89a7\n|publisher=Altima|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> and the Korean fighting game ''The King of Cyphers''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/1/165931.html|title=\u62f3\u7687 AR \u624b\u6a5f\u904a\u6232\u300a\u62f3\u7687\u5927\u86c7\u7bc7 Go\u300b\u5df2\u9054\u6700\u7d42\u958b\u767c\u968e\u6bb5 \u5c07\u5c55\u958b\u9ad4\u9a57\u8a66\u73a9\u6d3b\u52d5|work=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9|access-date=2018-07-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dreamcancel.com/2015/03/kyo-and-iori-show-up-in-new-korean-fighting-game-the-king-of-cyphers/|title=KYO AND IORI SHOW UP IN NEW KOREAN FIGHTING GAME \"THE KING OF CYPHERS\"|publisher=DreamCancel|accessdate=September 15, 2018|date=March 30, 2015}}</ref> SNK also released a [[pachinko]] based on the Orochi storyline.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slot.snk-corp.co.jp/official/kof/index.html|title=The King of Fighters|publisher=SNK|accessdate=September 16, 2018}}</ref> as well as the [[otome game]] ''King of Fighters for Girls''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-06-13/snk-victor-entertainment-reveal-king-of-fighters-for-girls-smartphone-game/.147812|title=SNK, Victor Entertainment Reveal 'King of Fighters for Girls' Smartphone Game|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=June 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIori also appears in SNK's hand-held game, ''[[SNK Gals' Fighters]]'', as a comical interpretation called {{nihongo|Miss X|\u30df\u30b9 X|Misu Ekkusu}}. The character insists he is a female in order to participate in the game's ''Queen of Fighters'' tournament, though several female fighters easily see through his disguise.<ref>{{cite video game|title=SNK Gals' Fighters |developer=Yumekobo |publisher=SNK of America |date=February 19, 2000 |platform=Neo Geo Pocket Color|quote='''Yuki:''' It's wish time! This Talisman will turn you into Ms. X forever.../'''Miss X:''' Argh! You're a sneaky tart!/'''Yuki:''' Tart? You asked for it! O, Talisman.../'''Miss X:''' Ah! Wait! I take it back! Curses...}}</ref> He is also present in ''[[The Rhythm of Fighters]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.androidcentral.com/rhythm-fighters-review|title=The Rhythm of Fighters review|website=AndroidCentral|accessdate=September 22, 2018|date=July 28, 2014}}</ref> Miss X reappears in the fighting game ''[[SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy]]'' as downloadable content, this time sharing both the original crossdresser and new true gender swapped form.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/10/25/missx-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-debut-will-occur-on-november-15-2018/|title=MissX SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy Debut Will Occur On November 15, 2018|accessdate=October 25, 2018|publisher=Siliconera}}</ref> In the story, Miss X fights against multiple female fighters (including his fellow gender-swapped fighters [[Terry Bogard]] and the guest fighter [[Skullomania]]) to stop the host Kukri and his ending involves an embarrassing nightmare in which he and Kyo become friendly rivals. Miss X's true identity, Iori also made a cameo on certain characters' endings in ''Heroines'', prior Miss X DLC debut.<ref>{{cite video game|title=SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy|developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=SNK|year=2018|platform=PlayStation 4 |stage=Miss X's ending}}</ref> In the crossover video games ''[[NeoGeo Battle Coliseum]]'' and ''[[SNK vs. Capcom]]'' series, Iori appears as a playable character; the latter includes his Riot of the Blood state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ignitionent.com/ngbc/main.htm |title=Neo Geo Battle Coliseum official website |publisher=[[SNK Playmore]] |accessdate=August 8, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061104041918/http://www.ignitionent.com/ngbc/main.htm |archivedate=November 4, 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capcom.co.jp/newproducts/consumer/cvss2/ |title=Capcom VS. SNK official website |publisher=[[Capcom]] |accessdate=August 8, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080808101118/http://www.capcom.co.jp/newproducts/consumer/cvss2/ |archivedate=August 8, 2008 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> His character is also a boss character (along with Geese) in the Game Boy version from ''[[Real Bout Fatal Fury Special]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/gameboy/action/nettourealboutgarouds/hints.html?tag=tabs;cheats|title=Nettou Real Bout Garou Densetsu Special Hints & Cheats|website=[[GameSpot]]|accessdate=April 15, 2009}}</ref> He also appears in [[Square Enix]]'s fighting game ''[[Million Arthur: Arcana Blood]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-26/million-arthur-arcana-blood-arcade-game-gets-ps4-release-on-november-29/.135931|title=Million Arthur: Arcana Blood Arcade Game Gets PS4 Release on November 29|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=August 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826075718/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-26/million-arthur-arcana-blood-arcade-game-gets-ps4-release-on-november-29/.135931|archive-date=August 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He is also available in ''The King Figthers X Fatal Fury'' mobile phone game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2013/04/28/king-of-fighters-x-fatal-fury-heats-up-at-snk-playmore/|title=King of Fighters X Fatal Fury Heats Up At SNK Playmore|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=September 11, 2018}}</ref> He is also present in the Chinese mobile phone game named ''KOF: WORLD'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kof.sdo.com:80/web1/about/about_03.asp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110512094018/http://kof.sdo.com/web1/about/about_03.asp|title=About|publisher=KOF SDO|accessdate=September 5, 2018|archivedate=May 12, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> the [[visual novel]] ''Days of Memories'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snk-corp.co.jp/official/dom/dom2/series1/|title=Days of Memories|publisher=SNK|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> ''Metal Slug Defense'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://store.steampowered.com/app/361470/METAL_SLUG_DEFENSE__KOF_Pack_Vol1/?l=tchinese|title=METAL SLUG DEFENSE - \"KOF Pack\" Vol.1|publisher=Steam|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> ''Lords of Vermillion'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www30.atwiki.jp/lord_of_vermilion/pages/1009.html|title=\u30ed\u30fc\u30c9\u30aa\u30d6\u30f4\u30a1\u30fc\u30df\u30ea\u30aa\u30f3\u3010LORD of VERMILION\u3011|publisher=Atwiki|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> and ''Lucent Heart''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lh.gamania.co.jp/landing/colabo/kof/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100620000101/http://lh.gamania.co.jp/landing/colabo/kof/|title=Update|publisher=Lucent Heart|accessdate=November 8, 2018|archivedate=June 20, 2010}}</ref> The character's original look is also being used in [[action role-playing]] ''[[Phantasy Star Online 2]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2019/02/22/kyo-iori-athena-mai-and-leona-join-phantasy-star-online-2-as-new-costumes/|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=February 22, 2019|title=Kyo, Iori, Athena, Mai, And Leona Join Phantasy Star Online 2 As New Costumes}}</ref>\n\nIori Yagami made his appearance as playable hero in ''War Song'', a mobile [[multiplayer online battle arena]] (MOBA) developed by Morefun Studio, a game studio owned by [[Tencent]]. Iori Yagami also made his appearance in another mobile MOBA game, ''Mobile Legends: Bang Bang'', as a skin for the hero Chou as a result of collaboration between Moonton and SNK.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://egg.network/news/king-fighters-and-mobile-legends-have-epic-collaboration|title=King of Fighters And Mobile Legends Have An EPIC Collaboration!|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.player.one/moonton-snk-king-fighters-mobile-legends-124909|title=Mobile Legends Adds King Of Fighters Skins|last=|first=|date=March 18, 2019|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Iori appears as one of the background characters on the King of Fighters Stadium stage in ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]''. In addition a costume based on him for the Mii Brawler appears as downloadable content.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2019/11/06/iori-nakoruru-ryo-akira-and-jacky-bryant-join-super-smash-bros-ultimates-mii-costumes/|title=Iori, Nakoruru, Ryo, Akira, And Jacky Bryant Join Super Smash Bros. Ultimate\u2019s Mii Costumes|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===In other media===\n\nAside from the ''King of Fighters'' series, the character is featured in an [[audio drama]]<ref>{{cite AV media notes | author= SNK | year=1999| title=Iori Yagami Original Drama -Sun and Moon- ~ Prologue| publisher=Pony Canyon Inc. | id=PCCB-00380 }}</ref> and a character [[image album]].<ref>{{cite AV media notes | author= SNK | year=1999| title=SNK Character Sounds Collection Volume 11 ~ Iori Yagami| publisher=Pony Canyon Inc. | id=PCCB-00378 }}</ref> In the anime ''[[The King of Fighters: Another Day]]'', Iori searches for Ash to regain his powers.<ref>{{cite video game|title=KOF Maximum Impact 2 |developer=SNK Playmore|publisher=SNK Playmore|date=April 27, 2006 |platform=PlayStation 2|level=The King of Fighters: Another Day}}</ref> Iori appears in the spin-off [[manga]] story entitled ''The King of Fighters: Kyo'', which is based on his adventure prior to ''[[The King of Fighters '96]]''.<ref>{{cite book |last=Natsumoto|first=Masato |title=The King of Fighters Kyo, volume 1|year=1996 |publisher=Kodansha|isbn=978-4-06-319759-4 }}</ref> Ryo Takamisaki's manga ''The King of Fighters G'' shows an alternative retelling of ''KOF '96'' in which Iori faces Kyo and Athena Asamiya.<ref>{{cite book |last=Takamisaki |first=Ryo|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30baG|year=1997 |publisher=Shinsenga|isbn=978-4881993507|volume=1}}</ref> The character appears in a [[manhua]] adaptation of ''The King of Fighters: Zillion'' created by [[Andy Seto]] that retells Iori's story of his fight against Orochi until he attacks NESTS to destroy Kyo's clones. He also stars in other manhua for the games, starting with ''The King of Fighters 2001'' and ending with ''2003'' along with the ''Maximum Impact'' series.<ref name=kofanivmanhua>{{cite web |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=6| title=Remembrances of KOF: An Interview with Eiji |publisher= King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=July 28, 2008 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080418040418/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=6 |archivedate = April 18, 2008}}</ref> In the manga ''The King of Fighters: A New Beginning'', Vice and Mature force the Orochi power to make Iori lose his mind during his battle with Kyo. The battle ends in a draw with Iori's team losing due the other fighters' rounds.<ref>{{cite book|title=The King of Fighters: A New Beginning|year=2018|volume=1|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|isbn=|author=Asuma, Ky\u014dtar\u014d|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The King of Fighters: A New Beginning|year=2019|volume=2|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|isbn=978-4757205970|author=Asuma, Ky\u014dtar\u014d|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nIori is played by [[Will Yun Lee]] in the film ''[[The King of Fighters (film)|The King of Fighters]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kotaku.com/5286754/king-of-fighters-movie-promotional-images |title=King of Fighters Movie Promotional Images |publisher=[[Kotaku]] |author=Ashcraft, Brian |date=July 11, 2009 |accessdate=August 16, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090815031856/http://kotaku.com/5286754/king-of-fighters-movie-promotional-images |archive-date=August 15, 2009 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In the CGI series ''[[The King of Fighters: Destiny]]'' Iori makes a brief appearance in the first season's finale, in which he tries to play music but starts going berserk.<ref>{{cite AV media|title=The King of Fighters: Destiny|number=24 |work=iDRAGONS Creative Studio, SNK}}</ref> He is one of two protagonists alongside Kyo in online gag manga ''Part Time Stories: Kyo & Iori'' by [[Falcoon]]; the two title characters work together to promote SNK's merchandising.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.snk-onlineshop.com/parttimestories/|title=Part Time Stories: Kyo & Iori|publisher=SNK|language=Japanese|accessdate=February 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180204000245/https://www.snk-onlineshop.com/parttimestories/|archive-date=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He is also featured in the manga ''The King of Fighters: A New Beginning''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/263400|title=\u683c\u95d8\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u300cKOF\u300d\u4eba\u6c17\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u7dcf\u51fa\u6f14\u306e\u30b3\u30df\u30ab\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba\u304c\u30de\u30ac\u30dd\u30b1\u3067\u59cb\u52d5|publisher=Natalie|language=Japanese|accessdate=January 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180114073634/https://natalie.mu/comic/news/263400|archive-date=January 14, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Iori is also present in novels based on the series.<ref>{{cite book|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba2000\u2015STRIKERS STRIKE BACK|year=2001|isbn=978-4757703483|publisher=Enterbrain |author=Ureshino, Akihiko|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba'99\u2015BEYOND THE\"K\"|year=1999|publisher=[[SNK]]|isbn=978-4757205970 |author=Ureshino, Aikhiko|trans-title=The King of Fighters '99 \uff5eBEYOND THE \"K\"|language=Japanese}}</ref> He is also set to be the protagonist of the light novel series ''Iori Yagami's Isekai Mu'sou'' by Nobuhiko Tenkawa which depicts him in an alternate universe fighting goblins.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321903000741/|title=THE KING OF FANTASY \u516b\u795e\u5eb5\u306e\u7570\u4e16\u754c\u7121\u53cc \u6708\u3092\u898b\u308b\u305f\u3073\u601d\u3044\u51fa\u305b\uff01|work=Kadokawa Shoten|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n\nThe character Iori Yagami was mostly well received by several video game publications and other media. [[IGN]]'s A. E. Sparrow considered him one of the most useful of the games' characters and one of the best characters for \"veteran players\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/445/445739p1.html|title=King of Fighters 2000/2001 Review|publisher=[[IGN]]|author=Sparrow, A. E.|date=December 11, 2003|accessdate=August 8, 2008|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6c0lpBsAW?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2003/12/11/king-of-fighters-20002001|archive-date=October 3, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>  He is ranked in the top-ten fighting games from [[GameTrailers]] and has been called one of the series' innovative characters from his introduction in ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' and during his development in the following games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gametrailers.com/player/47398.html|title=Top 10 Fighting Games|date=April 6, 2009|publisher=[[GameTrailers]]|accessdate=April 6, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408070007/http://www.gametrailers.com/player/47398.html|archive-date=April 8, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Some commentators found his recurring interactions with Kyo Kusanagi during fights to be appealing, adding depth to the games, despite English gamers not being able to understand them, and the lack of a storyline in some.<ref>{{Cite web|accessdate=August 17, 2011|url=https://www.wired.com/gamelife/2010/11/king-of-fighters-2002-review/|title=Review: King of Fighters 2002 Ultimate Match Delivers Knockout Action|author=Feit, Daniel|website=Wired.com|date=November 10, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101115012227/http://www.wired.com/gamelife/2010/11/king-of-fighters-2002-review/|archive-date=November 15, 2010|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nKevin S. from [[GameRevolution]] liked the interactions between Kyo and Iori in ''The King of Fighters XIV'' because it was one of the most famous parts from the series. The addition of a unique theme song to Iori's and Kyo's rival fight was also praised.<ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/the-king-of-fighters-xiv|title=The King of Fighters XIV Review|author=S., Kevin |publisher=[[GameRevolution]] |date=August 23, 2016 |archiveurl= https://archive.is/20160823182901/http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/the-king-of-fighters-xiv |archivedate= August 23, 2016 |accessdate= April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://royalflushmagazine.com/gaming/review-kof-xiv/#.W6buzHtKiUk|title=Review: King of Fighters XIV (KOF XIV)|publisher=RoyalFlush Magazine|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> Meristation compared Kyo's and Iori's antagonistic rivalry to that of [[Goku]] and [[Vegeta]] from the ''[[Dragon Ball]]'' manga by [[Akira Toriyama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meristation.com.mx/the-king-of-fighters-xiv-impresiones-e3/avance-juego/2132969|title=The King of Fighters XIV, Impresiones E3|website=Meristation|accessdate=September 15, 2018}}</ref> ''The Daily Star'' noted Kyo's and Iori's popularity comes from the way Kyo and Iori start facing each other as enemies but still become allies for other games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/shout/overclock/king-fighters-legacy-1376431|title=King of Fighters XIV|date=March 16, 2017|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> ThunderBoltGames stated that Iori stands out within the plot because of his rivalry with Kyo and because he is cursed with Orochi's power, which makes his heroic traits questionable yet well-written despite the series being from the fighting game genre.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thunderboltgames.com/review/the-king-of-fighters-collection-the-orochi-saga-2|title=The King of Fighters Collection: The Orochi Saga|date=December 6, 2008|publisher=ThunderBoltGames|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref> The formation of the Three Sacred Treasures Team in ''The King of Fighters '96'' had a major impact with fans because it was appealing because of the Orochi saga and because of its incorporation of Japanese mythology.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atomix.vg/feature-the-king-of-fighters-96-retro-review/|title=FEATURE \u2013 THE KING OF FIGHTERS 96 (RETRO REVIEW)|publisher=Atomix|accessdate=November 1, 2018|language=Spanish|date=August 26, 2016}}</ref> 4thletter enjoyed the ''KOF '97'' of Kyo, Kagura and Iori, stating \"this [is how you write a climax to a four-year-long story]\" at the ending of the Orochi story arc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://4thletter.net/2013/07/the-top-200-fighting-game-endings-part-ten/|title=The Top 200 Fighting Game Endings: Part Ten|publisher=4thletter|accessdate=April 19, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125062206/http://4thletter.net/2013/07/the-top-200-fighting-game-endings-part-ten/|archivedate=January 25, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Lucke M. Albiges from [[Eurogamer]] praised Iori as having one of the most unpredictable appearances in the series, and considered him a veteran character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=79794|title=King Of Fighters XI Review|publisher=[[Eurogamer]]|author=Albiges, Lucke M.|date=July 14, 2007|accessdate=August 15, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081204234108/http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=79794|archive-date=December 4, 2008|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAcross the franchise, Iori has been given new looks and techniques which have also resulted in different kind of responses. IGN's Jeremy Dunham praised Iori's appearance in ''[[KOF: Maximum Impact]]'' as one of the best designs from the game. However, Dunham complained about his lack of bloody scenes considering his actions in previous 2D games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/554/554861p1.html|title=King of Fighters: Maximum Impact Review|publisher=[[IGN]]|author=Dunham, Jeremy|date=October 14, 2004|accessdate=August 8, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081013100343/http://ps2.ign.com/articles/554/554861p1.html|archive-date=October 13, 2008|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The character's new design from ''[[The King of Fighters XII]]'' has been well received by [[GameSpot]] writer Andrew Park who found such moves interesting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1up.com/do/previewPage?cId=3174300&p=37|accessdate=May 10, 2016|author=Park, Andrew|date=July 31, 2009|website=[[GameSpot]]|title=The King of Fighters XII is the latest chapter in 15 years of fighting game history. It's also a disappointment.|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hSR9wWJB?url=http://www.1up.com/reviews/king-fighters-12-review|archivedate=May 12, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On the other hand, [[1UP.com]] writer Richard Li; Li complained about the lack of Iori's signature moves such as his fireballs, and while some of them remained, Li noted that they now require a different input from the ones they normally require.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1up.com/do/previewPage?cId=3174300&p=37 |accessdate=May 25, 2009 |author=Li, Richard |date=May 20, 2009 |publisher=[[1UP.com]] |title=1UP.com: The King of Fighters XII (PS3) |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hSR9wWJB?url=http://www.1up.com/reviews/king-fighters-12-review |archivedate=May 12, 2016 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The Orochi form from Iori was listed as the sixth best altered video game character alongside Leona's based on the impact both have on the storyline by [[Den of Geek]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/fighting-games/265246/the-20-best-altered-fighting-game-characters|title=The 20 Best Altered Fighting Game Characters|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=June 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706031040/http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/fighting-games/265246/the-20-best-altered-fighting-game-characters|archive-date=July 6, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Den of Geek same site also listed him as the fourth best ''King of Fighters'' characters based on his moves, rivalry with Kyo as well as apparent character arc based on how he retakes his lost powers in ''KOF XIII'' and used them in ''KOF XIV'' to once again seal Orochi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/king-of-fighters/258397/king-of-fighters-ranking-all-the-characters/page/0/5|title=King of Fighters: Ranking All the Characters|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=July 31, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731191855/http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/king-of-fighters/258397/king-of-fighters-ranking-all-the-characters/page/0/5|archive-date=July 31, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The writer noted that while Iori started as \"anti-hero\" due to his tendency to beat up his own teammates in his first two games, he would join forces Kyo for a greater good in upcoming titles which changed the way he was seen. However, the fact that Iori is defeated by Ash in ''KOF XI'' was noted to be the opposite due to how much it affected him to the point of creating a new fighting style that does not involve flames.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/king-of-fighters/255602/king-of-fighters-xiv-team-yagami-trailer|title=King of Fighters XIV: Team Yagami Trailer|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nTodd Ciolek from [[Anime News Network]] found Iori's appearance in ''KOF XIV'' dated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-12-10/expert-ease/.96324|title=The X Button Expert Ease|author=Ciolek, Todd|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 12, 2015|accessdate=April 14, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623202947/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-12-10/expert-ease/.96324|archivedate=June 23, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, Iori's return to his classic techniques in ''KOF XIV'' mainly using flames were celebrated by ''[[Hobby Consolas]]'' because of their popularity with fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hobbyconsolas.com/reviews/king-fighters-xiv-analisis-65028|title=The King Of Fighters XIV - An\u00e1lisis|publisher=Hobby Consolas|accessdate=February 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205040743/https://www.hobbyconsolas.com/reviews/king-fighters-xiv-analisis-65028|archive-date=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=August 22, 2016}}</ref> Atinux agreed, calling the character \"sadistic\" because of the violence of his attacks, most notably seen in his strongest moves that reference his enhanced Orochi form from previous games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atomix.vg/el-buen-iori-loco-y-su-equipo-se-presentan-en-the-king-of-fighters-xiv/|title=EL BUEN IORI (LOCO) Y SU EQUIPO SE PRESENTAN EN THE KING OF FIGHTERS XIV|publisher=Atomix|accessdate=October 30, 2018|date=May 19, 2016}}</ref> Shoryuken said that while Iori and Vice showed appealing skills in their ''KOF XIV'' trailer, they were overshadowed by Mature's techniques.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://shoryuken.com/2016/05/18/team-yagami-mature-revealed-alongside-iori-and-vice-in-latest-king-of-fighters-xiv-trailer/|title=Team Yagami: Mature Revealed Alongside Iori and Vice in Latest King of Fighters XIV Trailer|publisher=Shoryuken|access-date=September 22, 2018|date=May 18, 2016}}</ref>\n\nJournalists have also commented on Iori's appearances outside the ''KOF'' games. For the release of the tag game ''[[NeoGeo Battle Coliseum]]'', IGN suggested using Kyo and Iori as partners due to the moves they could perform together.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2008/01/04/neogeo-battle-coliseum-review-2|title=NeoGeo Battle Coliseum review|publisher=IGN|accessdate=September 15, 2018}}</ref> Iori's crossdressing persona Miss X has been popular; SNK stated they received multiple requests to add him into the crossover game ''[[SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy]]'', an upcoming fighting game focused on female characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2018/03/interview-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-yasuyuki-oda-kaito-soranaka-nis-america-staff|title=Interview: SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy's Yasuyuki Oda, Kaito Soranaka, and NIS America staff|publisher=Gematsu|accessdate=March 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180306082856/https://gematsu.com/2018/03/interview-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-yasuyuki-oda-kaito-soranaka-nis-america-staff|archive-date=March 6, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Destructoid]] stated he was shocked by Miss X's debut in ''SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy'' because of Iori's obvious secret identity and because she has different incarnations with a different gender and outfit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/miss-x-sizzles-in-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-528588.phtml|title=Miss X sizzles in SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy|publisher=Destructoid|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref> Atomix shared similar feelings but refrained from revealing the character's true identity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atomix.vg/la-tercera-peleadora-dlc-de-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-es-iori-yagami/|title=LA TERCERA PELEADORA DLC DE SNK HEROINES: TAG TEAM FRENZY ES\u2026 \u00a1IORI YAGAMI!|publisher=Atomix|accessdate=October 30, 2018|date=October 25, 2018}}</ref> Universo Nintendo originally thought the DLC character would be an alternative version of Ash Crimson and was surprised by the revelation. The website said Miss X's second form is possibly the most humiliating version because the character is wearing a t-shirt of his rival Kyo. Nevertheless, the character's movements were thought to be similar to those of the original Iori and thus long-time gamers would easily play as Miss X.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://universo-nintendo.com.mx/2018/10/25/iori-yagami-snk-heroines-para-nintendo-switch/|title=Iori Yagami\u2026 Perd\u00f3n, Miss X Llegar\u00e1 A SNK Heroines Para Nintendo Switch|publisher=Universo Nintendo|accessdate=October 30, 2018|date=October 26, 2018}}</ref> Den of Geek found the comic ''SVC Chaos'' ridiculous because as Iori commits suicide to follow the deceased Kyo to the Underworld.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/books-comics/street-fighter/235222/the-strange-history-of-street-fighter-comics|title=The Strange History of Street Fighter Comics|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=September 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Popularity===\nIori has been very popular with video gamers. In ''Gamest'''s 1996 Heroes Collection, Iori was ranked second in the poll Best Character from 1996.<ref>{{Cite book | year=1996 | editor=Gamest | title=Gamest Game Hero Collection 1996;| pages=2 | language=Japanese | publisher=Shinseisha }}</ref> In an issue from 1997, Iori was voted as the staff's favorite character, claiming first place over fifty other characters.<ref>{{Cite book | year=1997 | editor=Gamest | title=Gamest Game Hero Collection 1997; issue 208 | pages=1 | language=Japanese | publisher=Shinseisha }}</ref> He received the same rank on Neo Geo Freak's website with 3,792 votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neogeofreak.co.jp/ninki01htm.htm|title=Character polls|publisher=Official Neo Geo Freak website (archived version)|accessdate=January 26, 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000619213519/http://www.neogeofreak.co.jp/ninki01htm.htm |archivedate=June 19, 2000}}</ref> In a 2005 poll conducted by SNK-Playmore USA, he was voted the fans' eighth-favorite character with 145 votes.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://blog.ureshino.cn/?eid=19860#sequel | script-title=ja:\u30a6\u30ec\u30e6\u30b5\u65e5\u8a1803 | website=Akihiko Ureshino official web site | accessdate=September 16, 2008 | language=Japanese | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219051912/http://blog.ureshino.cn/?eid=19860#sequel | archivedate=February 19, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Merchandising based on Iori, including figurines, key-chains and puzzles, has been released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B0009PLEHO|title=Capcom vs SNK2 - Action Figures Series 1: Iori|language=Japanese|accessdate=August 17, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000V98GBK|title=Capcom vs Snk : King of Fighters Iori 3D 2\"-3\" Action Figure Key Chain|accessdate=August 17, 2008}}</ref> Two scale figures based on Iori's original form and his ''XIV'' look have also been released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/08/16/the-king-of-fighters-gantaku-scale-figures-shown-off-at-taipeis-2018-comic-exhibition/|title=The King Of Fighters Gantaku Scale Figures Shown Off At Taipei's 2018 Comic Exhibition|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref>  A replica of his ''KOF XIV'' coat was produced for merchandising.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.celebsmoviejackets.com/iori-yagami-kof-xiv-coat|title=King of Fighters XIV Iori Yagami Coat|publisher=Celebsmoviejackets|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn the book ''Gaming Cultures and Place in Asia-Pacific'', Iori was regarded as one of the most popular video game characters in Hong Kong from the mid 1990s onward alongside Kyo, Mai and others, to the point of overshadowing the ''Street Fighter'' characters, which were also well-known.<ref>{{cite book|title=Gaming Cultures and Place in Asia-Pacific|isbn=978-0415996273|author1=Hjorth, Larissa |author2=Chan, Dean |publisher=Routledge|year=2009|page=87|chapter=Consuming and Localizing Japanese Combat Games in Hong Kong}}</ref> The developers of ''KOF'' noted that Kyo and Iori were very popular in Korea, which led to their immediate inclusion is ''The King of Fighters 2001'' which was the first game in the series that was not developed by the original company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmcafe.com/news/news03-8-01.htm|title=KOF2001 \"Dream Match Revival\"(tentative title) to be released- |publisher=MMCafe|accessdate=September 16, 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Iori was voted as the seventh-most-popular Neo Geo character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.famitsu.com/news/201807/05160468.html|title=NEOGEO mini\uff08\u30cd\u30aa\u30b8\u30aa\u30df\u30cb\uff09\u767a\u58f2\u8a18\u5ff5\u3000\u597d\u304d\u306a\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\u4eba\u6c17\u6295\u7968\uff06NEOGEO mini\u5165\u3063\u3066\u307b\u3057\u304b\u3063\u305f\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u306e\u30a2\u30f3\u30b1\u30fc\u30c8\u7d50\u679c\u3092\u4e2d\u9593\u767a\u8868\uff01\u30001\u4f4d\u306f\u30b3\u30a4\u30c4\u3067\"\u30aa\u30fc\u30b1\u30fc\uff01\"|publisher=Famitsu|language=Japanese|accessdate=July 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705173649/https://www.famitsu.com/news/201807/05160468.html|archive-date=July 5, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nTo choose the cover for the Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3 ports of ''KOF XII'', [[Ignition Entertainment]] started a survey on May 4, 2009, in which users of their forum could vote for one of two covers they wanted to see in the game. While both covers feature multiple characters, one uses Kyo in the center and the other Iori.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=635|title=Rock the Box: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII Xbox 360 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810172051/http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=635|archivedate=August 10, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=636|title=Rock the Box: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII PlayStation 3 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-04|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5gWwMf78I?url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=636|archivedate=May 4, 2009|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> When the two surveys ended, Ignition started two new ones that asked people to vote between the previous winners and the Japanese covers from the game for both consoles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=727|title=Rock the Box Round 2: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII Xbox 360 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-20|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5gw0fxsWy?url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=727|archivedate=May 21, 2009|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=726|title=Rock the Box Round 2: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII PS3 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-20|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5gw0iCerX?url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=726|archivedate=May 21, 2009|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In late 2018, Iori and other SNK characters appeared as part of collaborations with other companies in [[Harajuku]], Japan, involving new merchandising. Iori's image was made by Falcoon.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000179.000028651.html|title=11\u670823\u65e5\uff08\u91d1\u30fb\u795d\uff09\u304b\u3089\u30ad\u30c7\u30a4\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u539f\u5bbf\u5e97\u306b\u3066\u300eSNK\u00d7\u30ad\u30c7\u30a4\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u539f\u5bbf\uff5eKawaii Holiday\u266a\uff5e\u300f\u3092\u958b\u50ac\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01|publisher=Pr Times|language=Japanese|accessdate=November 14, 2018}}</ref> Game designer [[Masahiro Sakurai]] was amazed when first seeing Iori in ''The King of Fighters '95'' due to his attitude and moves which made him praise the designers.<ref name=\"smash\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yK3VltKv3JI&t=2405s|title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate \u2013 Mr. Sakurai Presents \"Terry Bogard\"|publisher=Youtube|work=Nintendo|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n{{King of Fighters games}}\n\n[[Category:Action film characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional Japanese people in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional rock musicians]]\n[[Category:Male characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Musician characters in video games]]\n[[Category:SNK antagonists]]\n[[Category:SNK protagonists]]\n[[Category:The King of Fighters characters]]\n[[Category:Video game bosses]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in comics]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in film]]\n[[Category:Video game characters introduced in 1995]]\n[[Category:Video game characters with fire or heat abilities]]\n[[Category:Video game guest characters]]\n[[Category:Video game secret characters]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Fictional character}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox character\n|image=IoriYagamiXIII.png\n|name= Iori Yagami\n|caption=Iori Yagami in ''[[The King of Fighters XIII]]'' illustrated by Ogura\n|firstgame=''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' (1995)\n|series=[[The King of Fighters]]\n|designer=\n|voice=[[Kunihiko Yasui]]<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters '95 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 25, 1995 |platform=Neo Geo |level=Credits}}</ref> (''KOF '95'' - ''KOF XIII'')<br/>[[Takanori Hoshino]] (''KOF XIV'' onwards)<br/>Chisa Horii (female; ''SNKH: TTF'')<ref name=chisa>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=MTEP7NIwD3w|title=SNK\u30d2\u30ed\u30a4\u30f3\u30ba - DLC\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\u300c\u30df\u30b9X\u300d|via=YouTube|date=October 25, 2018|accessdate=October 25, 2018}}</ref><br/>Sho Sudo (Japanese dub of the King of Fighters movie)\n|portrayer  = [[Will Yun Lee]] (2010 film)\n|origin = Japan<br />United States <small>(2010 film)</small> \n|nationality = Japanese<br />[[Japanese Americans|Japanese-American]] <small>(2010 film)</small> \n|fighting_style=Yagami style of ancient martial arts + Pure instinct\n}} \n{{nihongo|'''Iori Yagami'''|\u516b\u795e \u5eb5|Yagami Iori|lead=yes}} is a character from [[SNK]]'s ''[[The King of Fighters]]'' [[video game]] series. The character first appeared in ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' as the leader of the Rivals Team, as the initial enemy and later rival of [[Kyo Kusanagi]]. Iori is the heir of the Yagami clan, who use [[pyrokinesis|pyrokinetic]] powers and sealed the [[Orochi (King of Fighters)|Orochi]] devil along with the Kusanagi and Yata clans. Iori suffers from a curse&nbsp;\u2013&#32;{{nihongo|\"The Riot of the Blood\"|\u8840\u306e\u66b4\u8d70|Chi no B\u014dso}}&nbsp;\u2013&#32;under which he becomes faster, stronger and wilder, exhibiting a deadly tendency to indiscriminately attack everyone in close proximity. In this state, Iori is commonly called \"Wild Iori\" or {{nihongo|\"Orochi Iori\"|\u6708\u306e\u591c\u5927\u86c7\u306e\u8840\u306b\u72c2\u3046\u5eb5|Tsuki no Yoru Orochi no Chi ni Kuruu Iori|lit. Insane Iori with Blood of Orochi Under the Night of the Moon}}.<ref name=curse/> Aside from the main series, Iori appears in several other media series, including [[Spin-off (media)|spin-offs]], crossover video games, and comic adaptations of the series.\n\nIori was created as Kyo's rival; his name and abilities were designed to relate him with the legend of ''[[Yamata no Orochi]]''. The designers ended up liking him so much they are careful of the character's [[Characterisation|development]] as the series expands. \nAs a result, Iori sometimes helps Kyo to have the opportunity to fight him. Finding his design appealing, new outfits presented the SNK staff with difficulties as they devised new appearances for the character that would retain his popularity.\n\nVideo game journalists have praised Iori Yagami as one of the most powerful characters in the series. Reviewers have also cited Iori as one of the best characters from the games, labeling him as a veteran character and praising his appearance as one of SNK's best creations. \"Miss X\", Iori's crossdressing form from ''[[SNK Gals' Fighters]]'' and the additional female one of ''[[SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy]]'', also received attention for its humor. A series of collectible items based on Iori's likeness, including key chains and figurines, have been manufactured.\n\n==Conception and creation==\n===Origins===\nIori's name is losely based on the Japanese mythological creature [[Yamata no Orochi]].<ref>{{cite book|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba\u201997\u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30b3\u30ec\u30af\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3 (\u30b2\u30fc\u30e1\u30b9\u30c8\u30e0\u30c3\u30af Vol. 93) \u30e0\u30c3\u30af \u2013 |year=1997|isbn=978-4881993811|publisher=Shinshosha|page=18}}</ref> In contrast to Kyo's life, SNK decided to keep Iori's life as private despite some related material mentioning the fact that Iori has relatives.<ref>{{cite cd|title=Snk Characters Sounds Collection Vol.11 \u516b\u795e\u5eb5|id=PCCB-00378|publisher=Scitron, Pony Canyon|year=1999}}</ref>  One of the planned objectives for ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' was to properly introduce Iori as Kyo Kusanagi's rival. According to his creators, Iori's personality and other aspects of his character such as his phrases and unique moves \"broke the mold for characters in fighting games at that time\".<ref name=kofaniviori/>  Like Kyo, several aspects of Iori, including his surname and abilities, were designed to relate him to the Japanese legend Yamata no Orochi, which was the inspiration for the plot.<ref name=kofaniviori>{{cite web | url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=iori | title=Iori Yagami Official Profile | quote=When you think of Iori Yagami, his intense personality most likely comes to mind. His moves are unique, and his dives choice of hairstyle, wardrobe, and manner of speaking was certainly a personality that broke the mold of former characters in fighting games at that time. During the initial location tests to determine the popularity of the game, Iori was the character who stood out most. His hair and his lines to provoke his opponents (\"You think I'm scary, do you?\") excited his fans to no end. | website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=March 24, 2008 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080410074739/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=iori | archive-date=April 10, 2008 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> After watching fan reactions at initial location testing for ''King of Fighters '95'', several staff members predicted Iori would be popular.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=8| title=Remembrances of KOF: An Interview with C.A.C Yamazaki | website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=March 24, 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080418040428/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=8|archivedate=April 18, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=11 |title=Remembrances of KOF: An Interview with Mr. Marito |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=March 24, 2008 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fvxXUUWS?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=8 |archivedate=April 10, 2009 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> One staff member was happy that at an event for ''[[The King of Fighters XIII]]'' on March 25, 2010, several fans reminded him that day is Iori's birthday according to his official profile.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://news.dengeki.com/elem/000/000/279/279862/| title=\u65e9\u304f\u904a\u3093\u3067\u307b\u3057\u3044\uff01 \u300eKOF XIII\u300f\u958b\u767a\u30b9\u30bf\u30c3\u30d52\u4eba\u304c\u7a3c\u50cd\u76f4\u524d\u306e\u6c17\u6301\u3061\u3092\u544a\u767d\uff01| publisher=ASCII Media Works| date=July 13, 2011| accessdate=August 1, 2011| language=Japanese| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110812040226/http://news.dengeki.com/elem/000/000/279/279862/| archive-date=August 12, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> The pixel art of Iori was made by Yuichiro Hiraki who, despite leaving SNK to work in another project a few years later, was asked by [[Capcom]]'s Kaname Fujioka to once again work on the character's design for the crossover fighting game ''[[Capcom vs. SNK: Millennium Fight 2000]]''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Devil May Cry: 3142 Graphic Arts|publisher=Capcom, Udon Entertainment|year=2015|isbn=978-1927925485|pages=198}}</ref>\n\nIori was originally introduced in ''The King of Fighters '95'' as the leader of a team composed of [[Billy Kane]], [[Eiji Kisaragi]] and himself. Each member shares a rivalry with another character in the game. Although the staff members worked hard to impress their superiors at SNK, Iori's characterization caused them to discard the team in the next game in the series. In the rival team's ending, Iori betrays Billy and Eiji, generating anger from the ''[[Art of Fighting]]'' developers for what Iori did to their character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kofaniv.snk-corp.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=billy |title=Billy Kane|publisher=SNK|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kofaniv.snk-corp.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=eiji|title=Eiji Kisaragi|publisher=SNK|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref>  Iori is a [[berserker]] due to the Orochi demon blood within him. This version of the character, officially named \"Orochi Iori\", is hinted to have existed before his debut in ''[[The King of Fighters '97]]'' as one of the game's [[mid-boss]]es. This form of Iori was designed to easily overpower other characters.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=orochi-iori| title=Orochi Iori Official Profile| website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website| accessdate=March 24, 2008| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207201041/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=orochi-iori| archive-date=February 7, 2009| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> Series' flagship director Toyohisa Tanabe states that the staff were initially reluctant to add this version of Iori to the series' roster; they were worried about fans' reactions but did so to add more impact to the Orochi saga's climax. Tanabe was particularly pleased to see surprised reactions from female fans to this form during ''KOF '97''{{'}}s location testing. Another minor development of the character was his change of \"most valued possession/valued treasure\" information. A girlfriend was also listed in ''The King of Fighters '95'', ''The King of Fighters '99'', and ''The King of Fighters 2000''. Starting with ''The King of Fighters 2001'' and every entry after that, however, the space is listed as \"None\". The SNK staff commented that it is curious that he does not have a girlfriend anymore.<ref>{{Cite book | year=2005 | editor=Akihiko Ureshino | title=The King of Fighters Perfect Reader | pages=144 | language=Japanese | publisher=Nikkei Business Publications, Inc. | isbn= 4-8222-1711-6}}</ref>\n\n===Development===\n[[File:IoriYagamiXIV.png|thumb|Iori's redesign for ''The King of Fighters XIV'' by Ogura.]]\nDuring the early development stages of ''[[The King of Fighters '99]]'', SNK planned to exclude Iori and Kyo from the game because the company wanted to focus the story on the new protagonist, [[K']]. They reversed this decision because of the characters' popularity.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=kyo-1| title=Kyo Kusanagi-1 Official Profile| website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website| accessdate=March 24, 2008| archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6c0SZaTay?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/character/index.php?num=kyo-1| archive-date=October 3, 2015| url-status=dead| df=mdy-all}}</ref> The repeated appearance of Iori, Kyo, and other SNK regular characters in the series is at the insistence of the marketers and main planners, making it a challenge to decide the story for each title.<ref>{{Cite book | year=2005 | editor=Akihiko Ureshino | title=The King of Fighters Perfect Reader | pages=136~139 | language=Japanese | publisher=Nikkei Business Publications, Inc. |isbn= 4-8222-1711-6}}</ref> Because of his popularity among fans, some of the series' main designers have said Iori is \"difficult to draw for\". Illustrator Shinkiro said he thought Iori was one of the series' wildest characters because of his hairstyle; similar sentiments were expressed by ''[[Last Blade]]'' illustrator Tonko.<ref name=kofanivmanhua/> ''[[KOF: Maximum Impact]]'' producer [[Falcoon]] stated that attempting to change an \"untouchable\" design such as Iori's put him under severe pressure. He stated that creating Iori's alternative design that appears in the ''Maximum Impact'' series almost felt \"unforgivable\" because he felt unsure of fans' reaction to the change.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.snkplaymore.jp/blog/falcoon/archives/2006/02/post_7.html| title=\u30a2\u30ca\u30b6\u30fc\u30b3\u30b9\u30c1\u30e5\u30fc\u30e0\u306e\u3053\u3068\u30fb\u30fb\u30fb\uff08\u4e00\u56de\u76ee\uff09| publisher=Falcoon official blog| accessdate=January 21, 2009| url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060501213857/http://www.snkplaymore.jp/blog/falcoon/archives/2006/02/post_7.html | archivedate=May 1, 2006| df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nFor the ''Maximum Impact'' spin-off games, Iori's characteristic hairstyle was changed dramatically. Throughout the series, his normal costume consists of a short jacket and [[bondage pants]]; without changing his design and adjusting only his coloring, a diverse number of image variations can be brought about.<ref>{{Cite book | date=June 17, 2006  |page=50|  title=The King of Fighters Maximum Impact Artbook| language=Japanese | publisher=SNK Playmore | isbn=978-4-7973-3543-9 }}</ref> During the making of ''The King of Fighters XIV'', Nobuyuki Kuroki wanted Iori, except the character's hair, to be redesigned. Character designer Eisuke Ogura created a new outfit for Iori and asked the modeler to focus on his masculinity and to pay close attention to the way the design of the character's eyes.<ref>{{Cite book | year= 2016 | title=The King of Fighters XIV artbook| page=45| language= | publisher=Atlus|isbn=}}</ref> This new design, alongside Kyo's, provoked controversy when it was revealed. ''KOF XIV'' director Yasuyuki Oda said the team wanted the characters to have new looks because the game is set in another story arc.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://xw.qq.com/games/20151017000037| script-title=zh:\u5c0f\u7530\u6cf0\u4e4b\uff1a\u5bf9\u62f3\u76879OL\u6ee1\u610f| publisher=QQ| accessdate=February 4, 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205001207/https://xw.qq.com/games/20151017000037| archive-date=February 5, 2018| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> \n\nIn an interview with Iori's [[Seiy\u016b|Japanese voice actor]], [[Kunihiko Yasui]] comments that he feels responsible as a voice actor for his performances as Iori, taking care to sound different in each installment as a means of developing and protecting his character's humanity.<ref>{{Cite book | date=September 20, 2005 | editor=Akihiko Ureshino | title=The King of Fighters Perfect Reader | pages=160 | language=Japanese | publisher=Nikkei Business Publications, Inc. | isbn=4-8222-1711-6}}</ref> Yasui was replaced by [[Takanori Hoshino]] starting in ''The King of Fighters XIV''; Hoshino said he was delighted to be the new voice actor of the character, thanking SNK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/shockhearts777/status/764027299977056256|publisher=Twitter|accessdate=September 22, 2018|date=August 12, 2016|title=\u516b\u795e\u5eb5\u306e\u58f0\u3092\u62c5\u5f53\u3055\u305b\u3066\u3044\u305f\u3060\u3051\u308b\u4e8b\u306b\u306a\u308a\u307e\u3057\u305f\uff01\u69d8\u3005\u306a\u60f3\u3044\u306f\u3042\u308b\u304b\u3068\u601d\u3044\u307e\u3059\u304c\u3001\u8aa0\u5fc3\u8aa0\u610f\u5411\u304d\u5408\u3044\u305f\u3044\u3068\u601d\u3044\u307e\u3059\uff01\u5b9c\u3057\u304f\u304a\u9858\u3044\u81f4\u3057\u307e\u3059\uff01|language=Japanese}}</ref> Chisa Horii voices Iori's female incarnation in ''SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy''.<ref name=chisa/>\n\n===Fighting style===\nWhen fighting, Iori employs the \"Yagami style of ancient martial arts\" as well as an art labelled as \"Pure instinct\" which involves the usage of blue flames. His strongest technique is known as {{nihongo|Kin 1211 Shiki: Yaotome|\u7981\u5343\u5f10\u767e\u62fe\u58f1\u5f0f\u30fb\u516b\u7a1a\u5973||lit. \"Forbidden Style 1211: Eight Maidens\"}} In ''The King of Fighters XIII'', Iori's gameplay mechanics were modified to become a close-range fighter. Despite losing his flaming techniques, he was given brutal moves using his nails to emphasize his ferociousness. Iori's strongest technique is {{nihongo|\"Forbidden 1218 Shiki: Yatagarasu\"|\u7981\u5343\u5f10\u767e\u62fe\u516b\u5f0f\u30fb\u516b\u54ab\u70cf}}, a new move that focuses on violent combinations and serves as a reference to the character's ending from ''The King of Fighters '96'', in which he murders his teammates. Iori's 10th color scheme in the game matches that of his classic outfit. During development of the game, details were added to increase the similarities.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2010/06/post_17.html| script-title=ja:\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0\u7d39\u4ecb \u516b\u795e\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0| publisher=SNK Playmore| date=June 24, 2011| accessdate=August 9, 2011| language=Japanese| title={title}| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110709093131/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2010/06/post_17.html| archive-date=July 9, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> This version, featuring his classic techniques, was designed to avoid surpassing the current Iori so players could choose the fighting style they prefer in the game.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_45.html| script-title=ja:\u708e\u3092\u53d6\u308a\u623b\u3057\u305f\u5eb5\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066| publisher=SNK Playmore| date=October 6, 2011| accessdate=October 6, 2011| language=Japanese| title={title}| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007115734/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_45.html| archive-date=October 7, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> This was further emphasized in the console version of ''The King of Fighters XIII'', in which Iori had his moveset were adjusted for better balance by not using flaming techniques.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_47.html| script-title=ja:\u7b2c\uff12\u56de\uff1a\u65e2\u5b58\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u306e\u8abf\u6574\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066| publisher=SNK Playmore| date=October 20, 2011| accessdate=October 24, 2011| language=Japanese| title={title}| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111025075455/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_47.html| archive-date=October 25, 2011| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAs downloadable content for ''The King of Fighters XIII'', SNK added the original Iori Yagami who can wield flames for his fighting style. This version was meant to be innovative similar rather than make him look like his classic ''The King of Fighters '95'' persona. Despite being the same person, the playstyle of Iori's flames is highly different from the regular Iori whose attacks involve hand-to-hand combat. Nevertheless, he was balanaced by SNK in order to avoid making the character be overpowered when exploring his special moves. Some distinguishable moves were given to him in order to give the player multiple options of tactics. This Neo Max was created with the idea of impressing gamers so that they would be attracted to use this version of the character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://game.snk-corp.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/blog/archives/2011/10/post_45.html|title=\u708e\u3092\u53d6\u308a\u623b\u3057\u305f\u5eb5\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066|publisher=SNK|language=Japanese|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> In ''XIV'' The commands for Iori's moves were also affected; one of his strongest attacks, the {{nihongo|Ura 316 Shiki Saia|\u88cf316\u88cf\u53c2}}, would require high skill for regular players because SNK attempted to balance the characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.4gamer.net/games/317/G031749/20160613002/index_2.html|title=\u65b0\u751fSNK\u306e\u30e2\u30ce\u4f5c\u308a\u306f\u3053\u3053\u304b\u3089\u59cb\u307e\u308b\u3002\u300c\u9913\u72fcMOW2\u300d\u306e\u8a71\u984c\u3082\u98db\u3073\u51fa\u3057\u305f\uff0c\u300cTHE KING OF FIGHTERS XIV\u300d\u958b\u767a\u9663\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30fc|publisher=4Gamer|accessdate=October 31, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n==Appearances==\n\n===In video games===\n====In main ''The King of Fighters'' games====\nIori is a violent, sadistic person who suffers from trauma because of his clan's past. In ancient times, the Yagami clan was known as the Yasakani who, With the help of the Yata and Kusanagi clans, sealed the demon Orochi. As time passed, the Yasakani tired of living in the shadow of the Kusanagi and made a blood pact with Orochi that gave them greater powers but cursed them and their descendants forever. They renamed their clan the Yagami and set out to destroy the Kusanagi with their new powers.<ref name=clanquote2/><ref name=clanquote2>{{cite video game|quote='''Spirit represented by purple flame:''' All is from the Orochi blood! From our blood allegiance. With the Orochi clan!/'''Kyo:''' Our clan? Yagami? The Yasakani clan?/'''Spirit represented by purple flame:''' A 660 year old error... It can't be corrected!|title=The King of Fighters '97 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 28, 1997 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Chizuru:''' The crimson flame of Yagami came from a part of your long-repressed true essence./'''Iori:''' Nonsense! I don't by [sic] that Freudian garbage!/'''Chizuru:''' The blue flames you control come from the Orochi power flowing within you. |title=The King of Fighters '96 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 30, 1996 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> The curse also causes each heir to die young and each mother to die in childbirth. Ior becomes obsessed with killing his heir Kyo, disregarding their clans' past. This sometimes results in Iori helping Kyo to defeat his enemies and to finish their battles.<ref name=enemy/> To find Kyo, Iori sometimes enters the King of Fighters tournaments and uses his teammates as tools to reach him.<ref name=tool/>\n\nIori Yagami first appeared in ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'', in which he enters an annual tournament as the leader of the Rival Team with Billy Kane and [[Eiji Kisaragi]]. Iori learns that the heir of the Kusanagi clan, [[Kyo Kusanagi|Kyo]], is expected to be there.<ref name=tool>{{cite web|title=Rival Team Official Story ~ KOF 95 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof95_story/index.php?num=rival |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509140115/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof95_story/index.php?num=rival|archivedate=May 9, 2016 }}</ref> After the team fails to defeat Kyo's team, Iori betrays his teammates.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Iori:''' What a fool! Such power can only by mine! Well, shall we wrap this up?/'''Eiji:''' What?/'''Billy:''' Hey! You're... you're Geese!/'''Iori:''' Just wait, Kyo. You're next for extermination. You and all Kusanagis! Yah, hah, hah|title=The King of Fighters '95 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 25, 1995 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> In the [[The King of Fighters '96|next video game]], Iori teams up with two women, [[Vice (King of Fighters)|Vice and Mature]], servants of the Orochi demon.<ref>{{cite web|title=The King of Fighters '98 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof98 |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=January 16, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fhEsGSDp?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof98 |archivedate=March 31, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=KOF 2002 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof2002 |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=January 29, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fhEwAHar?url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/history.php?num=kof2002 |archivedate=March 31, 2009 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/neowave/|title=The King of Fighters Neowave official website|publisher=[[SNK Playmore]]|accessdate=August 8, 2008|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5ff9Ydd3i?url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/neowave/character/index.html|archive-date=March 30, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> During the '96 competition, Iori meets [[Chizuru Kagura]], the heir of the Yata clan who wants to gather Kyo and Iori on her team to seal Orochi. They defeat the Orochi follower [[Goenitz]] but neither Iori nor Kyo agree with the idea.<ref name=curse>{{cite video game|quote='''Mature:''' Are you shaking?/'''Vice:''' Yeah, he ain't normal. But, that guy... I mean... He's really tough./'''Iori:''' W, what? I can't see! Yaaah! Unnhhh! Gya... GWAAAAH!/'''Vice:''' Hey, Yagami, take it easy!/'''Mature:''' Oh, my God.../'''Iori:''' I, it's the... Riot of the Blood!/'''Vice:''' Gah. You mean there's nothing we can do?/'''Mature:''' Ooowaaaaah! Ya, Yagami!/'''Iori:''' GOOOWAAAAH!|title=The King of Fighters '96 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 30, 1996 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> When Iori leaves with his teammates, he cannot control his surge of Orochi power, resulting in their deaths.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Goenitz:''' I guess I understimated you. I never thought... but this isn't the end for you./'''Iori:''' Hah! \"ONE-FOR-THE-ROAD\" BLAST!/'''Goenitz:''' AHHHHH!/'''Kyo:''' Hah! Eat this, pal! SERPENT WAVE!/'''Goenitz:'''GYAAAH! Why? Why is there no wind? GYAAAAAH!|title=The King of Fighters '96 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 30, 1996 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref> Iori continues to suffer from multiple outbreaks; during ''[[The King of Fighters '97]]'' he attacks other team members and appears as a [[Boss (video games)|sub-boss character]] in the game, depending on the characters the player uses.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iori Team Official Story ~ KOF 97 |url=http://kof.confusticated.com/frames.html |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705051310/http://kof.confusticated.com/frames.html |archivedate=July 5, 2008 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> He later joins Chizuru and Kyo to confront and seal Orochi.<ref name=enemy>{{cite video game|quote='''Iori:''' Aaaaah!! /'''Orochi:''' Kill Kusanagi and Yata! Break the Shingi troica! Fight, my Orochi son! Listen, Yagami! /'''Iori:'''Ahhhhhhh!!!/'''Orochi:''' Ah?!|title=The King of Fighters '97 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 28, 1997 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Kyo:''' Finish it, Kagura! Can you do it? /'''Chizuru:''' As a mirror keeper... I must do it! /'''Orochi:''' Fools! A waste of time! If I release my remaining power.../'''Iori:''' Waahh!/'''Chizuru:''' His power... too strong! Kusanagi! Quickly... /'''Kyo:''' Heeaahhh! Woooohh!|title=The King of Fighters '97 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 28, 1997 |platform=Neo Geo }}</ref>\n\nIn most version of ''[[The King of Fighters '99]]'' Iori is a secret character that can be faced as a bonus fight at the end of the game if the player scores enough points. In the story, Iori discovers the creation of Kyo clones and enters the annual tournament, where he finds those responsible, an organization named [[List of The King of Fighters characters#The NESTS cartel|NESTS]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Iori Team Official Story ~ KOF 99 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof99_story/index.php?num=yagami |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080528113043/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof99_story/index.php?num=yagami |archive-date=May 28, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Iori follows the battles in secret and fights against the NESTS' agents to continue his fight against Kyo.<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters 2000 |developer=SNK |publisher=SNK |date=July 26, 2000 |platform=Neo Geo |quote='''Kyo:''' Consider that payback for the way you used us!/'''Zero:''' \"'Used' you?  The strength of your Mushiki move... was used to power the Zero Cannon. It's the ultimate compliment!/'''Kyo:''' In your sick fantasies! You conceited freak!.../'''Zero:''' Chill out. I'll soon be dead. Instead of me, think... of the one who awaits you.../'''Kyo:'''...Someone awaits me?/'''Iori:''' Enough prattle..../'''Kyo:''' Don't you think?  Here's \"someone\"! Let's rumble, dude!}}</ref> An assistant version of his character named Striker also appears for Iori in ''[[The King of Fighters 2000]]'' wearing an outfit based on illustrations in artbooks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof2000/kof2000_top.html |title=Another Striker |publisher=[[SNK Playmore]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=March 17, 2009 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5fldpiXfv?url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof2000/kof2000_top.html |archivedate=April 3, 2009 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In ''[[The King of Fighters 2001]]'', an agent named [[Seth (King of Fighters)|Seth]] invites Iori to join his team for the next ''King of Fighters'' tournament, assuming he would get his shot against Kyo.<ref>{{cite web |title=Iori Team Official Story ~ KOF 2002 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2001_story/index.php?num=iori |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080528175725/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2001_story/index.php?num=iori |archive-date=May 28, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> While his regular form appears in ''KOF 2002'', his Orochi form is also featured in the PlayStation 2 port of the game and the remake of ''KOF '98''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/xbox/action/thekingoffighters2002/hints.html?tag=tabs;cheats|title=The King of Fighters 2002 Hints & Cheats|website=[[GameSpot]] |accessdate=February 26, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/action/the-king-of-fighters-98-ultimate-match/cheats.html?tag=tabs%253Bcheats|title=The King of Fighters '98 Ultimate Match Hints & Cheats|website=[[GameSpot]]|accessdate=August 5, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110812003410/http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/action/the-king-of-fighters-98-ultimate-match/cheats.html?tag=tabs%253Bcheats|archive-date=August 12, 2011|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In ''[[The King of Fighters 2003]]'', Chizuru appears to both Kyo and Iori, asking them to form a team and investigate suspicious activities concerning the Orochi seal.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sacred Team Official Story ~ KOF 2003 |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2003_story/index.php?num=3sacred |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 10, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080528193022/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/history/kof2003_story/index.php?num=3sacred |archive-date=May 28, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> During the investigation, the team is ambushed by the fighter [[Ash Crimson]], who plans to get the power from the descendants of the clans who sealed Orochi and steals the ones from Chizuru.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Ash:''' Where... is... it... now?/'''Chizuru:''' Ah.. ah.../'''Ash:''' Oh, oh, oh, here we are. With this my objective has come to fruition.|title=The King of Fighters 2003 |developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=SNK Playmore |date=December 12, 2003 |platform=PlayStation 2 }}</ref>\n\nIn the [[The King of Fighters XI|following video game]], Iori and Kyo form a team with Kyo's student Shingo Yabuki to fill Chizuru's spot to stop Ash.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kyo & Iori Team Official Story in KOF XI |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/history/kofxi_story/index.php?num=kyo_iori |website=King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website |accessdate=August 3, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081218130024/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/history/kofxi_story/index.php?num=kyo_iori |archive-date=December 18, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> At the end of the tournament, the strengthening presence of Orochi causes Iori to enter the Riot of Blood state, in which he attacks his comrades. Ash appears afterward and defeats Iori, stealing his powers.<ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Iori:''' Oooh... I'll kill you... Kyo.../'''Shingo:''' Damn, damn, my body... Must save... Gagh, Mr. K-Kusanagi... He's going to be killed.../'''Ash:''' Well, well, what's going on here? And without any protection, either?/'''Shingo:''' Uh, Ash... Yagami just went crazy all of a sudden./'''Ash:''' Well, well, well. You're in a tough spot, aren't you?/'''Shingo:''' W-watch out. H-he's not like he usually is./'''Iori:''' K... Kill.../'''Ash:''' (So that's the look... Now I see. If he's gotten this far, it can only mean...) Heh, heh. Talk about pressure!/'''Iori:''' Ga, ga, ga, gaaaaah... |title=The King of Fighters XI |developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=SNK Playmore |date=November 13, 2007 |platform=PlayStation 2 }}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|quote='''Ash:''' Holy moley, you're scary as ever. But that's not how it'll work out. And why? It's because I... am not the same old Ash./'''Elizabeth:''' That color! Iori Yagami's? No, it can't be, can it? The Orochi?!|title=The King of Fighters XI |developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=Igniton Entertainment |date=November 13, 2007 |platform=PlayStation 2 }}</ref> Iori is a playable character in ''[[The King of Fighters XII]]'', in which he is featured with a different outfit and a new moveset that does not use purple flames. He does not have a team.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xii/character/index.html| title=\u300e\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30baXII\u300f\u7a3c\u52d5\u6642\u671f\u304c\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01| publisher=Official The King of Fighters XII Homepage| accessdate=September 17, 2008| language=Japanese| archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5ff9Pj4uz?url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xii/character/index.html| archive-date=March 30, 2009| url-status=live| df=mdy-all}}</ref> Iori's appearance in ''[[The King of Fighters XIII]]'' sees him teamed with Mature and Vice, his teammates from the 1996 tournament who return as spirits.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/character/index.html | title=CHARACTER THE KING OF FIGHTERS XIII | date=April 22, 2010 | accessdate=April 22, 2010 | publisher=SNK Playmore | language=Japanese | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100428035643/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/official/kof-xiii/character/index.html | archive-date=April 28, 2010 | url-status=live | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Following Ash's disappearance, Iori recovers his flames at the end and appears as downloadable content in this form.<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters XIII|developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=Atlus|year=2011|platform=PlayStation 4 |level=Team Yagami's ending}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2012-01-11/the-king-of-fighters-xiii-gets-two-new-dlc-characters/nests-style-kyo-and-mr-karate|title=The King of Fighters XIII Gets Two New DLC Characters: Nests Style Kyo and Mr. Karate|publisher=Anime News Network|date=January 11, 2012|accessdate=August 21, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925010311/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2012-01-11/the-king-of-fighters-xiii-gets-two-new-dlc-characters/nests-style-kyo-and-mr-karate|archive-date=September 25, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He returns in ''[[The King of Fighters XIV]]'', in which he tracks Orochi's weakened body in central Hungary after the tournament is over. He seals the weakened snake with the help of Kyo and Chizuru.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-09-16/on-with-the-show/.92999|title=The X Button On With the Show|publisher=Anime News Network|date=September 16, 2015|accessdate=September 16, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917175726/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-09-16/on-with-the-show/.92999|archive-date=September 17, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Iori wears a new costume in the game and his classic one appears as [[downloadable content]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.snk-corp.co.jp/us/games/kof-xiv/news/news06.php|title=DLC Costumes|publisher=SNK|accessdate=January 28, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180127071150/http://www.snk-corp.co.jp/us/games/kof-xiv/news/news06.php|archive-date=January 27, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters XIV |developer=SNK |publisher=Atlus|year=2016|platform=PlayStation 4 |level=Team Yagami's ending}}</ref>\n\n====Other games====\n[[File:MissXSNKHeroines.png|thumb|right|300px|The three looks of Miss X from ''SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy''.]]\n\nIn ''The King of Fighters: Kyo'', a [[role-playing video game]] set before the events of ''KOF '97'', Iori appears as Kyo's antagonist in his journey around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/consumer/psp.php | title=PSP\u5bb6\u5ead\u7528\u30bd\u30d5\u30c8\uff1aSNK\u30d7\u30ec\u30a4\u30e2\u30a2 \u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u60c5\u5831\u7dcf\u5408\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\u3000NEOGEO WORLD| website= SNK Playmore Official Homepage | accessdate=March 26, 2008 | language=Japanese |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071026051919/http://game.snkplaymore.co.jp/consumer/psp.php |archivedate = October 26, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba \u4eac |url=http://www.jp.playstation.com/ps3/psn/ac_title/0706-06.html?keepThis=true&TB_iframe=true&height=330&width=560 |website=Playstation.com |accessdate=March 26, 2008 |language=Japanese |title={title} |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081222103843/http://www.jp.playstation.com/ps3/psn/ac_title/0706-06.html?keepThis=true&TB_iframe=true&height=330&width=560 |archive-date=December 22, 2008 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Both ''[[King of Fighters R-1]]'' and ''[[King of Fighters R-2]]'' feature the regular Iori and his berserker form as playable characters; the latter game features him as a teamless character.<ref>{{cite video game|title=King of Fighters R-1|developer=SNK|publisher=SNK|date=1998 |platform=Neo Geo Pocket|level=Savior Team Ending}}</ref><ref>{{cite video game|title=King of Fighters R-2|developer=SNK|publisher=SNK|date=1998 |platform=Neo Geo Pocket|level=Edit Team Ending}}</ref> Iori appears in the spin-off video games [[The King of Fighters: Maximum Impact|''Maximum Impact'' series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snkplaymoreusa.com/game_kof2006.php|title=The King of Fighters: Maximum Impact 2 official website|publisher=[[SNK Playmore]]|accessdate=August 8, 2008 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080504022832/http://www.snkplaymoreusa.com/game_kof2006.php |archivedate = May 4, 2008}}</ref> In the North American editions of ''Maximum Impact'', Iori is voiced by Eric Summerer.<ref>{{cite video game|title=The King of Fighters 2006 |developer=SNK Playmore|publisher=SNK Playmore|year=2006 |platform=PlayStation 2|level=Credits}}</ref> Iori appears as a sub-boss in ''The King of Fighters Ex: Neo Blood'', which is set after his fight against Orochi. Although Iori enters the tournament to fight Kyo, [[Geese Howard]], the organizer of the tournament, tries but fails to make him awaken his Riot of the Blood to absorb his powers. In ''[[The King of Fighters EX2: Howling Blood]]'', Iori enters another tournament and is joined by two women who want to find a man controlled by the Orochi power.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atlus.com/kofex2/teams_yagami.html|title=The King of Fighters EX2: Howling Blood official website|publisher=[[Atlus]]|accessdate=January 16, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090107033125/http://www.atlus.com/kofex2/teams_yagami.html|archive-date=January 7, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The shooter game ''KOF: Sky Stage'' also features Iori as a boss, while ''Neo Geo Heroes: Ultimate Shooting'' makes him playable.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2009-11-04|author=Ciolek, Todd|title=The X Button Strange Days|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 4, 2009|accessdate=November 4, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091107045214/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2009-11-04|archive-date=November 7, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snk-corp.co.jp/official/neogeo_heroes/character/iori.html|title=Characters|publisher=SNK|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> He is also featured in ''KOF X Arena Masters'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nexon.co.jp/news/132611|title=\u3010\u30d7\u30ec\u30b9\u30ea\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u3011\u300eArena Masters\uff08\u30a2\u30ea\u30fc\u30ca\u30de\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba\uff09\u300f\u304c\u300eTHE KING OF FIGHTERS\u300f\u3068\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\uff01 \u4eac\u30fb\u30a2\u30c6\u30ca\u30fb\u5eb5\u304c\u30b3\u30e9\u30dc\u30d2\u30fc\u30ed\u30fc\u3068\u306a\u3063\u3066\u53c2\u6226\uff01|publisher=Nexon|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> ''Game of Dice''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kongbakpao.com/kof-98-characters-visiting-game-of-dice/|title=KOF '98 Characters Visiting Game of Dice!|publisher=Kongbakpao|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The King of Fighters All Star]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://altema.jp/kofallstar/charamatome/12|title=\u516b\u795e\u5eb5\u306e\u5168\u30b7\u30ea\u30fc\u30ba\u8a55\u4fa1\u3068\u30b9\u30ad\u30eb\u4e00\u89a7\n|publisher=Altima|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> and the Korean fighting game ''The King of Cyphers''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/1/165931.html|title=\u62f3\u7687 AR \u624b\u6a5f\u904a\u6232\u300a\u62f3\u7687\u5927\u86c7\u7bc7 Go\u300b\u5df2\u9054\u6700\u7d42\u958b\u767c\u968e\u6bb5 \u5c07\u5c55\u958b\u9ad4\u9a57\u8a66\u73a9\u6d3b\u52d5|work=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9|access-date=2018-07-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dreamcancel.com/2015/03/kyo-and-iori-show-up-in-new-korean-fighting-game-the-king-of-cyphers/|title=KYO AND IORI SHOW UP IN NEW KOREAN FIGHTING GAME \"THE KING OF CYPHERS\"|publisher=DreamCancel|accessdate=September 15, 2018|date=March 30, 2015}}</ref> SNK also released a [[pachinko]] based on the Orochi storyline.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://slot.snk-corp.co.jp/official/kof/index.html|title=The King of Fighters|publisher=SNK|accessdate=September 16, 2018}}</ref> as well as the [[otome game]] ''King of Fighters for Girls''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-06-13/snk-victor-entertainment-reveal-king-of-fighters-for-girls-smartphone-game/.147812|title=SNK, Victor Entertainment Reveal 'King of Fighters for Girls' Smartphone Game|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=June 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIori also appears in SNK's hand-held game, ''[[SNK Gals' Fighters]]'', as a comical interpretation called {{nihongo|Miss X|\u30df\u30b9 X|Misu Ekkusu}}. The character insists he is a female in order to participate in the game's ''Queen of Fighters'' tournament, though several female fighters easily see through his disguise.<ref>{{cite video game|title=SNK Gals' Fighters |developer=Yumekobo |publisher=SNK of America |date=February 19, 2000 |platform=Neo Geo Pocket Color|quote='''Yuki:''' It's wish time! This Talisman will turn you into Ms. X forever.../'''Miss X:''' Argh! You're a sneaky tart!/'''Yuki:''' Tart? You asked for it! O, Talisman.../'''Miss X:''' Ah! Wait! I take it back! Curses...}}</ref> He is also present in ''[[The Rhythm of Fighters]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.androidcentral.com/rhythm-fighters-review|title=The Rhythm of Fighters review|website=AndroidCentral|accessdate=September 22, 2018|date=July 28, 2014}}</ref> Miss X reappears in the fighting game ''[[SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy]]'' as downloadable content, this time sharing both the original crossdresser and new true gender swapped form.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/10/25/missx-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-debut-will-occur-on-november-15-2018/|title=MissX SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy Debut Will Occur On November 15, 2018|accessdate=October 25, 2018|publisher=Siliconera}}</ref> In the story, Miss X fights against multiple female fighters (including his fellow gender-swapped fighters [[Terry Bogard]] and the guest fighter [[Skullomania]]) to stop the host Kukri and his ending involves an embarrassing nightmare in which he and Kyo become friendly rivals. Miss X's true identity, Iori also made a cameo on certain characters' endings in ''Heroines'', prior Miss X DLC debut.<ref>{{cite video game|title=SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy|developer=SNK Playmore |publisher=SNK|year=2018|platform=PlayStation 4 |stage=Miss X's ending}}</ref> In the crossover video games ''[[NeoGeo Battle Coliseum]]'' and ''[[SNK vs. Capcom]]'' series, Iori appears as a playable character; the latter includes his Riot of the Blood state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ignitionent.com/ngbc/main.htm |title=Neo Geo Battle Coliseum official website |publisher=[[SNK Playmore]] |accessdate=August 8, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061104041918/http://www.ignitionent.com/ngbc/main.htm |archivedate=November 4, 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capcom.co.jp/newproducts/consumer/cvss2/ |title=Capcom VS. SNK official website |publisher=[[Capcom]] |accessdate=August 8, 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080808101118/http://www.capcom.co.jp/newproducts/consumer/cvss2/ |archivedate=August 8, 2008 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> His character is also a boss character (along with Geese) in the Game Boy version from ''[[Real Bout Fatal Fury Special]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/gameboy/action/nettourealboutgarouds/hints.html?tag=tabs;cheats|title=Nettou Real Bout Garou Densetsu Special Hints & Cheats|website=[[GameSpot]]|accessdate=April 15, 2009}}</ref> He also appears in [[Square Enix]]'s fighting game ''[[Million Arthur: Arcana Blood]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-26/million-arthur-arcana-blood-arcade-game-gets-ps4-release-on-november-29/.135931|title=Million Arthur: Arcana Blood Arcade Game Gets PS4 Release on November 29|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=August 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826075718/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-08-26/million-arthur-arcana-blood-arcade-game-gets-ps4-release-on-november-29/.135931|archive-date=August 26, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He is also available in ''The King Figthers X Fatal Fury'' mobile phone game.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2013/04/28/king-of-fighters-x-fatal-fury-heats-up-at-snk-playmore/|title=King of Fighters X Fatal Fury Heats Up At SNK Playmore|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=September 11, 2018}}</ref> He is also present in the Chinese mobile phone game named ''KOF: WORLD'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kof.sdo.com:80/web1/about/about_03.asp|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110512094018/http://kof.sdo.com/web1/about/about_03.asp|title=About|publisher=KOF SDO|accessdate=September 5, 2018|archivedate=May 12, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> the [[visual novel]] ''Days of Memories'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://game.snk-corp.co.jp/official/dom/dom2/series1/|title=Days of Memories|publisher=SNK|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> ''Metal Slug Defense'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://store.steampowered.com/app/361470/METAL_SLUG_DEFENSE__KOF_Pack_Vol1/?l=tchinese|title=METAL SLUG DEFENSE - \"KOF Pack\" Vol.1|publisher=Steam|language=Japanese|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> ''Lords of Vermillion'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www30.atwiki.jp/lord_of_vermilion/pages/1009.html|title=\u30ed\u30fc\u30c9\u30aa\u30d6\u30f4\u30a1\u30fc\u30df\u30ea\u30aa\u30f3\u3010LORD of VERMILION\u3011|publisher=Atwiki|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref> and ''Lucent Heart''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lh.gamania.co.jp/landing/colabo/kof/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100620000101/http://lh.gamania.co.jp/landing/colabo/kof/|title=Update|publisher=Lucent Heart|accessdate=November 8, 2018|archivedate=June 20, 2010}}</ref> The character's original look is also being used in [[action role-playing]] ''[[Phantasy Star Online 2]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2019/02/22/kyo-iori-athena-mai-and-leona-join-phantasy-star-online-2-as-new-costumes/|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=February 22, 2019|title=Kyo, Iori, Athena, Mai, And Leona Join Phantasy Star Online 2 As New Costumes}}</ref>\n\nIori Yagami made his appearance as playable hero in ''War Song'', a mobile [[multiplayer online battle arena]] (MOBA) developed by Morefun Studio, a game studio owned by [[Tencent]]. Iori Yagami also made his appearance in another mobile MOBA game, ''Mobile Legends: Bang Bang'', as a skin for the hero Chou as a result of collaboration between Moonton and SNK.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://egg.network/news/king-fighters-and-mobile-legends-have-epic-collaboration|title=King of Fighters And Mobile Legends Have An EPIC Collaboration!|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.player.one/moonton-snk-king-fighters-mobile-legends-124909|title=Mobile Legends Adds King Of Fighters Skins|last=|first=|date=March 18, 2019|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Iori appears as one of the background characters on the King of Fighters Stadium stage in ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]''. In addition a costume based on him for the Mii Brawler appears as downloadable content.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/2019/11/06/iori-nakoruru-ryo-akira-and-jacky-bryant-join-super-smash-bros-ultimates-mii-costumes/|title=Iori, Nakoruru, Ryo, Akira, And Jacky Bryant Join Super Smash Bros. Ultimate\u2019s Mii Costumes|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===In other media===\n\nAside from the ''King of Fighters'' series, the character is featured in an [[audio drama]]<ref>{{cite AV media notes | author= SNK | year=1999| title=Iori Yagami Original Drama -Sun and Moon- ~ Prologue| publisher=Pony Canyon Inc. | id=PCCB-00380 }}</ref> and a character [[image album]].<ref>{{cite AV media notes | author= SNK | year=1999| title=SNK Character Sounds Collection Volume 11 ~ Iori Yagami| publisher=Pony Canyon Inc. | id=PCCB-00378 }}</ref> In the anime ''[[The King of Fighters: Another Day]]'', Iori searches for Ash to regain his powers.<ref>{{cite video game|title=KOF Maximum Impact 2 |developer=SNK Playmore|publisher=SNK Playmore|date=April 27, 2006 |platform=PlayStation 2|level=The King of Fighters: Another Day}}</ref> Iori appears in the spin-off [[manga]] story entitled ''The King of Fighters: Kyo'', which is based on his adventure prior to ''[[The King of Fighters '96]]''.<ref>{{cite book |last=Natsumoto|first=Masato |title=The King of Fighters Kyo, volume 1|year=1996 |publisher=Kodansha|isbn=978-4-06-319759-4 }}</ref> Ryo Takamisaki's manga ''The King of Fighters G'' shows an alternative retelling of ''KOF '96'' in which Iori faces Kyo and Athena Asamiya.<ref>{{cite book |last=Takamisaki |first=Ryo|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30baG|year=1997 |publisher=Shinsenga|isbn=978-4881993507|volume=1}}</ref> The character appears in a [[manhua]] adaptation of ''The King of Fighters: Zillion'' created by [[Andy Seto]] that retells Iori's story of his fight against Orochi until he attacks NESTS to destroy Kyo's clones. He also stars in other manhua for the games, starting with ''The King of Fighters 2001'' and ending with ''2003'' along with the ''Maximum Impact'' series.<ref name=kofanivmanhua>{{cite web |url=http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=6| title=Remembrances of KOF: An Interview with Eiji |publisher= King of Fighters 10th Anniversary Official Website | accessdate=July 28, 2008 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080418040418/http://kofaniv.snkplaymore.co.jp/english/comment/remember_kof.php?num=6 |archivedate = April 18, 2008}}</ref> In the manga ''The King of Fighters: A New Beginning'', Vice and Mature force the Orochi power to make Iori lose his mind during his battle with Kyo. The battle ends in a draw with Iori's team losing due the other fighters' rounds.<ref>{{cite book|title=The King of Fighters: A New Beginning|year=2018|volume=1|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|isbn=|author=Asuma, Ky\u014dtar\u014d|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The King of Fighters: A New Beginning|year=2019|volume=2|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|isbn=978-4757205970|author=Asuma, Ky\u014dtar\u014d|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nIori is played by [[Will Yun Lee]] in the film ''[[The King of Fighters (film)|The King of Fighters]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kotaku.com/5286754/king-of-fighters-movie-promotional-images |title=King of Fighters Movie Promotional Images |publisher=[[Kotaku]] |author=Ashcraft, Brian |date=July 11, 2009 |accessdate=August 16, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090815031856/http://kotaku.com/5286754/king-of-fighters-movie-promotional-images |archive-date=August 15, 2009 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In the CGI series ''[[The King of Fighters: Destiny]]'' Iori makes a brief appearance in the first season's finale, in which he tries to play music but starts going berserk.<ref>{{cite AV media|title=The King of Fighters: Destiny|episode=24 Destiny|work=iDRAGONS Creative Studio, SNK}}</ref> He is one of two protagonists alongside Kyo in online gag manga ''Part Time Stories: Kyo & Iori'' by [[Falcoon]]; the two title characters work together to promote SNK's merchandising.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.snk-onlineshop.com/parttimestories/|title=Part Time Stories: Kyo & Iori|publisher=SNK|language=Japanese|accessdate=February 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180204000245/https://www.snk-onlineshop.com/parttimestories/|archive-date=February 4, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> He is also featured in the manga ''The King of Fighters: A New Beginning''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/263400|title=\u683c\u95d8\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u300cKOF\u300d\u4eba\u6c17\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u7dcf\u51fa\u6f14\u306e\u30b3\u30df\u30ab\u30e9\u30a4\u30ba\u304c\u30de\u30ac\u30dd\u30b1\u3067\u59cb\u52d5|publisher=Natalie|language=Japanese|accessdate=January 13, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180114073634/https://natalie.mu/comic/news/263400|archive-date=January 14, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Iori is also present in novels based on the series.<ref>{{cite book|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba2000\u2015STRIKERS STRIKE BACK|year=2001|isbn=978-4757703483|publisher=Enterbrain |author=Ureshino, Akihiko|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=\u30b6\u30fb\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30fb\u30aa\u30d6\u30fb\u30d5\u30a1\u30a4\u30bf\u30fc\u30ba'99\u2015BEYOND THE\"K\"|year=1999|publisher=[[SNK]]|isbn=978-4757205970 |author=Ureshino, Aikhiko|trans-title=The King of Fighters '99 \uff5eBEYOND THE \"K\"|language=Japanese}}</ref> He is also set to be the protagonist of the light novel series ''Iori Yagami's Isekai Mu'sou'' by Nobuhiko Tenkawa which depicts him in an alternate universe fighting goblins.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321903000741/|title=THE KING OF FANTASY \u516b\u795e\u5eb5\u306e\u7570\u4e16\u754c\u7121\u53cc \u6708\u3092\u898b\u308b\u305f\u3073\u601d\u3044\u51fa\u305b\uff01|work=Kadokawa Shoten|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n\nThe character Iori Yagami was mostly well received by several video game publications and other media. [[IGN]]'s A. E. Sparrow considered him one of the most useful of the games' characters and one of the best characters for \"veteran players\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/445/445739p1.html|title=King of Fighters 2000/2001 Review|publisher=[[IGN]]|author=Sparrow, A. E.|date=December 11, 2003|accessdate=August 8, 2008|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6c0lpBsAW?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2003/12/11/king-of-fighters-20002001|archive-date=October 3, 2015|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>  He is ranked in the top-ten fighting games from [[GameTrailers]] and has been called one of the series' innovative characters from his introduction in ''[[The King of Fighters '95]]'' and during his development in the following games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gametrailers.com/player/47398.html|title=Top 10 Fighting Games|date=April 6, 2009|publisher=[[GameTrailers]]|accessdate=April 6, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408070007/http://www.gametrailers.com/player/47398.html|archive-date=April 8, 2009|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Some commentators found his recurring interactions with Kyo Kusanagi during fights to be appealing, adding depth to the games, despite English gamers not being able to understand them, and the lack of a storyline in some.<ref>{{Cite web|accessdate=August 17, 2011|url=https://www.wired.com/gamelife/2010/11/king-of-fighters-2002-review/|title=Review: King of Fighters 2002 Ultimate Match Delivers Knockout Action|author=Feit, Daniel|website=Wired.com|date=November 10, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101115012227/http://www.wired.com/gamelife/2010/11/king-of-fighters-2002-review/|archive-date=November 15, 2010|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nKevin S. from [[GameRevolution]] liked the interactions between Kyo and Iori in ''The King of Fighters XIV'' because it was one of the most famous parts from the series. The addition of a unique theme song to Iori's and Kyo's rival fight was also praised.<ref>{{Cite web |url= http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/the-king-of-fighters-xiv|title=The King of Fighters XIV Review|author=S., Kevin |publisher=[[GameRevolution]] |date=August 23, 2016 |archiveurl= https://archive.is/20160823182901/http://www.gamerevolution.com/review/the-king-of-fighters-xiv |archivedate= August 23, 2016 |accessdate= April 13, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://royalflushmagazine.com/gaming/review-kof-xiv/#.W6buzHtKiUk|title=Review: King of Fighters XIV (KOF XIV)|publisher=RoyalFlush Magazine|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> Meristation compared Kyo's and Iori's antagonistic rivalry to that of [[Goku]] and [[Vegeta]] from the ''[[Dragon Ball]]'' manga by [[Akira Toriyama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meristation.com.mx/the-king-of-fighters-xiv-impresiones-e3/avance-juego/2132969|title=The King of Fighters XIV, Impresiones E3|website=Meristation|accessdate=September 15, 2018}}</ref> ''The Daily Star'' noted Kyo's and Iori's popularity comes from the way Kyo and Iori start facing each other as enemies but still become allies for other games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/shout/overclock/king-fighters-legacy-1376431|title=King of Fighters XIV|date=March 16, 2017|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref> ThunderBoltGames stated that Iori stands out within the plot because of his rivalry with Kyo and because he is cursed with Orochi's power, which makes his heroic traits questionable yet well-written despite the series being from the fighting game genre.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thunderboltgames.com/review/the-king-of-fighters-collection-the-orochi-saga-2|title=The King of Fighters Collection: The Orochi Saga|date=December 6, 2008|publisher=ThunderBoltGames|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref> The formation of the Three Sacred Treasures Team in ''The King of Fighters '96'' had a major impact with fans because it was appealing because of the Orochi saga and because of its incorporation of Japanese mythology.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atomix.vg/feature-the-king-of-fighters-96-retro-review/|title=FEATURE \u2013 THE KING OF FIGHTERS 96 (RETRO REVIEW)|publisher=Atomix|accessdate=November 1, 2018|language=Spanish|date=August 26, 2016}}</ref> 4thletter enjoyed the ''KOF '97'' of Kyo, Kagura and Iori, stating \"this [is how you write a climax to a four-year-long story]\" at the ending of the Orochi story arc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://4thletter.net/2013/07/the-top-200-fighting-game-endings-part-ten/|title=The Top 200 Fighting Game Endings: Part Ten|publisher=4thletter|accessdate=April 19, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125062206/http://4thletter.net/2013/07/the-top-200-fighting-game-endings-part-ten/|archivedate=January 25, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Lucke M. Albiges from [[Eurogamer]] praised Iori as having one of the most unpredictable appearances in the series, and considered him a veteran character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=79794|title=King Of Fighters XI Review|publisher=[[Eurogamer]]|author=Albiges, Lucke M.|date=July 14, 2007|accessdate=August 15, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081204234108/http://www.eurogamer.net/article.php?article_id=79794|archive-date=December 4, 2008|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAcross the franchise, Iori has been given new looks and techniques which have also resulted in different kind of responses. IGN's Jeremy Dunham praised Iori's appearance in ''[[KOF: Maximum Impact]]'' as one of the best designs from the game. However, Dunham complained about his lack of bloody scenes considering his actions in previous 2D games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ps2.ign.com/articles/554/554861p1.html|title=King of Fighters: Maximum Impact Review|publisher=[[IGN]]|author=Dunham, Jeremy|date=October 14, 2004|accessdate=August 8, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081013100343/http://ps2.ign.com/articles/554/554861p1.html|archive-date=October 13, 2008|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The character's new design from ''[[The King of Fighters XII]]'' has been well received by [[GameSpot]] writer Andrew Park who found such moves interesting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1up.com/do/previewPage?cId=3174300&p=37|accessdate=May 10, 2016|author=Park, Andrew|date=July 31, 2009|website=[[GameSpot]]|title=The King of Fighters XII is the latest chapter in 15 years of fighting game history. It's also a disappointment.|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hSR9wWJB?url=http://www.1up.com/reviews/king-fighters-12-review|archivedate=May 12, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On the other hand, [[1UP.com]] writer Richard Li; Li complained about the lack of Iori's signature moves such as his fireballs, and while some of them remained, Li noted that they now require a different input from the ones they normally require.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.1up.com/do/previewPage?cId=3174300&p=37 |accessdate=May 25, 2009 |author=Li, Richard |date=May 20, 2009 |publisher=[[1UP.com]] |title=1UP.com: The King of Fighters XII (PS3) |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hSR9wWJB?url=http://www.1up.com/reviews/king-fighters-12-review |archivedate=May 12, 2016 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> The Orochi form from Iori was listed as the sixth best altered video game character alongside Leona's based on the impact both have on the storyline by [[Den of Geek]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/fighting-games/265246/the-20-best-altered-fighting-game-characters|title=The 20 Best Altered Fighting Game Characters|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=June 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706031040/http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/fighting-games/265246/the-20-best-altered-fighting-game-characters|archive-date=July 6, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Den of Geek same site also listed him as the fourth best ''King of Fighters'' characters based on his moves, rivalry with Kyo as well as apparent character arc based on how he retakes his lost powers in ''KOF XIII'' and used them in ''KOF XIV'' to once again seal Orochi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/king-of-fighters/258397/king-of-fighters-ranking-all-the-characters/page/0/5|title=King of Fighters: Ranking All the Characters|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=July 31, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731191855/http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/king-of-fighters/258397/king-of-fighters-ranking-all-the-characters/page/0/5|archive-date=July 31, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The writer noted that while Iori started as \"anti-hero\" due to his tendency to beat up his own teammates in his first two games, he would join forces Kyo for a greater good in upcoming titles which changed the way he was seen. However, the fact that Iori is defeated by Ash in ''KOF XI'' was noted to be the opposite due to how much it affected him to the point of creating a new fighting style that does not involve flames.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/games/king-of-fighters/255602/king-of-fighters-xiv-team-yagami-trailer|title=King of Fighters XIV: Team Yagami Trailer|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=October 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\nTodd Ciolek from [[Anime News Network]] found Iori's appearance in ''KOF XIV'' dated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-12-10/expert-ease/.96324|title=The X Button Expert Ease|author=Ciolek, Todd|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 12, 2015|accessdate=April 14, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170623202947/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/the-x-button/2015-12-10/expert-ease/.96324|archivedate=June 23, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Meanwhile, Iori's return to his classic techniques in ''KOF XIV'' mainly using flames were celebrated by ''[[Hobby Consolas]]'' because of their popularity with fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hobbyconsolas.com/reviews/king-fighters-xiv-analisis-65028|title=The King Of Fighters XIV - An\u00e1lisis|publisher=Hobby Consolas|accessdate=February 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180205040743/https://www.hobbyconsolas.com/reviews/king-fighters-xiv-analisis-65028|archive-date=February 5, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all|date=August 22, 2016}}</ref> Atinux agreed, calling the character \"sadistic\" because of the violence of his attacks, most notably seen in his strongest moves that reference his enhanced Orochi form from previous games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atomix.vg/el-buen-iori-loco-y-su-equipo-se-presentan-en-the-king-of-fighters-xiv/|title=EL BUEN IORI (LOCO) Y SU EQUIPO SE PRESENTAN EN THE KING OF FIGHTERS XIV|publisher=Atomix|accessdate=October 30, 2018|date=May 19, 2016}}</ref> Shoryuken said that while Iori and Vice showed appealing skills in their ''KOF XIV'' trailer, they were overshadowed by Mature's techniques.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://shoryuken.com/2016/05/18/team-yagami-mature-revealed-alongside-iori-and-vice-in-latest-king-of-fighters-xiv-trailer/|title=Team Yagami: Mature Revealed Alongside Iori and Vice in Latest King of Fighters XIV Trailer|publisher=Shoryuken|access-date=September 22, 2018|date=May 18, 2016}}</ref>\n\nJournalists have also commented on Iori's appearances outside the ''KOF'' games. For the release of the tag game ''[[NeoGeo Battle Coliseum]]'', IGN suggested using Kyo and Iori as partners due to the moves they could perform together.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2008/01/04/neogeo-battle-coliseum-review-2|title=NeoGeo Battle Coliseum review|publisher=IGN|accessdate=September 15, 2018}}</ref> Iori's crossdressing persona Miss X has been popular; SNK stated they received multiple requests to add him into the crossover game ''[[SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy]]'', an upcoming fighting game focused on female characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2018/03/interview-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-yasuyuki-oda-kaito-soranaka-nis-america-staff|title=Interview: SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy's Yasuyuki Oda, Kaito Soranaka, and NIS America staff|publisher=Gematsu|accessdate=March 5, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180306082856/https://gematsu.com/2018/03/interview-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-yasuyuki-oda-kaito-soranaka-nis-america-staff|archive-date=March 6, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> [[Destructoid]] stated he was shocked by Miss X's debut in ''SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy'' because of Iori's obvious secret identity and because she has different incarnations with a different gender and outfit.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/miss-x-sizzles-in-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-528588.phtml|title=Miss X sizzles in SNK Heroines: Tag Team Frenzy|publisher=Destructoid|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref> Atomix shared similar feelings but refrained from revealing the character's true identity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://atomix.vg/la-tercera-peleadora-dlc-de-snk-heroines-tag-team-frenzy-es-iori-yagami/|title=LA TERCERA PELEADORA DLC DE SNK HEROINES: TAG TEAM FRENZY ES\u2026 \u00a1IORI YAGAMI!|publisher=Atomix|accessdate=October 30, 2018|date=October 25, 2018}}</ref> Universo Nintendo originally thought the DLC character would be an alternative version of Ash Crimson and was surprised by the revelation. The website said Miss X's second form is possibly the most humiliating version because the character is wearing a t-shirt of his rival Kyo. Nevertheless, the character's movements were thought to be similar to those of the original Iori and thus long-time gamers would easily play as Miss X.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://universo-nintendo.com.mx/2018/10/25/iori-yagami-snk-heroines-para-nintendo-switch/|title=Iori Yagami\u2026 Perd\u00f3n, Miss X Llegar\u00e1 A SNK Heroines Para Nintendo Switch|publisher=Universo Nintendo|accessdate=October 30, 2018|date=October 26, 2018}}</ref> Den of Geek found the comic ''SVC Chaos'' ridiculous because as Iori commits suicide to follow the deceased Kyo to the Underworld.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denofgeek.com/us/books-comics/street-fighter/235222/the-strange-history-of-street-fighter-comics|title=The Strange History of Street Fighter Comics|publisher=Den of Geek|accessdate=September 29, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Popularity===\nIori has been very popular with video gamers. In ''Gamest'''s 1996 Heroes Collection, Iori was ranked second in the poll Best Character from 1996.<ref>{{Cite book | year=1996 | editor=Gamest | title=Gamest Game Hero Collection 1996;| pages=2 | language=Japanese | publisher=Shinseisha }}</ref> In an issue from 1997, Iori was voted as the staff's favorite character, claiming first place over fifty other characters.<ref>{{Cite book | year=1997 | editor=Gamest | title=Gamest Game Hero Collection 1997; issue 208 | pages=1 | language=Japanese | publisher=Shinseisha }}</ref> He received the same rank on Neo Geo Freak's website with 3,792 votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neogeofreak.co.jp/ninki01htm.htm|title=Character polls|publisher=Official Neo Geo Freak website (archived version)|accessdate=January 26, 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000619213519/http://www.neogeofreak.co.jp/ninki01htm.htm |archivedate=June 19, 2000}}</ref> In a 2005 poll conducted by SNK-Playmore USA, he was voted the fans' eighth-favorite character with 145 votes.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://blog.ureshino.cn/?eid=19860#sequel | script-title=ja:\u30a6\u30ec\u30e6\u30b5\u65e5\u8a1803 | website=Akihiko Ureshino official web site | accessdate=September 16, 2008 | language=Japanese | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219051912/http://blog.ureshino.cn/?eid=19860#sequel | archivedate=February 19, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Merchandising based on Iori, including figurines, key-chains and puzzles, has been released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B0009PLEHO|title=Capcom vs SNK2 - Action Figures Series 1: Iori|language=Japanese|accessdate=August 17, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000V98GBK|title=Capcom vs Snk : King of Fighters Iori 3D 2\"-3\" Action Figure Key Chain|accessdate=August 17, 2008}}</ref> Two scale figures based on Iori's original form and his ''XIV'' look have also been released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2018/08/16/the-king-of-fighters-gantaku-scale-figures-shown-off-at-taipeis-2018-comic-exhibition/|title=The King Of Fighters Gantaku Scale Figures Shown Off At Taipei's 2018 Comic Exhibition|publisher=Siliconera|accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref>  A replica of his ''KOF XIV'' coat was produced for merchandising.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.celebsmoviejackets.com/iori-yagami-kof-xiv-coat|title=King of Fighters XIV Iori Yagami Coat|publisher=Celebsmoviejackets|accessdate=October 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn the book ''Gaming Cultures and Place in Asia-Pacific'', Iori was regarded as one of the most popular video game characters in Hong Kong from the mid 1990s onward alongside Kyo, Mai and others, to the point of overshadowing the ''Street Fighter'' characters, which were also well-known.<ref>{{cite book|title=Gaming Cultures and Place in Asia-Pacific|isbn=978-0415996273|author1=Hjorth, Larissa |author2=Chan, Dean |publisher=Routledge|year=2009|page=87|chapter=Consuming and Localizing Japanese Combat Games in Hong Kong}}</ref> The developers of ''KOF'' noted that Kyo and Iori were very popular in Korea, which led to their immediate inclusion is ''The King of Fighters 2001'' which was the first game in the series that was not developed by the original company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmcafe.com/news/news03-8-01.htm|title=KOF2001 \"Dream Match Revival\"(tentative title) to be released- |publisher=MMCafe|accessdate=September 16, 2018}}</ref> In 2018, Iori was voted as the seventh-most-popular Neo Geo character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.famitsu.com/news/201807/05160468.html|title=NEOGEO mini\uff08\u30cd\u30aa\u30b8\u30aa\u30df\u30cb\uff09\u767a\u58f2\u8a18\u5ff5\u3000\u597d\u304d\u306a\u30ad\u30e3\u30e9\u30af\u30bf\u30fc\u4eba\u6c17\u6295\u7968\uff06NEOGEO mini\u5165\u3063\u3066\u307b\u3057\u304b\u3063\u305f\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u306e\u30a2\u30f3\u30b1\u30fc\u30c8\u7d50\u679c\u3092\u4e2d\u9593\u767a\u8868\uff01\u30001\u4f4d\u306f\u30b3\u30a4\u30c4\u3067\"\u30aa\u30fc\u30b1\u30fc\uff01\"|publisher=Famitsu|language=Japanese|accessdate=July 29, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705173649/https://www.famitsu.com/news/201807/05160468.html|archive-date=July 5, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nTo choose the cover for the Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3 ports of ''KOF XII'', [[Ignition Entertainment]] started a survey on May 4, 2009, in which users of their forum could vote for one of two covers they wanted to see in the game. While both covers feature multiple characters, one uses Kyo in the center and the other Iori.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=635|title=Rock the Box: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII Xbox 360 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170810172051/http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=635|archivedate=August 10, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=636|title=Rock the Box: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII PlayStation 3 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-04|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5gWwMf78I?url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=636|archivedate=May 4, 2009|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> When the two surveys ended, Ignition started two new ones that asked people to vote between the previous winners and the Japanese covers from the game for both consoles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=727|title=Rock the Box Round 2: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII Xbox 360 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-20|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5gw0fxsWy?url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=727|archivedate=May 21, 2009|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=726|title=Rock the Box Round 2: Vote for your favorite King of Fighters XII PS3 box art!|publisher=[[Ignition Entertainment]]|accessdate=2009-05-20|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5gw0iCerX?url=http://forums.ignitionusa.net/showthread.php?t=726|archivedate=May 21, 2009|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}</ref> In late 2018, Iori and other SNK characters appeared as part of collaborations with other companies in [[Harajuku]], Japan, involving new merchandising. Iori's image was made by Falcoon.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://prtimes.jp/main/html/rd/p/000000179.000028651.html|title=11\u670823\u65e5\uff08\u91d1\u30fb\u795d\uff09\u304b\u3089\u30ad\u30c7\u30a4\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u539f\u5bbf\u5e97\u306b\u3066\u300eSNK\u00d7\u30ad\u30c7\u30a4\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\u539f\u5bbf\uff5eKawaii Holiday\u266a\uff5e\u300f\u3092\u958b\u50ac\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01|publisher=Pr Times|language=Japanese|accessdate=November 14, 2018}}</ref> Game designer [[Masahiro Sakurai]] was amazed when first seeing Iori in ''The King of Fighters '95'' due to his attitude and moves which made him praise the designers.<ref name=\"smash\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yK3VltKv3JI&t=2405s|title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate \u2013 Mr. Sakurai Presents \"Terry Bogard\"|publisher=Youtube|work=Nintendo|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n{{King of Fighters games}}\n\n[[Category:Action film characters]]\n[[Category:Fictional Japanese people in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional rock musicians]]\n[[Category:Male characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Musician characters in video games]]\n[[Category:SNK antagonists]]\n[[Category:SNK protagonists]]\n[[Category:The King of Fighters characters]]\n[[Category:Video game bosses]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in comics]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in film]]\n[[Category:Video game characters introduced in 1995]]\n[[Category:Video game characters with fire or heat abilities]]\n[[Category:Video game guest characters]]\n[[Category:Video game secret characters]]\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed cite error", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iori_Yagami"}
{"title_page": "Devin Cuddy", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian singer-songwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name            = Devin Cuddy\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| image_size      = \n| background      = solo_singer\n| birth_name      = Devin Cuddy\n| origin          = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| instrument      = Guitar, piano, vocals\n| genre           = [[Country music|Country]], Rock\n| occupation      = Musician, songwriter\n| years_active    = 2012&ndash;present\n| label           = Cameron House Records\n| associated_acts = [[Blue Rodeo]], The Jim Cuddy Band\n| website         = {{URL|devincuddy.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Devin Cuddy''' (born 1987) is a Canadian singer-songwriter who fronts the Devin Cuddy Band.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nHis father, [[Jim Cuddy|Jim]], is a founding member of the well-known Canadian band [[Blue Rodeo]].  His mother, Rena Polley, is an actress.<ref name=Star>{{Cite news|last=Quill |first=Greg |title=Jim Cuddy on the road again |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/article/305778 |newspaper=Toronto Star |date=23 February 2008 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5nT9ZGw8E?url=http://www.thestar.com/printarticle/305778 |archivedate=11 February 2010 |accessdate=11 February 2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> He has a younger sister Emma (b. 1988) and brother Sam (b. 1992).\n\n==Devin Cuddy Band==\n\nThe '''Devin Cuddy Band''' consists of Devin Cuddy, Nichol Robertson, Zach Sutton, and Devon Richardson.  Their first album \"Volume One\" was released on Cameron House Records in 2012 and has been nominated for roots & traditional album of the year (group) at the 2014 [[Juno Award]]s.<ref name=Juno>{{Cite web |url = http://junoawards.ca/nominees-2014/#Roots__Traditional_Album_of_the_Year_Group_Sponsored_by_the_Winnipeg_Folk_Festival |title = Nominees 2014 |website = The Juno Awards |accessdate = 13 February 2014 |url-status = dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140222215902/http://junoawards.ca/nominees-2014/#Roots__Traditional_Album_of_the_Year_Group_Sponsored_by_the_Winnipeg_Folk_Festival |archivedate = 22 February 2014 |df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn early 2014, his band opened for Blue Rodeo on that band's \"In Our Nature\" tour.<ref name=\"DevinCuddy.com\">{{Cite news |title=Devin Cuddy band opens for Blue Rodeo|url=http://www.devincuddy.com/bio.html|accessdate=11 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cuddy, Devin}}\n[[Category:Canadian rock singers]]\n[[Category:Canadian country singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:Canadian country guitarists]]\n[[Category:Canadian male guitarists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Canadian country rock musicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n\n\n{{Canada-musician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Canadian singer-songwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist  <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name            = Devin Cuddy\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| image_size      = \n| background      = solo_singer\n| birth_name      = Devin Cuddy\n| origin          = [[Toronto]], Ontario, Canada\n| instrument      = Guitar, piano, vocals\n| genre           = [[Country music|Country]], Rock\n| occupation      = Musician, songwriter\n| years_active    = 2012&ndash;present\n| label           = Cameron House Records\n| associated_acts = [[Blue Rodeo]], The Jim Cuddy Band\n| website         = {{URL|devincuddy.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Devin Cuddy''' (born 1987) is a Canadian singer-songwriter who fronts the Devin Cuddy Band.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nHis father, [[Jim Cuddy|Jim]], is a founding member of the well-known Canadian band [[Blue Rodeo]].  His mother, Rena Polley, is an actress.<ref name=Star>{{Cite news|last=Quill |first=Greg |title=Jim Cuddy on the road again |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/article/305778 |newspaper=Toronto Star |date=23 February 2008 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5nT9ZGw8E?url=http://www.thestar.com/printarticle/305778 |archivedate=11 February 2010 |accessdate=11 February 2010 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref> He has a younger sister Emma (b. 1988) and brother Sam (b. 1992).\n\n==Devin Cuddy Band==\n\nThe '''Devin Cuddy Band''' consists of Devin Cuddy, Nichol Robertson, Zach Sutton, and Devon Richardson.  Their first album \"Volume One\" was released on Cameron House Records in 2012 and has been nominated for roots & traditional album of the year (group) at the 2014 [[Juno Award]]s.<ref name=Juno>{{Cite web |url = http://junoawards.ca/nominees-2014/#Roots__Traditional_Album_of_the_Year_Group_Sponsored_by_the_Winnipeg_Folk_Festival |title = Nominees 2014 |website = The Juno Awards |accessdate = 13 February 2014 |url-status = dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140222215902/http://junoawards.ca/nominees-2014/#Roots__Traditional_Album_of_the_Year_Group_Sponsored_by_the_Winnipeg_Folk_Festival |archivedate = 22 February 2014 |df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn early 2014, his band opened for Blue Rodeo on that band's \"In Our Nature\" tour.<ref name=\"DevinCuddy.com\">{{Cite news |title=Devin Cuddy band opens for Blue Rodeo|url=http://www.devincuddy.com/bio.html|accessdate=11 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cuddy, Devin}}\n[[Category:Canadian rock singers]]\n[[Category:Canadian country singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Canadian rock guitarists]]\n[[Category:Canadian country guitarists]]\n[[Category:Canadian male guitarists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Canadian country rock musicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n\n\n{{Canada-musician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Plectral Rhythms", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Devin_Cuddy"}
{"title_page": "UK Youth Parliament", "text_new": "{{Infobox Organization\n|name         = UK Youth Parliament\n|image        = UKYouthParliament-Logo.jpg\n|image_border = \n|size         = 220px\n|caption      = \n|map          = \n|msize        = \n|mcaption     = \n|abbreviation = UKYP\n|motto        = Making Our Mark\n|formation    = {{Start date and years ago|1998|06|09|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=1998-06-09a.875.0|title=Youth Parliament: House of Commons debates, 9 June 1998, 3:34 pm |date=9 June 1998|work=[[Hansard]]|publisher=[[UK Parliament]]|accessdate=2009-11-02}}</ref>\n|extinction   = \n|status       = \n|headquarters = London, England <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/16403/index.html|title=UK Youth Parliament: Contact Us|accessdate=2011-02-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110211160207/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/16403/index.html|archivedate=2011-02-11}}</ref>\n|location     = \n|region_served = United Kingdom\n|membership   = 369<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/about-us/ukyp-work|title=YHow does UKYP Work? |date=9 June 1998|publisher=UK Youth Parliament|accessdate=2017-12-04}}</ref>\n|language     = English\n|leader_name  =\n|speaker      = [[John Bercow]], [[Speaker of the British House of Commons|Speaker of the House of Commons]]\n|parent_organisation = [[British Youth Council]]\n|affiliations = [[Scottish Youth Parliament]], Young Mayors Network, [[Welsh Youth Parliament]] and [[Funky Dragon]] (defunct)\n|num_staff    = \n|num_volunteers = \n|budget       = \n|website      = [http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/ ukyouthparliament.org.uk] \n|remarks      =\n}}\n\nThe '''UK Youth Parliament''' ('''UKYP''') is a [[Youth organization|youth organisation]] in the [[United Kingdom]], consisting of [[Democracy|democratically]] elected members aged between 11 and 18.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ukyp.org.uk/204867/204929.html|title=How to become an MYP|publisher=UK Youth Parliament|accessdate=16 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nFormed in 2000, the parliament has 369 members, who are elected to represent the views of young people in their area to government and service providers. Over 500,000 young people vote in the elections each year, which are held in over 90 percent of constituencies. It is managed by the [[British Youth Council]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.byc.org.uk/uk-work/uk-youth-parliament.aspx|title = UK Youth Parliament|accessdate = 2014-07-11|website = British Youth Council|publisher = British Youth Council|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140707111212/http://www.byc.org.uk/uk-work/uk-youth-parliament.aspx|archivedate = 2014-07-07}}</ref>\n\nMembers meet regularly to hold debates and plan campaigns at least three times a year locally, and twice on a national level, which includes the annual debate within the Chamber of the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] every November. Young people hold positions throughout the organisation's management, and it has been endorsed by the majority of the UK's political parties.\n\nThose elected for UKYP hold the suffix of MYP (Member of the UK Youth Parliament).\n\nDuring House of Commons sitting, UK Youth Parliament will be co-chaired by [[Speaker of the House of Commons|Speaker]] [[Lindsay Hoyle]] and Deputy Speaker [[Eleanor Laing]].\n\n== Formation ==\nThe concept of a United Kingdom Youth Parliament first arose at an event in [[Coventry]] entitled \"Heirs To The Millennium\".<ref name=\"history\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/4655/46854.html |title=History |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |accessdate=2009-03-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070818152512/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/4655/46854.html |archivedate=2007-08-18 }}</ref> After the event, the MP [[Andrew Rowe]] and the [[National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children]] and youth worker Kate Parish began to develop a proposal for the youth advocacy group. In 1998, a steering committee was formed, led by Andrew Rowe and chaired by a young person named Jannik Ecke.<ref name=\"About - UK Youth Parliament\">{{Cite web|url = http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/about/|title = About - UK Youth Parliament|date = |accessdate = 2014-07-11|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, [[Malcolm Wicks]], [[Department for Education and Employment]], agreed to employ a member of staff who would work full-time on developing the UK Youth Parliament alongside Kate Parish. Soon after, the first elections for the UK Youth Parliament were held, with the first Annual Sitting being held in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/about-us/history/ |title = Our history \u00ab UK Youth Parliament}}</ref>\n\nThere is wide debate over who was key to the formation of the UK Youth Parliament with several people trying to claim that they were key to its formation.{{Citation needed|date=September 2017}}\n\n== Composition ==\n\n=== Membership ===\n{{Main article|Member of Youth Parliament}}\nA Member of Youth Parliament (MYP) works with MPs, service providers, and decision makers in order to present the views of their constituents to them. Deputy Members of Youth Parliament are also elected, although not every MYP has a deputy.<ref name=\"About - UK Youth Parliament\"/> Deputies work with and support their Member of Youth Parliament locally and regionally, but are not entitled to attend the Annual Sitting or other national events \u2013 unless their MYP is unable to.\n\nThere are 369 constituencies that MYPs can sit in.\n\n=== Elections ===\nThe UK Youth Parliament elections are held every one or two years (depending on the local authority), with all young people between the ages of 11\u201318 being entitled to vote or stand. In England, over 90 percent of the [[local education authority|local education authorities]] hold UKYP elections.\n\nYoung people elect their local area's MYPs, who provide a voice for the young people in their area. The number of MYP positions is proportionate to the population of young people in the authority.\n\nOver one million votes were cast in the elections between 2006 and 2009. In 2008, 565,802 young people voted, with 1,625 standing as candidates from across [[England]], [[Wales]], and [[Northern Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/ukypdebatable/issue7/elections.pdf |title=Debatable Issue 7 |accessdate=2009-03-16 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090108053124/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/ukypdebatable/Issue7/elections.pdf |archivedate=2009-01-08 }}</ref>\n\nOutside of England, partner organisations undertake the elections; in [[Scotland]], elections are held every two years for young people to elect their local Member of the Scottish Youth Parliament (MSYP). The [[Scottish Youth Parliament]] then internally appoints sixteen of their members to represent the nation as their Members of the UK Youth Parliament which means that Scottish MYPs hold a [[dual mandate]] as both a MYP and a MSYP. In Northern Ireland a similar system is used by the [[Northern Ireland Youth Forum]] and was used in Wales until 2014 by the [[Children and Young People's Assembly for Wales]]. In 2018 the first online elections were held in Wales which returned 60 members for the Welsh Youth Parliament.\n\n== Meetings ==\n\n=== Annual Sitting ===\n\n{{Update|section|date=September 2017}}\n\n[[File:MYPs at the University of Kent.jpg|thumb|right|Members of Youth Parliament in session at the 2009 Annual Sitting]]\nThe Annual Sitting is the parliament's main yearly meeting, which all MYPs attend.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ukyp.org.uk/4655/index.html |title=About Us |accessdate=2008-11-14 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament }}</ref> It takes place on a university campus over three days. Proceedings include keynote speeches from political figures, followed by question and answer sessions. Past speakers include [[Hazel Blears]], [[Ben Bradshaw]], and [[Des Browne]]. MYPs also hold debates on topical issues, undertake training in [[political campaign|campaigning]], democracy and leadership, and consult with outside organisations such as the [[Ministry of Justice]], [[BBC Trust]] and [[Department for Transport]].\n\nAt each Annual Sitting, a [[manifesto]] is created, in which MYPs aim to fully represent the issues that affect their constituents in a single document. Policies are developed based on seven key areas: Culture, Media & Sport, Education & Employment, Empowering Young People, Health, International Matters, Law & Society, and Transport, Environment and Rural Affairs. This manifesto is then presented to government as a current overview of young peoples\u2019 views.\n\nThe 9th Annual Sitting was held at the [[University of Kent]] from 24 July to 27 July 2009. The keynote speakers were:\n* [[John Bercow]], [[Speaker of the British House of Commons|Speaker of the House of Commons]]\n* [[Wes Streeting]], President of the [[National Union of Students (United Kingdom)|National Union of Students]]\n* [[Jonathan Shaw (politician)|Jonathan Shaw]], Minister for the [[South East England|South East]]\n* [[Rowan Williams]], the [[Archbishop of Canterbury]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Kent hosts national UK Youth Parliament summit|url=http://www.cypnow.co.uk/news/ByDiscipline/Youth-Work/923163/Kent-hosts-national-UK-Youth-Parliament-summit|accessdate=2009-07-27|work=Children & Young People Now}}</ref>{{deadlink|date=September 2017}}\n\nUKYP's 10th Annual Sitting for 2010 was held at [[Ulster University]] between Friday 23 July and Monday 26 July.\n\nUKYP held its 11th Annual Sitting in 2011 at the [[University of Leeds]] from Friday 22 July to Sunday 24 July. UKYP were joined by the following speakers:\n* John Bercow\n* Iby Knell, a [[the Holocaust|Holocaust]] survivor\n* [[Natascha Engel]], Chair of the [[Backbench Business Committee]]\n* [[Tim Loughton]], Parliamentary Under Secretary for Children & Families\n* Maggie Atkinson, [[Children's Commissioner for England|Children's Commissioner]]\n* [[Chris Williamson (politician)|Chris Williamson]], Labour politician\n* [[Liam Burns (NUS)|Liam Burns]], [[National Union of Students (United Kingdom)|NUS]] President\n* Susan Nash, Chair of [[Young Labour (United Kingdom)|Young Labour]]\n* [[Ben Howlett (politician)|Ben Howlett]], Chairman of [[Conservative Future]]\n\nThe 12th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2012 took place at the [[University of Nottingham]] over the weekend of 27\u201329 July.\n\nThe 13th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2013 again took place at the [[University of Leeds]]. Speakers included [[Vince Cable]]; John Bercow; and [[Pamela Warhurst]] of [[Incredible Edible]].\n\nThe 14th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2014 took place at the [[University of Lancaster]] over the weekend of 25\u201327 July. Keynote Speakers included John Bercow; Maggie Atkinson; and Kamal Hyman, a previous Member of Youth Parliament for [[Peterborough]].\n\nThe 15th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2015 took place at the [[University of Exeter]] over the weekend of 31 July - 2 August. Keynote Speakers included John Bercow; Jonny Chatteron, founder of the campaign group Campaign BootCamp; and [[Si\u00e2n James (politician)|Si\u00e2n James]] former [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Swansea East (UK Parliament constituency)|Swansea East]].\n\nUKYP'S 16th Annual Sitting for 2016 took place at the [[University of York]], between 22\u201324 July. Keynote speakers included John Bercow and [[Gulwali Passarlay]].\n\nIn 2017, UKYP's 17th Annual Sitting took place at [[Liverpool Hope University]] between 28\u201330 July 2017, with keynote speakers John Bercow and Hillsborough campaigner Margaret Aspinall, as well as various MPs and campaigners involved in a panel debate.\n\nThe 18th UKYP Annual Conference - name changed after a vote was held and majority returned in favour of change - took place at the [[University of Nottingham]] from the 27-29 July 2018. The keynote speakers included John Bercow, Joy Warmington of brap and Alison Kriel of Amaya Trust.\n\n=== Circles of Influence ===\nThe annual Circles of Influence aimed to focus on key youth issues, by engaging government departments, public organisations and young people in an exciting debate format. It involved around 200 MYPs holding discussions seated in a circular shape.\n\nThe event was first held in 2006, and took place at the [[British Museum]]. It has focused on topics including talent, leadership, and intergenerational relations. Prominent attendees included [[Tessa Jowell]], [[John Taylor, Baron Taylor of Warwick|Lord Taylor]] and [[Harriet Harman]].\n\n=== House of Lords debates ===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:UK Youth Parliament House of Lords 2008.jpg|thumb|right|Members of Youth Parliament debating in the House of Lords]]  -->In May 2008, the UKYP was granted permission to hold a debate between over 300 MYPs in the [[House of Lords]],<ref>{{cite news|title=UK Youth Parliament at Westminster |date=May 2008 |publisher=[[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] |url=http://www.parliament.uk/education/visiting-parliament/uk-youth-parliament.htm |work=Parliament.uk |accessdate=14 November 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090228194558/http://www.parliament.uk/education/visiting-parliament/uk-youth-parliament.htm |archivedate=February 28, 2009 }}</ref> making it one of only two organisations to ever use the venue for non-Parliamentary proceedings, the other being the English Speaking Union for their International Mace Final on 12 May 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/devon/7371723.stm\n |title=Youth Parliament debate in Lords |publisher=BBC News |date=2008-04-28 |accessdate=2009-03-16 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/06_02_08_stormlords.html |title=Young People Set to Storm House of Lords |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |date=2008-02-06 |accessdate=2009-03-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722151948/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/06_02_08_stormlords.html |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref> The event was chaired by the [[Lord Speaker]] [[Baroness Hayman]] and was broadcast on [[BBC Parliament]].\n\nThe debates held were:\n* Recycling and the [[Natural environment|environment]]\n* National transport concession for young people\n* [[Top-up fees|Abolish university tuition fees]]\n* [[Fear of youth|Fair representation of young people]] in the media\n* [[Votes at 16|Lowering the voting age to 16]]\n* Whether the amount of [[betting stores]] should be restricted.  \n* Single age of adulthood\n\n=== House of Commons debates ===\n\n==== 2007\u201309 ====\nPrime Minister [[Gordon Brown]] suggested that members of the UK Youth Parliament could have annual access to the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] chamber in 2007,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2007/03_07_07_gordonbrown.html |title=Gordon Brown calls for greater role for the UK Youth Parliament in constitutional reform |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |date=2007-07-03 |accessdate=2009-03-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722152020/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2007/03_07_07_gordonbrown.html |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref> but this did not come about until March 2009, when a motion was passed<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/2009/mar/17/youngpeople-houseofcommons|title=Smells like teen spirit: youths to sit in the Commons|last=Sparrow|first=Andrew|date=17 March 2009 |work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref> to allow the UK Youth Parliament to use the House of Commons for that year's annual meeting. However, a Conservative Member of Parliament objected, which forced a vote to be taken on the issue, also employing a procedure called \"[[Strangers (Parliament of the United Kingdom)|I spy strangers]]\" (historically used to expel disruptive spectators, but now mostly to disrupt the House's business)<ref name=\"ispystrangers\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/glossary/?gl=180|title=TheyWorkForYou.com glossary: I Spy Strangers|accessdate=18 March 2009}}</ref> to take business in the House beyond 7:00pm and stifle any possible debate on the issue. On 12 March, a second debate was held in the House of Commons with a vote set to be taken four days later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.politics.co.uk/mps/press-releases/party-politics/labour/sharon-hodgson-mp-slams-tory-\u2018dinosaurs\u2019-over-uk-youth-parliament-debate-$1280028.htm\n |title=Sharon Hodgson MP slams Tory \"dinosaurs\" over UK Youth Parliament debate |publisher=Politics.co.uk |date=2009-03-12 |accessdate=2009-03-16 }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2009-03-12a.528.0\n |title=House of Commons debates |publisher=TheyWorkForYou.com |date=2009-03-12 |accessdate=2009-03-16 }}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2009, 189 [[Member of Parliament|Members of Parliament]] voted to allow the UK Youth Parliament to debate in the House of Commons, with 16 votes of opposition by Conservative [[backbencher]]s. It was the first time in history that the House of Commons chamber was used by a group other than MPs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/7947335.stm\n |title=Youth to meet in Commons chamber |publisher=BBC News |date=2009-03-16 |accessdate=2009-03-17 }}</ref>\n\nAn online vote was held from July to determine the debate topics, which were:\n* [[Top-up fees|Abolish university tuition fees]]\n* [[Juvenile delinquency|Youth crime]] and how to tackle it\n* [[Concessionary Bus Travel Act 2007|Free transport for over 60s]], but not for young people\n* [[Capitalism]], [[Late-2000s recession|the economy]] and job opportunities for young people\n* [[Voting age#Chronology of lowering the voting age to 16|Lowering the voting age to 16]]\n\n{{Rquote|right|At 16, we can marry our MP, we can sleep with our MP and we can have children with our MP. We can sign up in preparation for fighting and potentially dying for our MP. And suddenly we are not mature enough to vote for them. What an absolute disgrace!|James Evans MYP|{{cite hansard | url=http://www.parliament.the-stationery-office.co.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/youth/debtext/91030.htm#09110254000236 | house=House of Commons | date=30 October 2009 | column=33 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604193952/http://www.parliament.the-stationery-office.co.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/youth/debtext/91030.htm#09110254000236 | archivedate=4 June 2011 }}}}\nThe debates took place in the House of Commons chamber on Friday 30 October 2009, from 11am to 3:30pm. The session was recorded in [[Hansard]], and the morning debates were broadcast on BBC Parliament the same day. The final two debates were televised later in the week.\n\nThe debates were chaired by [[John Bercow]], Speaker of the House of Commons, who closed the event with a dramatic speech to MYPs in which he described the [[British National Party]] as \"a poison which we could well do without\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8333161.stm|title=Speaker attacks \"poison\" of BNP |date=30 October 2009|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref> The Speaker is usually expected to remain impartial, so as not to compromise his authority, but in this case was able to express personal opinion because the ornamental mace that indicates Parliament is sitting was not in place.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/bercow-breaks-convention-to-attack-bnp-1812274.html|title=Bercow breaks convention to attack BNP|last=Savage|first=Michael|date=31 October 2009|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n==== 2010 ====\nIn 2010 a debate was held to disuses the possibility of the youth parliament returning for a second sitting.  This resulted in the decision to allow their return not only for that year, but every year for the remainder of the sitting of the current parliament.\n\nUKYP's 2010 Debate took place on 29 October, again chaired by [[John Bercow]], Speaker of the House of Commons with the topics chosen for debate being selected from an Online Ballot. It was broadcast live on Parliament's Website & BBC Parliament.\n\nAs reported on the UK Youth Parliament's official website, the results of the five issues that were debated are listed as follows:\n*Should sex and relationships education be compulsory from primary school onwards? FOR-211 and AGAINST-104 \n*Should university tuition fees rise? FOR-57 and AGAINST-267\n*Should the school leaving age be raised to 18 immediately in order to lower youth unemployment? FOR-56 and AGAINST-271 \n*Should we withdraw all British troops from Afghanistan by 2012? FOR-137 and AGAINST-179 \n*Should reduced transport fares for young people be protected from spending cuts? FOR-239 and AGAINST-80\n\nTherefore, \"Should reduced transport fares for young people be protected from spending cuts?\" became UKYP's National Campaign for 2011.\n\n==== 2011 ====\nIn 2011, the Members of Youth Parliament again debated in the House of Commons on 4 November. This time five topics were chosen by over 65,000 young people. The event was chaired by [[John Bercow]], Speaker of the House of Commons, after his persistence in supporting the youth parliament. The sitting was broadcast on [[BBC Parliament]] but this time live from 11:00am \u2013 4:00pm.\n\nFollowing the debates, the motion entitled 'Make public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all' was chosen as UKYP's National Campaign for 2012.\n\n==== 2012 ====\nIn 2012 and for the fourth time, Members of UKYP gathered in the House of Commons on 23 November, with the topics again being chosen through the Make Your Ballot. There was a large increase in turnout. From 65,000 in 2011, over 253,000 took part to choose the five topics that were debated. Again it was chaired by John Bercow, Speaker of the House of Commons, and was broadcast live via Parliament's Website & BBC Parliament from 11:00-16:00. \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 received 154 votes from the 295 cast and therefore became UKYP's 2013 National Campaign.\n\n==== 2013 ====\nIn 2013, Members of UKYP came together for the fifth year in a row to debate on the green benches on 15 November, the top five issues chosen through the Make Your Mark Ballot. A record 478,386 young people took part, an increase of over 225,000 from 2012. In a difference to choosing campaigns, Members of UKYP chose two campaigns for 2014; one UK-wide issue and one devolved issue (England only). It was chaired like the other debates by John Bercow, Speaker of the House of Commons, and broadcast live on Parliament's Website & BBC Parliament from 11:00-16:00.\n\nFollowing the debates in which [[Nick Hurd]] MP, then Minister for Civil Society stated that 'Old shouldn't dominate politics', \u2018Votes For 16 and 17 Year Olds In All Public Elections\u2019 was prioritised as the UK Priority Campaign for 2014, whilst \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 was voted as the priority campaign for England.\n\n==== 2014 ====\nThe 2014 UKYP sitting in the House of Commons took place on 14 November with the biggest media attention in the sitting's six-year history. Once more chaired by John Bercow, Speaker of the House of Commons, the topics were chosen through 876,488 ballots, around 14.8% of the UK's 11-18-year-old population. The proceedings were broadcast on Parliament's website as tradition but were only shown through the [[BBC]] via their Democracy Live Site; the reason for this was due to the [[Scottish National Party]]'s Annual Autumn Conference commencing that day. However, it was broadcast between 20:20-00:00 on [[BBC Parliament]] that day to give chance for viewers to watch if they couldn't watch online. Also, for the first time the event was covered by [[Sky News]] on the world's biggest video sharing site, [[YouTube]] through their 'Stand Up Be Counted' campaign, which was launched in the summer of 2014.\n\nBefore the debates on campaigns occurred, MYPs held a special commemoration marking the 100th anniversary of the start of [[World War I]]. Thirteen MYPs were selected by a video application process to speak from the Dispatch Boxes on how the war affected either their families of region followed by one minute of silence. This was agreed on at UKYP's Annual Sitting in Lancaster that summer.\n\nOnce the debates and speeches from [[Leader of the House of Commons]], [[William Hague]], [[Natascha Engel]] MP and [[Tessa Munt]] MP had taken place, the following information shows the results of the two votes; one for the UK-wide 2015 issue and like 2013's debate, one devolved issue for England:\n\nUK-wide issue: \n*Everyone should be paid at least the Living Wage: 156 \n*Votes for 16- and 17-year-olds in all public elections: 117\n\nEngland-wide issue:\n*Mental health services should be improved with our help: 176\n*Better work experience and careers advice: 78\n*Bring back exam resits in English and Maths: 32\n\nTherefore, 'Everyone should be paid at least the Living Wage' was chosen as UKYP's UK Campaign for 2015 whiles 'Mental Health services should be improved by our help' became UKYP's 2015 Campaign for England.\n\n==== 2015 ====\n\nThe 2015 sitting took place on 13 November, following the counting of 969,992 Make Your Mark Ballots that were cast through the ballot.\n\nAfter the debates occurred, a special 30 minute debate entitled \"My Magna Carta\" was held, 800 years after the historic document was first signed.\n\nThe information below states the results of the ballots, to choose what of the debated topics would become the two priority campaigns for 2016:\n\nUK Wide:\n\n\u2022\tWorking together to combat racism and religious discrimination: 155\n\n\u2022\tEveryone should be paid at least the Living Wage: 117\n\nTackling Racism and Religious Discrimination therefore became the UK Wide campaign for 2016, and became the inquiry subject for the year's Youth Select Committee.\n\nDevolved:\n\n\u2022\tMental health services should be improved with our help: 176\n\n\u2022\tA curriculum to prepare us for life: 110\n\n\u2022\tMake public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all: 33\n\nThe existing Mental Health campaign was therefore re-selected as the devolved campaign for 2016.\n\n==== 2019 Sitting - amongst the General Election campaign ====\n\nDespite the calling of the [[2019 United Kingdom general election]], the sitting still went ahead and took place on November 8th 2019. The debates were chaired for the first time by both the new Speaker [[Lindsay Hoyle | Sir Lindsay Hoyle]] and fellow speakership candidate and current 1st Deputy Speaker [[Eleanor Laing | Dame Eleanor Laing]]. \n\nAs has been for each sitting, the Make Your Mark ballot determined the topics and overall saw just over 840,000 young people take part across the United Kingdom in 2019, with the motion on Protecting the Environment becoming the parliament's UK wise campaign for 2020 and Ending Knife Crime being chosen by MYP's as the devolved campaign topic.\n\nThe full results were as follows:\n\n'''UK Wide Campaign Topic'''\n\nProtecting the Climate - 179\n\nTackling Hate Crime - 68\n\n'''Devolved Campaign Topic'''\n\nMental Health - 69\n\nCurriculum to Prepare us for Life - 86\n\nPut an End to Knife Crime - 87\n\nFor the first time, the UK wide campaign topic will be launched as a Parliamentary E-Petition of which will be debated in the Commons chamber, if 100,000 members of the public sign it. The petition will be launched in early 2020.\n\nDue to dissolution of Parliament and it having taken place on November 6th 2019 (being prior to November 8th's proceedings), full broadcasting of the debates along with the publication of media reports, under election regulations were not published until 16th December 2019 - the week following the election. Full proceedings were made available on Parliament's YouTube channel that morning.\n\n==== Paul Boskett Memorial Trophy ====\n\nIn 2014 the introduction of the Paul Boskett Debate Lead Trophy was introduced. Every region elects someone to represent them and speak at the Dispatch Box and the strongest speaker is now awarded; the name comes from the late Paul Boskett MBE, who died in 2014 aged 59; he worked and was a lead figure within the [[British Youth Council]]. Paul is cited as a major inspiration for many young people and seen as a key champion of youth voice. The first Debate Lead Champion was Ife Grillo who sat as a Vice Chair to the British Youth Council between 2015-2017 and at the time of the Commons debate on 14 November 2014, represented the London Borough of Hackney.\n\n== Regional ==\nMembers of Youth Parliament in England are split into nine geographical regions, which meet and work together regularly: [[London]], [[East Midlands]], [[West Midlands (region)|West Midlands]], [[South West England|South West]], [[South East England|South East]], [[North West England|North West]], [[North East England|North East]], [[Yorkshire and the Humber]], [[East of England]].\n\nRegional meetings known as conventions take place three times a year (June, October and December) and last around a day. Members share news, issues and resources, in addition to taking part in training to help them in their role, relevant Government Consultations and within the October Convention, Elections occur to decide regional representatives to be a Debate Lead for UKYP's House of Commons Debate and the UKYP Steering Group for the following year (1 February to 31 January).\n\n== Campaigns ==\nThe UK Youth Parliament launched the \"Make Your Mark\" ballot in 2011. The purpose of the ballot to get young people from across the UK to determine which five topics the UK Youth Parliament would debate within the House of Commons. Over 65,000 young people completed the ballot after several months of campaigning.\n\nThe first five issues debated in the House of Commons chamber through 'Make Your Mark' were:\n# \"Make public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all\"\n# \"No to tuition fees, yes to graduate tax\"\n# \"Zero tolerance towards bullying in schools\"\n# \"End child poverty\"\n# \"A Greener future for Britain\"\n\nOn 4 November 2011, Members of Youth Parliament came from across the UK to debate and vote at House of Commons the most important issue to campaign on in 2012. The winning campaign topic was \"Make public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all\".\n\n2012's sitting chose \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 as the 2013 National Campaign. Over 253,000 young people took part.\n\nIn 2013, \u2018Votes For 16 and 17 Year Old's In All Public Elections\u2019 was prioritised as the UK Priority Campaign for 2014, whilst \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 was voted as the priority campaign for England. A new record of 478,386 young people cast a vote.\n\nIn 2014  876,488 young people helped to choose the House of Commons topics; over 14.8% of the UK's 11-18 year old population. 'Everyone should be paid at least the Living Wage' was chosen as UKYP's UK Campaign for 2015 with a National Campaign Day occurring on 24 January 2015. Also 'Mental Health services should be improved by our help' became UKYP's 2015 Campaign for England.\n\n2015 recorded 969,992 votes and saw that year's Commons Debate select Mental Health chosen as the England Campaign issue and Tackling Racism & Discrimination as the UK priority topic to campaign on.\n\n2016 saw another increase in MYM's total, with 978,216 having there say and as a result of that year's debates on the famous Green Benches, saw Votes at 16 be selected as the England campaign issue and a Curriculum for Life for the 2nd time be the national priority campaign topic.\n\nIn 2017, the Make Your Mark for the first time in the ballot's history fell, to 954,766 - of which however was widely still seen as an impressive total considering the scale of Youth Provision cuts since 2010. Both issues chosen in 2016, of a Curriculum for Life and Votes at 16 were once again selected by MYP's to be the priority campaign topics, however with them being switched in relation to the campaign area, meaning Votes at 16 took national precedent and a Curriculum for Life reverted to England only focus.\n\n2018's Ballot has written history and seen a initial total of 1,022,286 votes be declared, marking the first time Make Your Mark has exceeded 7 figures; with an increased and revised 2nd total to be announced on 24 October 2018, along with the Commons Debate topics for this year's proceedings - to be held on 9 November 2018.\n\n== Organisation ==\n\n=== Governance ===\n\n==== Steering Group ====\nDecisions regarding the development and progression of the organisation is undertaken by the Steering Group, made up of one MYP elected from each region and nation (known as \"SGs\"), for a 12-month term from 1 February to 31 January the following year. Their main focus is \"key decisions relating to the membership and the programme of work, within the given strategic boundaries\".<ref name=\"Accounts2008\">{{cite web |url=http://www.charity-commission.gov.uk/registeredcharities/ScannedAccounts/Ends16%5C0001084716_ac_20080331_e_c.pdf|title=Democracy for Young People Accounts 31 Mar 2008|publisher=[[Charity Commission]]|pages=4|accessdate=2009-11-03}}{{dead link|date=October 2017|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}} </ref>\n\nThey meet a minimum of four times a year to represent their regions nationally, coordinate campaign efforts and organise events such as the Annual Conference. Reports are taken back to MYPs at their regional conventions & other meetings.\n\nThe name of the group was changed from Procedures Group to Steering Group in November 2019 in order to reflect the groups varied responsibilities better.\n\n==== Management and support ====\n \nThe [[British Youth Council]] manages the UK Youth Parliament. The British Youth Council won a bid in 2011, granted by the [[Department for Education]] to lead a national Youth Voice Service. Youth Voice will support young people in influencing local and national Government decision making in England, and provide continued support for the UK Youth Parliament.\n\nThe corporate and administrative governance is overseen by the Board of Trustees of the [[British Youth Council]].\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Praise ===\nThe organisation has been endorsed by former Prime Ministers [[Gordon Brown]] and [[David Cameron]]. It has also been endorsed by former [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] Party Leader and former Deputy Prime Minister [[Nick Clegg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.epolitix.com/stakeholder-websites/stakeholder-website-page/sites/uk-youth-parliament/\n |title=UK Youth Parliament |publisher=ePoliticx |accessdate=2009-04-27 }}</ref> In 2009, Brown described the UK Youth Parliament as \"a symbol of the politics we should all strive for - politics that bring people together to work for what is best for us all.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.number10.gov.uk/Page21138|title=Youth Parliament takes over Commons|date=30 October 2009|publisher=[[10 Downing Street]]|accessdate=2009-11-03|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091101012234/http://www.number10.gov.uk/Page21138|archivedate=1 November 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, the organisation's Head of Programmes Kate Parish was given a [[National Council for Voluntary Youth Services]] Award, for her \"commendable dedication to the development of UK Youth Parliament\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ncvys.org.uk/UserFiles/File/News/Press%20Releases/NCVYS%20Press%20Release_VYOs%20debate%20key%20issues%20around%20faith%20and%20young%20people_22.10.07.pdf|title=Voluntary Youth Organisations debate key issues around faith and young people in society at the NCVYS annual conference|date=22 October 2007|publisher=National Council for Voluntary Youth Services|accessdate=2009-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721121041/http://www.ncvys.org.uk/UserFiles/File/News/Press%20Releases/NCVYS%20Press%20Release_VYOs%20debate%20key%20issues%20around%20faith%20and%20young%20people_22.10.07.pdf#|archive-date=2011-07-21|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the UK Youth Parliament was given the Positive Images award by the ''[[Children & Young People Now]]'' magazine for exposing young people\u2019s experiences of the current levels of sex and relationships education in a high-profile publicity campaign.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/13_06_08_award.html |title=UK Youth Parliament Scoops Another Award! |accessdate=2008-06-13 |date=2009-03-16 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722152010/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/13_06_08_award.html |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref> In 2009, the organisation also received a Brook special achievement award for this campaign.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2009/25_03_09_brookaward.html |title=UK Youth Parliament wins Brook special achievement award for SRE campaign! |accessdate=2009-02-25 |date=2009-05-01 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090704223936/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2009/25_03_09_brookaward.html |archivedate=2009-07-04 }}</ref>\n\n=== Criticism ===\nMYPs co-signed an open letter with public figures including [[Davina McCall]] and [[Polly Toynbee]] to ''[[The Times]]''. The letter protested against the lack of sufficient [[Sex education|sex and relationships education]] in schools, and that the UK Youth Parliament believe that this has led to increasing [[teenage pregnancy]].{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\nA study by the [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado]] found that youth participation organisations in the UK, including the UK Youth Parliament, needed to \"tackle the unintentional practice of [[tokenism]]\". The paper concludes that \"failing to act upon [young people's] opinions \nor take them very seriously\" once they are identified is often a cause of frustration amongst participants.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Youth Participation in the UK: Bureaucratic Disaster or Triumph of Child Rights?|journal=Children, Youth and Environments|year=2006|first=Emily|last=Middleton|volume=16|issue=2|pages=11|url=http://www.colorado.edu/journals/cye/16_2/16_2_12_YouthParticipationUK.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111217044158/http://www.colorado.edu/journals/cye/16_2/16_2_12_YouthParticipationUK.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=2011-12-17|accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Commonscat|UK youth parliament}}\n*[[Scottish Youth Parliament]]\n*[[Welsh Youth Parliament]]\n*[[Youth politics]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk Official website]\n{{UK Youth Parliament}}\n{{Youth empowerment}}\n\n[[Category:Youth model government]]\n[[Category:Youth-led organizations]]\n[[Category:Political organisations based in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Youth empowerment organizations]]\n[[Category:1999 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Charities based in London]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in the London Borough of Hackney]]\n[[Category:Youth organisations based in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Organization\n|name         = UK Youth Parliament\n|image        = UKYouthParliament-Logo.jpg\n|image_border = \n|size         = 220px\n|caption      = \n|map          = \n|msize        = \n|mcaption     = \n|abbreviation = UKYP\n|motto        = Making Our Mark\n|formation    = {{Start date and years ago|1998|06|09|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=1998-06-09a.875.0|title=Youth Parliament: House of Commons debates, 9 June 1998, 3:34 pm |date=9 June 1998|work=[[Hansard]]|publisher=[[UK Parliament]]|accessdate=2009-11-02}}</ref>\n|extinction   = \n|status       = \n|headquarters = London, England <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/16403/index.html|title=UK Youth Parliament: Contact Us|accessdate=2011-02-21|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110211160207/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/16403/index.html|archivedate=2011-02-11}}</ref>\n|location     = \n|region_served = United Kingdom\n|membership   = 369<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/about-us/ukyp-work|title=YHow does UKYP Work? |date=9 June 1998|publisher=UK Youth Parliament|accessdate=2017-12-04}}</ref>\n|language     = English\n|leader_name  =\n|speaker      = [[John Bercow]], [[Speaker of the British House of Commons|Speaker of the House of Commons]]\n|parent_organisation = [[British Youth Council]]\n|affiliations = [[Scottish Youth Parliament]], Young Mayors Network, [[Welsh Youth Parliament]] and [[Funky Dragon]] (defunct)\n|num_staff    = \n|num_volunteers = \n|budget       = \n|website      = [http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/ ukyouthparliament.org.uk] \n|remarks      =\n}}\n\nThe '''UK Youth Parliament''' ('''UKYP''') is a [[Youth organization|youth organisation]] in the [[United Kingdom]], consisting of [[Democracy|democratically]] elected members aged between 11 and 18.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ukyp.org.uk/204867/204929.html|title=How to become an MYP|publisher=UK Youth Parliament|accessdate=16 July 2010}}</ref>\n\nFormed in 2000, the parliament has 369 members, who are elected to represent the views of young people in their area to government and service providers. Over 500,000 young people vote in the elections each year, which are held in over 90 percent of constituencies. It is managed by the [[British Youth Council]].<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.byc.org.uk/uk-work/uk-youth-parliament.aspx|title = UK Youth Parliament|accessdate = 2014-07-11|website = British Youth Council|publisher = British Youth Council|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140707111212/http://www.byc.org.uk/uk-work/uk-youth-parliament.aspx|archivedate = 2014-07-07}}</ref>\n\nMembers meet regularly to hold debates and plan campaigns at least three times a year locally, and twice on a national level, which includes the annual debate within the Chamber of the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] every November. Young people hold positions throughout the organisation's management, and it has been endorsed by the majority of the UK's political parties.\n\nThose elected for UKYP hold the suffix of MYP (Member of the UK Youth Parliament).\n\nDuring House of Commons sitting, UK Youth Parliament will be co-chaired by [[Speaker of the House of Commons|Speaker]] [[Lindsay Hoyle]] and Deputy Speaker [[Eleanor Laing]].\n\n== Formation ==\nThe concept of a United Kingdom Youth Parliament first arose at an event in [[Coventry]] entitled \"Heirs To The Millennium\".<ref name=\"history\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/4655/46854.html |title=History |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |accessdate=2009-03-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070818152512/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/4655/46854.html |archivedate=2007-08-18 }}</ref> After the event, the MP [[Andrew Rowe]] and the [[National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children]] and youth worker Kate Parish began to develop a proposal for the youth advocacy group. In 1998, a steering committee was formed, led by Andrew Rowe and chaired by a young person named Jannik Ecke.<ref name=\"About - UK Youth Parliament\">{{Cite web|url = http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/about/|title = About - UK Youth Parliament|date = |accessdate = 2014-07-11|website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, [[Malcolm Wicks]], [[Department for Education and Employment]], agreed to employ a member of staff who would work full-time on developing the UK Youth Parliament alongside Kate Parish. Soon after, the first elections for the UK Youth Parliament were held, with the first Annual Sitting being held in 2001.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/about-us/history/ |title = Our history \u00ab UK Youth Parliament}}</ref>\n\nThere is wide debate over who was key to the formation of the UK Youth Parliament with several people trying to claim that they were key to its formation.{{Citation needed|date=September 2017}}\n\n== Composition ==\n\n=== Membership ===\n{{Main article|Member of Youth Parliament}}\nA Member of Youth Parliament (MYP) works with MPs, service providers, and decision makers in order to present the views of their constituents to them. Deputy Members of Youth Parliament are also elected, although not every MYP has a deputy.<ref name=\"About - UK Youth Parliament\"/> Deputies work with and support their Member of Youth Parliament locally and regionally, but are not entitled to attend the Annual Sitting or other national events \u2013 unless their MYP is unable to.\n\nThere are 369 constituencies that MYPs can sit in.\n\n=== Elections ===\nThe UK Youth Parliament elections are held every one or two years (depending on the local authority), with all young people between the ages of 11\u201318 being entitled to vote or stand. In England, over 90 percent of the [[local education authority|local education authorities]] hold UKYP elections.\n\nYoung people elect their local area's MYPs, who provide a voice for the young people in their area. The number of MYP positions is proportionate to the population of young people in the authority.\n\nOver one million votes were cast in the elections between 2006 and 2009. In 2008, 565,802 young people voted, with 1,625 standing as candidates from across [[England]], [[Wales]], and [[Northern Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/ukypdebatable/issue7/elections.pdf |title=Debatable Issue 7 |accessdate=2009-03-16 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090108053124/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/ukypdebatable/Issue7/elections.pdf |archivedate=2009-01-08 }}</ref>\n\nOutside of England, partner organisations undertake the elections; in [[Scotland]], elections are held every two years for young people to elect their local Member of the Scottish Youth Parliament (MSYP). The [[Scottish Youth Parliament]] then internally appoints sixteen of their members to represent the nation as their Members of the UK Youth Parliament which means that Scottish MYPs hold a [[dual mandate]] as both a MYP and a MSYP. In Northern Ireland a similar system is used by the [[Northern Ireland Youth Forum]] and was used in Wales until 2014 by the [[Children and Young People's Assembly for Wales]]. In 2018 the first online elections were held in Wales which returned 60 members for the Welsh Youth Parliament.\n\n== Meetings ==\n\n=== Annual Sitting ===\n\n{{Update|section|date=September 2017}}\n\n[[File:MYPs at the University of Kent.jpg|thumb|right|Members of Youth Parliament in session at the 2009 Annual Sitting]]\nThe Annual Sitting is the parliament's main yearly meeting, which all MYPs attend.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ukyp.org.uk/4655/index.html |title=About Us |accessdate=2008-11-14 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament }}</ref> It takes place on a university campus over three days. Proceedings include keynote speeches from political figures, followed by question and answer sessions. Past speakers include [[Hazel Blears]], [[Ben Bradshaw]], and [[Des Browne]]. MYPs also hold debates on topical issues, undertake training in [[political campaign|campaigning]], democracy and leadership, and consult with outside organisations such as the [[Ministry of Justice]], [[BBC Trust]] and [[Department for Transport]].\n\nAt each Annual Sitting, a [[manifesto]] is created, in which MYPs aim to fully represent the issues that affect their constituents in a single document. Policies are developed based on seven key areas: Culture, Media & Sport, Education & Employment, Empowering Young People, Health, International Matters, Law & Society, and Transport, Environment and Rural Affairs. This manifesto is then presented to government as a current overview of young peoples\u2019 views.\n\nThe 9th Annual Sitting was held at the [[University of Kent]] from 24 July to 27 July 2009. The keynote speakers were:\n* [[John Bercow]], [[Speaker of the British House of Commons|Speaker of the House of Commons]]\n* [[Wes Streeting]], President of the [[National Union of Students (United Kingdom)|National Union of Students]]\n* [[Jonathan Shaw (politician)|Jonathan Shaw]], Minister for the [[South East England|South East]]\n* [[Rowan Williams]], the [[Archbishop of Canterbury]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Kent hosts national UK Youth Parliament summit|url=http://www.cypnow.co.uk/news/ByDiscipline/Youth-Work/923163/Kent-hosts-national-UK-Youth-Parliament-summit|accessdate=2009-07-27|work=Children & Young People Now}}</ref>{{deadlink|date=September 2017}}\n\nUKYP's 10th Annual Sitting for 2010 was held at [[Ulster University]] between Friday 23 July and Monday 26 July.\n\nUKYP held its 11th Annual Sitting in 2011 at the [[University of Leeds]] from Friday 22 July to Sunday 24 July. UKYP were joined by the following speakers:\n* John Bercow\n* Iby Knell, a [[the Holocaust|Holocaust]] survivor\n* [[Natascha Engel]], Chair of the [[Backbench Business Committee]]\n* [[Tim Loughton]], Parliamentary Under Secretary for Children & Families\n* Maggie Atkinson, [[Children's Commissioner for England|Children's Commissioner]]\n* [[Chris Williamson (politician)|Chris Williamson]], Labour politician\n* [[Liam Burns (NUS)|Liam Burns]], [[National Union of Students (United Kingdom)|NUS]] President\n* Susan Nash, Chair of [[Young Labour (United Kingdom)|Young Labour]]\n* [[Ben Howlett (politician)|Ben Howlett]], Chairman of [[Conservative Future]]\n\nThe 12th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2012 took place at the [[University of Nottingham]] over the weekend of 27\u201329 July.\n\nThe 13th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2013 again took place at the [[University of Leeds]]. Speakers included [[Vince Cable]]; John Bercow; and [[Pamela Warhurst]] of [[Incredible Edible]].\n\nThe 14th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2014 took place at the [[University of Lancaster]] over the weekend of 25\u201327 July. Keynote Speakers included John Bercow; Maggie Atkinson; and Kamal Hyman, a previous Member of Youth Parliament for [[Peterborough]].\n\nThe 15th UKYP Annual Sitting for 2015 took place at the [[University of Exeter]] over the weekend of 31 July - 2 August. Keynote Speakers included John Bercow; Jonny Chatteron, founder of the campaign group Campaign BootCamp; and [[Si\u00e2n James (politician)|Si\u00e2n James]] former [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] [[Member of Parliament]] for [[Swansea East (UK Parliament constituency)|Swansea East]].\n\nUKYP'S 16th Annual Sitting for 2016 took place at the [[University of York]], between 22\u201324 July. Keynote speakers included John Bercow and [[Gulwali Passarlay]].\n\nIn 2017, UKYP's 17th Annual Sitting took place at [[Liverpool Hope University]] between 28\u201330 July 2017, with keynote speakers John Bercow and Hillsborough campaigner Margaret Aspinall, as well as various MPs and campaigners involved in a panel debate.\n\nThe 18th UKYP Annual Conference - name changed after a vote was held and majority returned in favour of change - took place at the [[University of Nottingham]] from the 27-29 July 2018. The keynote speakers included John Bercow, Joy Warmington of brap and Alison Kriel of Amaya Trust.\n\n=== Circles of Influence ===\nThe annual Circles of Influence aimed to focus on key youth issues, by engaging government departments, public organisations and young people in an exciting debate format. It involved around 200 MYPs holding discussions seated in a circular shape.\n\nThe event was first held in 2006, and took place at the [[British Museum]]. It has focused on topics including talent, leadership, and intergenerational relations. Prominent attendees included [[Tessa Jowell]], [[John Taylor, Baron Taylor of Warwick|Lord Taylor]] and [[Harriet Harman]].\n\n=== House of Lords debates ===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:UK Youth Parliament House of Lords 2008.jpg|thumb|right|Members of Youth Parliament debating in the House of Lords]]  -->In May 2008, the UKYP was granted permission to hold a debate between over 300 MYPs in the [[House of Lords]],<ref>{{cite news|title=UK Youth Parliament at Westminster |date=May 2008 |publisher=[[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] |url=http://www.parliament.uk/education/visiting-parliament/uk-youth-parliament.htm |work=Parliament.uk |accessdate=14 November 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090228194558/http://www.parliament.uk/education/visiting-parliament/uk-youth-parliament.htm |archivedate=February 28, 2009 }}</ref> making it one of only two organisations to ever use the venue for non-Parliamentary proceedings, the other being the English Speaking Union for their International Mace Final on 12 May 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/devon/7371723.stm\n |title=Youth Parliament debate in Lords |publisher=BBC News |date=2008-04-28 |accessdate=2009-03-16 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/06_02_08_stormlords.html |title=Young People Set to Storm House of Lords |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |date=2008-02-06 |accessdate=2009-03-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722151948/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/06_02_08_stormlords.html |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref> The event was chaired by the [[Lord Speaker]] [[Baroness Hayman]] and was broadcast on [[BBC Parliament]].\n\nThe debates held were:\n* Recycling and the [[Natural environment|environment]]\n* National transport concession for young people\n* [[Top-up fees|Abolish university tuition fees]]\n* [[Fear of youth|Fair representation of young people]] in the media\n* [[Votes at 16|Lowering the voting age to 16]]\n* Whether the amount of [[betting stores]] should be restricted.  \n* Single age of adulthood\n\n=== House of Commons debates ===\n\n==== 2007\u201309 ====\nPrime Minister [[Gordon Brown]] suggested that members of the UK Youth Parliament could have annual access to the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] chamber in 2007,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2007/03_07_07_gordonbrown.html |title=Gordon Brown calls for greater role for the UK Youth Parliament in constitutional reform |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |date=2007-07-03 |accessdate=2009-03-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722152020/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2007/03_07_07_gordonbrown.html |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref> but this did not come about until March 2009, when a motion was passed<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/2009/mar/17/youngpeople-houseofcommons|title=Smells like teen spirit: youths to sit in the Commons|last=Sparrow|first=Andrew|date=17 March 2009 |work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref> to allow the UK Youth Parliament to use the House of Commons for that year's annual meeting. However, a Conservative Member of Parliament objected, which forced a vote to be taken on the issue, also employing a procedure called \"[[Strangers (Parliament of the United Kingdom)|I spy strangers]]\" (historically used to expel disruptive spectators, but now mostly to disrupt the House's business)<ref name=\"ispystrangers\">{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/glossary/?gl=180|title=TheyWorkForYou.com glossary: I Spy Strangers|accessdate=18 March 2009}}</ref> to take business in the House beyond 7:00pm and stifle any possible debate on the issue. On 12 March, a second debate was held in the House of Commons with a vote set to be taken four days later.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.politics.co.uk/mps/press-releases/party-politics/labour/sharon-hodgson-mp-slams-tory-\u2018dinosaurs\u2019-over-uk-youth-parliament-debate-$1280028.htm\n |title=Sharon Hodgson MP slams Tory \"dinosaurs\" over UK Youth Parliament debate |publisher=Politics.co.uk |date=2009-03-12 |accessdate=2009-03-16 }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theyworkforyou.com/debates/?id=2009-03-12a.528.0\n |title=House of Commons debates |publisher=TheyWorkForYou.com |date=2009-03-12 |accessdate=2009-03-16 }}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2009, 189 [[Member of Parliament|Members of Parliament]] voted to allow the UK Youth Parliament to debate in the House of Commons, with 16 votes of opposition by Conservative [[backbencher]]s. It was the first time in history that the House of Commons chamber was used by a group other than MPs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/7947335.stm\n |title=Youth to meet in Commons chamber |publisher=BBC News |date=2009-03-16 |accessdate=2009-03-17 }}</ref>\n\nAn online vote was held from July to determine the debate topics, which were:\n* [[Top-up fees|Abolish university tuition fees]]\n* [[Juvenile delinquency|Youth crime]] and how to tackle it\n* [[Concessionary Bus Travel Act 2007|Free transport for over 60s]], but not for young people\n* [[Capitalism]], [[Late-2000s recession|the economy]] and job opportunities for young people\n* [[Voting age#Chronology of lowering the voting age to 16|Lowering the voting age to 16]]\n\n{{Rquote|right|At 16, we can marry our MP, we can sleep with our MP and we can have children with our MP. We can sign up in preparation for fighting and potentially dying for our MP. And suddenly we are not mature enough to vote for them. What an absolute disgrace!|James Evans MYP|{{cite hansard | url=http://www.parliament.the-stationery-office.co.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/youth/debtext/91030.htm#09110254000236 | house=House of Commons | date=30 October 2009 | column=33 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110604193952/http://www.parliament.the-stationery-office.co.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/youth/debtext/91030.htm#09110254000236 | archivedate=4 June 2011 }}}}\nThe debates took place in the House of Commons chamber on Friday 30 October 2009, from 11am to 3:30pm. The session was recorded in [[Hansard]], and the morning debates were broadcast on BBC Parliament the same day. The final two debates were televised later in the week.\n\nThe debates were chaired by [[John Bercow]], Speaker of the House of Commons, who closed the event with a dramatic speech to MYPs in which he described the [[British National Party]] as \"a poison which we could well do without\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8333161.stm|title=Speaker attacks \"poison\" of BNP |date=30 October 2009|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref> The Speaker is usually expected to remain impartial, so as not to compromise his authority, but in this case was able to express personal opinion because the ornamental mace that indicates Parliament is sitting was not in place.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/bercow-breaks-convention-to-attack-bnp-1812274.html|title=Bercow breaks convention to attack BNP|last=Savage|first=Michael|date=31 October 2009|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=28 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n==== 2010 ====\nIn 2010 a debate was held to disuses the possibility of the youth parliament returning for a second sitting.  This resulted in the decision to allow their return not only for that year, but every year for the remainder of the sitting of the current parliament.\n\nUKYP's 2010 Debate took place on 29 October, again chaired by [[John Bercow]], Speaker of the House of Commons with the topics chosen for debate being selected from an Online Ballot. It was broadcast live on Parliament's Website & BBC Parliament.\n\nAs reported on the UK Youth Parliament's official website, the results of the five issues that were debated are listed as follows:\n*Should sex and relationships education be compulsory from primary school onwards? FOR-211 and AGAINST-104 \n*Should university tuition fees rise? FOR-57 and AGAINST-267\n*Should the school leaving age be raised to 18 immediately in order to lower youth unemployment? FOR-56 and AGAINST-271 \n*Should we withdraw all British troops from Afghanistan by 2012? FOR-137 and AGAINST-179 \n*Should reduced transport fares for young people be protected from spending cuts? FOR-239 and AGAINST-80\n\nTherefore, \"Should reduced transport fares for young people be protected from spending cuts?\" became UKYP's National Campaign for 2011.\n\n==== 2011 ====\nIn 2011, the Members of Youth Parliament again debated in the House of Commons on 4 November. This time five topics were chosen by over 65,000 young people. The event was chaired by [[John Bercow]], Speaker of the House of Commons, after his persistence in supporting the youth parliament. The sitting was broadcast on [[BBC Parliament]] but this time live from 11:00am \u2013 4:00pm.\n\nFollowing the debates, the motion entitled 'Make public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all' was chosen as UKYP's National Campaign for 2012.\n\n==== 2012 ====\nIn 2012 and for the fourth time, Members of UKYP gathered in the House of Commons on 23 November, with the topics again being chosen through the Make Your Ballot. There was a large increase in turnout. From 65,000 in 2011, over 253,000 took part to choose the five topics that were debated. Again it was chaired by John Bercow, Speaker of the House of Commons, and was broadcast live via Parliament's Website & BBC Parliament from 11:00-16:00. \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 received 154 votes from the 295 cast and therefore became UKYP's 2013 National Campaign.\n\n==== 2013 ====\nIn 2013, Members of UKYP came together for the fifth year in a row to debate on the green benches on 15 November, the top five issues chosen through the Make Your Mark Ballot. A record 478,386 young people took part, an increase of over 225,000 from 2012. In a difference to choosing campaigns, Members of UKYP chose two campaigns for 2014; one UK-wide issue and one devolved issue (England only). It was chaired like the other debates by John Bercow, Speaker of the House of Commons, and broadcast live on Parliament's Website & BBC Parliament from 11:00-16:00.\n\nFollowing the debates in which [[Nick Hurd]] MP, then Minister for Civil Society stated that 'Old shouldn't dominate politics', \u2018Votes For 16 and 17 Year Olds In All Public Elections\u2019 was prioritised as the UK Priority Campaign for 2014, whilst \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 was voted as the priority campaign for England.\n\n==== 2014 ====\nThe 2014 UKYP sitting in the House of Commons took place on 14 November with the biggest media attention in the sitting's six-year history. Once more chaired by John Bercow, Speaker of the House of Commons, the topics were chosen through 876,488 ballots, around 14.8% of the UK's 11-18-year-old population. The proceedings were broadcast on Parliament's website as tradition but were only shown through the [[BBC]] via their Democracy Live Site; the reason for this was due to the [[Scottish National Party]]'s Annual Autumn Conference commencing that day. However, it was broadcast between 20:20-00:00 on [[BBC Parliament]] that day to give chance for viewers to watch if they couldn't watch online. Also, for the first time the event was covered by [[Sky News]] on the world's biggest video sharing site, [[YouTube]] through their 'Stand Up Be Counted' campaign, which was launched in the summer of 2014.\n\nBefore the debates on campaigns occurred, MYPs held a special commemoration marking the 100th anniversary of the start of [[World War I]]. Thirteen MYPs were selected by a video application process to speak from the Dispatch Boxes on how the war affected either their families of region followed by one minute of silence. This was agreed on at UKYP's Annual Sitting in Lancaster that summer.\n\nOnce the debates and speeches from [[Leader of the House of Commons]], [[William Hague]], [[Natascha Engel]] MP and [[Tessa Munt]] MP had taken place, the following information shows the results of the two votes; one for the UK-wide 2015 issue and like 2013's debate, one devolved issue for England:\n\nUK-wide issue: \n*Everyone should be paid at least the Living Wage: 156 \n*Votes for 16- and 17-year-olds in all public elections: 117\n\nEngland-wide issue:\n*Mental health services should be improved with our help: 176\n*Better work experience and careers advice: 78\n*Bring back exam resits in English and Maths: 32\n\nTherefore, 'Everyone should be paid at least the Living Wage' was chosen as UKYP's UK Campaign for 2015 whiles 'Mental Health services should be improved by our help' became UKYP's 2015 Campaign for England.\n\n==== 2015 ====\n\nThe 2015 sitting took place on 13 November, following the counting of 969,992 Make Your Mark Ballots that were cast through the ballot.\n\nAfter the debates occurred, a special 30 minute debate entitled \"My Magna Carta\" was held, 800 years after the historic document was first signed.\n\nThe information below states the results of the ballots, to choose what of the debated topics would become the two priority campaigns for 2016:\n\nUK Wide:\n\n\u2022\tWorking together to combat racism and religious discrimination: 155\n\n\u2022\tEveryone should be paid at least the Living Wage: 117\n\nTackling Racism and Religious Discrimination therefore became the UK Wide campaign for 2016, and became the inquiry subject for the year's Youth Select Committee.\n\nDevolved:\n\n\u2022\tMental health services should be improved with our help: 176\n\n\u2022\tA curriculum to prepare us for life: 110\n\n\u2022\tMake public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all: 33\n\nThe existing Mental Health campaign was therefore re-selected as the devolved campaign for 2016.\n\n==== 2019 Sitting - amongst the General Election campaign ====\n\nDespite the calling of the [[2019 United Kingdom general election]], the sitting still went ahead and took place on November 8th 2019. The debates were chaired for the first time by both the new Speaker [[Lindsay Hoyle | Sir Lindsay Hoyle]] and fellow speakership candidate and current 1st Deputy Speaker [[Eleanor Laing | Dame Eleanor Laing]]. \n\nAs has been for each sitting, the Make Your Mark ballot determined the topics and overall saw just over 840,000 young people take part across the United Kingdom in 2019, with the motion on Protecting the Environment becoming the parliament's UK wise campaign for 2020 and Ending Knife Crime being chosen by MYP's as the devolved campaign topic.\n\nThe full results were as follows:\n\n'''UK Wide Campaign Topic'''\n\nProtecting the Climate - 179\n\nTackling Hate Crime - 68\n\n'''Devolved Campaign Topic'''\n\nMental Health - 69\n\nCurriculum to Prepare us for Life - 86\n\nPut an End to Knife Crime - 87\n\nFor the first time, the UK wide campaign topic will be launched as a Parliamentary E-Petition of which will be debated in the Commons chamber, if 100,000 members of the public sign it. The petition will be launched in early 2020.\n\nDue to dissolution of Parliament and it having taken place on November 6th 2019 (being prior to November 8th's proceedings), full broadcasting of the debates along with the publication of media reports, under election regulations were not published until 16th December 2019 - the week following the election. Full proceedings were made available on Parliament's YouTube channel that morning.\n\n==== Paul Boskett Memorial Trophy ====\n\nIn 2014 the introduction of the Paul Boskett Debate Lead Trophy was introduced. Every region elects someone to represent them and speak at the Dispatch Box and the strongest speaker is now awarded; the name comes from the late Paul Boskett MBE, who died in 2014 aged 59; he worked and was a lead figure within the [[British Youth Council]]. Paul is cited as a major inspiration for many young people and seen as a key champion of youth voice. The first Debate Lead Champion was Ife Grillo who sat as a Vice Chair to the British Youth Council between 2015-2017 and at the time of the Commons debate on 14 November 2014, represented the London Borough of Hackney.\n\n== Regional ==\nMembers of Youth Parliament in England are split into nine geographical regions, which meet and work together regularly: [[London]], [[East Midlands]], [[West Midlands (region)|West Midlands]], [[South West England|South West]], [[South East England|South East]], [[North West England|North West]], [[North East England|North East]], [[Yorkshire and the Humber]], [[East of England]].\n\nRegional meetings known as conventions take place three times a year (June, October and December) and last around a day. Members share news, issues and resources, in addition to taking part in training to help them in their role, relevant Government Consultations and within the October Convention, Elections occur to decide regional representatives to be a Debate Lead for UKYP's House of Commons Debate and the UKYP Procedure's Group for the following year (1 February to 31 January).\n\n== Campaigns ==\nThe UK Youth Parliament launched the \"Make Your Mark\" ballot in 2011. The purpose of the ballot to get young people from across the UK to determine which five topics the UK Youth Parliament would debate within the House of Commons. Over 65,000 young people completed the ballot after several months of campaigning.\n\nThe first five issues debated in the House of Commons chamber through 'Make Your Mark' were:\n# \"Make public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all\"\n# \"No to tuition fees, yes to graduate tax\"\n# \"Zero tolerance towards bullying in schools\"\n# \"End child poverty\"\n# \"A Greener future for Britain\"\n\nOn 4 November 2011, Members of Youth Parliament came from across the UK to debate and vote at House of Commons the most important issue to campaign on in 2012. The winning campaign topic was \"Make public transport cheaper, better and accessible for all\".\n\n2012's sitting chose \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 as the 2013 National Campaign. Over 253,000 young people took part.\n\nIn 2013, \u2018Votes For 16 and 17 Year Old's In All Public Elections\u2019 was prioritised as the UK Priority Campaign for 2014, whilst \u2018A Curriculum To Prepare Us For Life\u2019 was voted as the priority campaign for England. A new record of 478,386 young people cast a vote.\n\nIn 2014  876,488 young people helped to choose the House of Commons topics; over 14.8% of the UK's 11-18 year old population. 'Everyone should be paid at least the Living Wage' was chosen as UKYP's UK Campaign for 2015 with a National Campaign Day occurring on 24 January 2015. Also 'Mental Health services should be improved by our help' became UKYP's 2015 Campaign for England.\n\n2015 recorded 969,992 votes and saw that year's Commons Debate select Mental Health chosen as the England Campaign issue and Tackling Racism & Discrimination as the UK priority topic to campaign on.\n\n2016 saw another increase in MYM's total, with 978,216 having there say and as a result of that year's debates on the famous Green Benches, saw Votes at 16 be selected as the England campaign issue and a Curriculum for Life for the 2nd time be the national priority campaign topic.\n\nIn 2017, the Make Your Mark for the first time in the ballot's history fell, to 954,766 - of which however was widely still seen as an impressive total considering the scale of Youth Provision cuts since 2010. Both issues chosen in 2016, of a Curriculum for Life and Votes at 16 were once again selected by MYP's to be the priority campaign topics, however with them being switched in relation to the campaign area, meaning Votes at 16 took national precedent and a Curriculum for Life reverted to England only focus.\n\n2018's Ballot has written history and seen a initial total of 1,022,286 votes be declared, marking the first time Make Your Mark has exceeded 7 figures; with an increased and revised 2nd total to be announced on 24 October 2018, along with the Commons Debate topics for this year's proceedings - to be held on 9 November 2018.\n\n== Organisation ==\n\n=== Governance ===\n\n==== Steering Group ====\nDecisions regarding the development and progression of the organisation is undertaken by the Steering Group, made up of one MYP elected from each region and nation (known as \"SGs\"), for a 12-month term from 1 February to 31 January the following year. Their main focus is \"key decisions relating to the membership and the programme of work, within the given strategic boundaries\".<ref name=\"Accounts2008\">{{cite web |url=http://www.charity-commission.gov.uk/registeredcharities/ScannedAccounts/Ends16%5C0001084716_ac_20080331_e_c.pdf|title=Democracy for Young People Accounts 31 Mar 2008|publisher=[[Charity Commission]]|pages=4|accessdate=2009-11-03}}{{dead link|date=October 2017|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}} </ref>\n\nThey meet a minimum of four times a year to represent their regions nationally, coordinate campaign efforts and organise events such as the Annual Conference. Reports are taken back to MYPs at their regional conventions & other meetings.\n\nThe name of the group was changed from Procedures Group to Steering Group in November 2019 in order to reflect the groups varied responsibilities better.\n\n==== Management and support ====\n \nThe [[British Youth Council]] manages the UK Youth Parliament. The British Youth Council won a bid in 2011, granted by the [[Department for Education]] to lead a national Youth Voice Service. Youth Voice will support young people in influencing local and national Government decision making in England, and provide continued support for the UK Youth Parliament.\n\nThe corporate and administrative governance is overseen by the Board of Trustees of the [[British Youth Council]].\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Praise ===\nThe organisation has been endorsed by former Prime Ministers [[Gordon Brown]] and [[David Cameron]]. It has also been endorsed by former [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] Party Leader and former Deputy Prime Minister [[Nick Clegg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.epolitix.com/stakeholder-websites/stakeholder-website-page/sites/uk-youth-parliament/\n |title=UK Youth Parliament |publisher=ePoliticx |accessdate=2009-04-27 }}</ref> In 2009, Brown described the UK Youth Parliament as \"a symbol of the politics we should all strive for - politics that bring people together to work for what is best for us all.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.number10.gov.uk/Page21138|title=Youth Parliament takes over Commons|date=30 October 2009|publisher=[[10 Downing Street]]|accessdate=2009-11-03|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091101012234/http://www.number10.gov.uk/Page21138|archivedate=1 November 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn 2006, the organisation's Head of Programmes Kate Parish was given a [[National Council for Voluntary Youth Services]] Award, for her \"commendable dedication to the development of UK Youth Parliament\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ncvys.org.uk/UserFiles/File/News/Press%20Releases/NCVYS%20Press%20Release_VYOs%20debate%20key%20issues%20around%20faith%20and%20young%20people_22.10.07.pdf|title=Voluntary Youth Organisations debate key issues around faith and young people in society at the NCVYS annual conference|date=22 October 2007|publisher=National Council for Voluntary Youth Services|accessdate=2009-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721121041/http://www.ncvys.org.uk/UserFiles/File/News/Press%20Releases/NCVYS%20Press%20Release_VYOs%20debate%20key%20issues%20around%20faith%20and%20young%20people_22.10.07.pdf#|archive-date=2011-07-21|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, the UK Youth Parliament was given the Positive Images award by the ''[[Children & Young People Now]]'' magazine for exposing young people\u2019s experiences of the current levels of sex and relationships education in a high-profile publicity campaign.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/13_06_08_award.html |title=UK Youth Parliament Scoops Another Award! |accessdate=2008-06-13 |date=2009-03-16 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722152010/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2008/13_06_08_award.html |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref> In 2009, the organisation also received a Brook special achievement award for this campaign.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2009/25_03_09_brookaward.html |title=UK Youth Parliament wins Brook special achievement award for SRE campaign! |accessdate=2009-02-25 |date=2009-05-01 |publisher=UK Youth Parliament |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090704223936/http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk/newsroom_site/pages/news/2009/25_03_09_brookaward.html |archivedate=2009-07-04 }}</ref>\n\n=== Criticism ===\nMYPs co-signed an open letter with public figures including [[Davina McCall]] and [[Polly Toynbee]] to ''[[The Times]]''. The letter protested against the lack of sufficient [[Sex education|sex and relationships education]] in schools, and that the UK Youth Parliament believe that this has led to increasing [[teenage pregnancy]].{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\nA study by the [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado]] found that youth participation organisations in the UK, including the UK Youth Parliament, needed to \"tackle the unintentional practice of [[tokenism]]\". The paper concludes that \"failing to act upon [young people's] opinions \nor take them very seriously\" once they are identified is often a cause of frustration amongst participants.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Youth Participation in the UK: Bureaucratic Disaster or Triumph of Child Rights?|journal=Children, Youth and Environments|year=2006|first=Emily|last=Middleton|volume=16|issue=2|pages=11|url=http://www.colorado.edu/journals/cye/16_2/16_2_12_YouthParticipationUK.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111217044158/http://www.colorado.edu/journals/cye/16_2/16_2_12_YouthParticipationUK.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=2011-12-17|accessdate=2008-11-14}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Commonscat|UK youth parliament}}\n*[[Scottish Youth Parliament]]\n*[[Welsh Youth Parliament]]\n*[[Youth politics]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.ukyouthparliament.org.uk Official website]\n{{UK Youth Parliament}}\n{{Youth empowerment}}\n\n[[Category:Youth model government]]\n[[Category:Youth-led organizations]]\n[[Category:Political organisations based in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Youth empowerment organizations]]\n[[Category:1999 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Charities based in London]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in the London Borough of Hackney]]\n[[Category:Youth organisations based in England]]\n", "name_user": "Cameronwhodds", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRegional", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UK_Youth_Parliament"}
{"title_page": "French Academy of Sciences", "text_new": "{{short description|Acad\u00e9mie des sciences, founded in 1666 by Louis XIV}}\n{{For|the National Academy of Medicine|Acad\u00e9mie Nationale de M\u00e9decine}}\n{{refimprove|date=February 2013}}\n[[File:Colbert Presenting the Members of the Royal Academy of Sciences to Louis XIV in 1667.PNG|thumb|right|''Colbert Presenting the Members of the Royal Academy of Sciences to Louis XIV in 1667'', by [[Henri Testelin]]; in the background appears the new [[Paris Observatory]]]]\n\nThe '''French Academy of Sciences''' (French: ''Acad\u00e9mie des sciences'') is a [[learned society]], founded in 1666 by [[Louis XIV of France|Louis XIV]] at the suggestion of [[Jean-Baptiste Colbert]], to encourage and protect the spirit of French [[Scientific method|scientific research]]. It was at the forefront of scientific developments in Europe in the 17th and 18th centuries, and is one of the earliest [[Academy of Sciences|Academies of Sciences]].\n\nCurrently headed by [[S\u00e9bastien Candel]]{{Fix|name={{{name|out of date?}}}|link=Wikipedia:Updating information|text=out of date?}} (President of the Academy), it is one of the five Academies of the [[Institut de France]].<ref name=\"institut\">{{cite web |title=Les Acad\u00e9mies |url=http://www.institut-de-france.fr/fr/une-institution/les-acad\u00e9mies |website=Institut de France |accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n[[Image:Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences 1698.jpg|thumb|left|240px|<center>A heroic depiction of the activities of the Academy from 1698</center>]]\nThe Academy of Sciences traces its origin to Colbert's plan to create a general academy. He chose a small group of scholars who met on 22 December 1666 in the King's library, near the present-day [[Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France|Biblioth\u00e8que Nationals]], and thereafter held twice-weekly working meetings there in the two rooms assigned to the group.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Watson|first=E.|date=1939|title=The Early Days of the Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences as Portrayed in the Engravings of S\u00e9bastien Le Clerc|url=|journal=Osiris|volume=7|pages=556\u2013587|doi=10.1086/368508|via=JSTOR}}</ref> The first 30 years of the Academy's existence were relatively informal, since no statutes had as yet been laid down for the institution.  In contrast to [[Royal Society|its British counterpart]], the Academy was founded as an organ of government. In Paris, there weren't many membership openings, to fill positions there were tenacious elections.<ref name=\":0\" /> The Academy was expected to remain apolitical, and to avoid discussion of religious and social issues.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hahn |first1=Roger |title=Anatomy of a Scientific Institution: The Paris Academy of Sciences, 1666-1803 |date=1971 |publisher=University of California Press |location=Berkeley, California |isbn=0-520-01818-4 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/1 1-34] |url=https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/1 }}</ref> The election process was at least a 6 stage process with rules and regulations that allowed for chosen candidates to canvas other members and for current members to consider postponing certain stages of the process if the need would arise.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|date=1978|title=The French Academy of Sciences in the Nineteenth Century|url=|journal=Minerva|volume=16|pages=78-79|via=JSTOR}}</ref>\n[[File:S\u00e9bastien Leclerc I, Louis XIV Visiting the Royal Academy of Sciences, 1671.jpg|thumb|right|[[Louis XIV]] Visiting the Royal Academy of Sciences, (S\u00e9bastien Leclerc I, France, 1671)]]\nOn 20 January 1699, Louis XIV gave the Company its first rules. The Academy received the name of '''Royal Academy of Sciences''' and was installed in the [[Louvre]] in Paris. Following this reform, the Academy began publishing a volume each year with information on all the work done by its members and obituaries for members who had died. This reform also codified the method by which members of the Academy could receive pensions for their work.<ref>{{cite book|editor1-last=Moak|editor1-first=David|title=The Encyclopedia of Diderot & d'Alembert Collaborative Translation Project.|date=2007|publisher=Michigan Publishing, University of Michigan LIbrary|location=Ann Arbor|pages=54\u201355|hdl=2027/spo.did2222.0000.874}}</ref>  The academy was originally organized by the royal reform hierarchically into the following groups: Pensionaires, Pupils, Honoraires, and Associ\u00e9s. The reform also added new groups not previously recognized, such as V\u00e9t\u00e9ran. Some of these role's member limits were expanded and some roles even removed or combined throughout the course of academy's history.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=84|via=JSTOR}}</ref> Membership in the academy only exceeded 100 officially recognized full members in 1976, 310 years after the academy's inception in 1666.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=86|via=JSTOR}}</ref> On 8 August 1793, the [[National Convention]] abolished all the academies. On 22 August 1795, a '''National Institute of Sciences and Arts''' was put in place, bringing together the old academies of the sciences, literature and arts, among them the [[Acad\u00e9mie fran\u00e7aise]] and the Acad\u00e9mie des sciences. Also in 1795, The Academy determined these 10 titles to be their newly accepted branches of scientific study:\n\n# Mathematics\n# Mechanics\n# Astronomy\n# Physics\n# Chemistry\n# Minerolgy\n# Botony\n# Agriculture\n# Anatomy and Zoology\n# Medicine and Surgery. <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|date=Apr 2007|title=The French Academy of Sciences As a Patron of the Medical  Sciences in the Early Nineteenth Century|url=|journal=Annals of Science|volume=|pages=|via=Academic Search Premier}}</ref>\n\nThe last two sections are bundled since there were many good candidates fit to be elected for those practices, and the competition was stiff. Some individuals like [[Fran\u00e7ois Magendie|Francois Magendie]] had made stellar advancements in their selected fields of study, that warranted a possible addition of new fields. However, even someone like Magendie that had made breakthroughs in [[Physiology]] and impressed the Academy with his hands-on [[vivisection]] experiments, could not get his study into its own category.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fran%C3%A7ois_Magendie|title=Fran\u00e7ois Magendie|last=|first=|date=|website=wikipedia.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Despite Magendie being one of the leading innovators of his time, it was still a battle for him to become an official member of the Academy, a feat he would later accomplish in 1821.<ref name=\":0\" /> He further improved the reverence of the academy when he produced the widely known \"[[Bell\u2013Magendie law|Bell-Magendie Law]]\". \u00a0\n\nFrom 1795 until 1914, the first world war, the French Academy of Science was the most prevalent organization of French science.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite journal|last=Alter|first=Peter|date=June 1995|title=Science under Control. The French Academy of Sciences|url=|journal=The English Historical Review|volume=110|pages=783|via=}}</ref> Almost all the old members of the previously abolished Acad\u00e9mie were formally re-elected and retook their ancient seats. Among the exceptions was [[Dominique, comte de Cassini]], who refused to take his seat. Membership in the Academy was not restricted to scientists: in 1798 [[Napoleon Bonaparte]] was elected a member of the Academy and three years later a president in connection with his [[Napoleonic Campaign in Egypt|Egyptian expedition]], which had a scientific component.<ref name=\"alder\">{{citation\n|first=Ken\n|last=Alder\n|title=The Measure of All Things \u2013 The Seven-Year Odyssey and Hidden Error that Transformed the World\n|publisher=[[Free Press (publisher)|The Free Press]]\n|year=2002\n|isbn=0-7432-1675-X\n|url-access=registration\n|url=https://archive.org/details/measureofallthin00alde\n}}</ref> In 1816, the again renamed \"Royal Academy of Sciences\" became autonomous, while forming part of the [[Institute of France]]; the head of State became its patron. In the [[French Second Republic|Second Republic]], the name returned to Acad\u00e9mie des sciences. During this period, the Academy was funded by and accountable to the [[Minister of National Education (France)|Ministry of Public Instruction]].<ref>{{harvnb|Crosland|1992}}</ref>\nThe Academy came to control French patent laws in the course of the eighteenth century, acting as the liaison of artisans' knowledge to the public domain. As a result, [[academician]]s dominated technological activities in France.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hahn |first1=Roger |title=The Anatomy of a Scientific Institution: The Paris Academy of Sciences, 1666-1803 |date=1971 |publisher=University of California Press |location=Berkeley, California |isbn=0-520-01818-4 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/187 187-189] |url=https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/187 }}</ref>\nThe Academy proceedings were published under the name ''[[Comptes rendus de l'Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences]]'' (1835\u20131965). The ''Comptes rendus'' is now a journal series with seven titles. The publications can be found on site of the [[Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France|French National Library]].\n\nIn 1818 the French Academy of Sciences launched a competition to explain the properties of light. The civil engineer [[Augustin-Jean Fresnel]] entered this competition by submitting a new [[wave theory of light]].<ref name=\"fresnel1868\">{{Citation \n| last = Fresnel | first = A.J.\n| year =1868\n| title = OEuvres Completes 1\n| publisher = Imprimerie imp\u00e9riale\n| location = Paris\n| url = https://books.google.com/books/about/%C5%92uvres_compl%C3%A8tes_d_Augustin_Fresnel_Th.html?id=3QgAAAAAMAAJ\n}}</ref> [[Sim\u00e9on Denis Poisson]], one of the members of the judging committee, studied Fresnel's theory in detail. Being a supporter of the particle-theory of light, he looked for a way to disprove it. Poisson thought that he had found a flaw when he demonstrate that Fresnel's theory predicts that an on-axis bright spot would exist in the shadow of a circular obstacle, where there should be complete darkness according to the particle-theory of light. The [[Poisson spot]] is not easily observed in every-day situations, so it was only natural for Poisson to interpret it as an absurd result and that it should disprove Fresnel's theory. However, the head of the committee, [[Fran\u00e7ois Arago|Dominique-Fran\u00e7ois-Jean Arago]], and who incidentally later became Prime Minister of France, decided to perform the experiment in more detail. He molded a 2-mm metallic disk to a glass plate with wax.<ref name=\"fresnel1868_arago\">{{Citation \n| last = Fresnel | first = A.J.\n| year =1868\n| title = OEuvres Completes 1\n| publisher = Imprimerie imp\u00e9riale\n| location = Paris\n| page = 369\n| url = https://books.google.com/books/about/%C5%92uvres_compl%C3%A8tes_d_Augustin_Fresnel_Th.html?id=3QgAAAAAMAAJ\n}}</ref> To everyone's surprise he succeeded in observing the predicted spot, which convinced most scientists of the wave-nature of light.\n[[File:Acta Eruditorum - I orologi, 1737 \u2013 BEIC 13458392.jpg|thumb|Illustration from [[Acta Eruditorum]] (1737) where was published ''Machines et inventions approuv\u00e9es par l'Academie Royale des Sciences'']]\nFor three centuries women were not allowed as members of the Academy. This meant that many women scientists were excluded, including two-time Nobel Prize winner [[Marie Curie]], Nobel winner [[Ir\u00e8ne Joliot-Curie]], mathematician [[Sophie Germain]], and many other deserving women scientists. The first woman admitted as a correspondent member was a student of Curie's, [[Marguerite Perey]], in 1962.  The first female full member was [[Yvonne Choquet-Bruhat]] in 1979. {{Citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n\nMembership in the academy is highly geared towards representing common [[Demographics of France|French populace demographics]]. French population increases and changes in the early 21st century lead to the academy expanding reference population sizes by reform in the early 2002.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=86|via=JSTOR}}</ref>\n\nThe overwhelming majority of members leave the academy posthumously, with a few exceptions of removals, transfers, and resignations. The last member to be removed from the academy was in 1944. Removal from the academy was often for not preforming to standards, not preforming at all, leaving the country, or political reasons. In some rare occasions, a member has been elected twice and subsequently removed twice. This is the case for [[Marie-Adolphe Carnot]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=90|via=JSTOR}}</ref>\n\n== Government Interference ==\nThe most direct involvement of the government in the affairs of the institute came in the initial nomination of members in 1795. But as the members nominated constituted only one third of the membership and most of these had previously been elected as members of the respective Academies under the old regime, few objections were raised. Moreover, these nominated members were then completely free to nominate the remaining members of the institute. Members expected to remain such for life, but interference occurred in a few cases where the government suddenly terminated membership for political reasons. The other main interference came when the government refused to accept the result of Academy elections.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|title=Science Under Control The French Academy of Sciences 1795-1914|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1992|isbn=0521413737|location=Great Britain|pages=303}}</ref> The academies control by the government was apparent in 1803, when Bonaparte decided on a general reorganization. His principal concern was not the First class but the Second, which included political scientists who were potential critics of his government. Bonaparte abolished the second class completely and, after a few expulsions, redistributed its remaining members, together with those of the Third class, into a new Second class concerned with literature and a new Third class devoted to the fine arts. Still this relationship between the Academy and the government wasn't a one way affair, as members expected to receive their payment of an honorarium.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|title=Science Under Control The French Academy of Sciences 1795-1914|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1992|isbn=0521413737|location=Great Britain|pages=302}}</ref>\n\n== Decline of the Academy ==\nAlthough the Academy still exists today, after World war one, the reputation and status of the Academy was largely questioned.<ref name=\":1\" /> One factor of decline was the development from a meritocracy to gerontocracy, in other words; a shift from people with scientific ability leading the Academy to people who had been there longer leading it.<ref name=\":1\" /> It became known as a sort of \u201chall of fame\u201d that lost control, real and symbolic, of the professional scientific diversity in France at the time.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== The Academy today ==\n[[Image:Institut France.jpg|thumb|right|<center>The [[Institut de France]] in Paris where the Academy is housed</center>]]\nToday the Academy is one of five academies comprising the [[Institut de France]]. Its members are elected for life. Currently there are 150 full members, 300 corresponding members, and 120 foreign associates. They are divided into two scientific groups: the [[Mathematics|Mathematical]] and [[Physics|Physical]] sciences and their applications and the [[Chemistry|Chemical]], [[Biology|Biological]], Geological and Medical sciences and their applications. The Academy currently has five missions that its pursuing. These being the encouraging of the scientific life, promoting the teaching of science, transmitting knowledge between scientific communities, fostering international collaborations, and ensuring a dual role of expertise and advise.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/About-us/five-basic-missions-in-the-academy-s-remit.html|title=Five basic missions in the Academy's remit|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The French Academy of Science originally focused its development efforts into creating a true co-development Euro-African program beginning in 1997. Since then they have broadened their scope of action to other regions of the world. The standing committee COPED is in charge of the international development projects undertaken by the French Academy of Science and their associates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/Overview/actions-targeted-towards-development.html|title=Actions Targeted Towards Development|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The current president of COPED is [[Pierre Auger (biologist)|Pierre Auger]], the vice president is [[Michel Delseny]], and the honorary president is [[Fran\u00e7ois Gros|Francois Gros]]. All of which are current members of the French Academy of Science. COPED has hosted several workshops or colloquia in Paris, involving representatives from African academies, universities or Research centers, addressing a variety of themes and challenges dealing with African development and covering a large field spectrum. Specifically higher education in sciences, and research practices in basic and applied sciences that deal with various aspects relevant to development (renewable energy, infectious diseases, animal pathologies,food resources,access to safe water,agriculture,urban health,etc).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/Actions-targeted-towards-development/standing-committee-for-developing-countries-coped.html|title=Standing Committee for Developing Countries|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Current Committees and Working Parties ==\nThe Academic Standing Committees and Working Parties prepare the advice notes, policy statements and the Academic Reports. Some have a statutory remit, such as the Select Committee, the Committee for International Affairs and the Committee for Scientists' Rights, some are created ad hoc by the Academy and approved formally by vote in a Members only session.\n\nToday the academies standing committees and working parties include:\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee in charge of the Biennial Report on Science and Technology\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Science, Ethics and Society\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for the Environment\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Space Research\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Science and Metrology\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for the Science History and Epistemology\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Science and Safety Issues[[File:Pierre auger.jpg|thumb|[[Pierre Auger (biologist)|Pierre Auger]] the current president of COPED<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/Liste-des-membres-de-l-Academie-des-sciences-/-A/pierre-auger.html|title=Pierre Auger|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>]]- The Academic Standing Committee for Science Education and Training\n\n- The Academic Standing La main \u00e0 la p\u00e2te Committee\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for the Defense of Scientists' Rights (CODHOS)\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for International Affairs (CORI)\n\n- The French Committee for International Scientific Unions (COFUSI)\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Scientific and Technological International Relations (CARIST)\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Developing Countries (COPED)\n\n- The Inter-academic Group for Development (GID) - Cf. for further reading\n\n- The Academic Standing Commission for Sealed Deposits\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Terminology and Neologisms\n\n- The Antoine Lavoisier Standing Committee\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Prospects in Energy Procurement\n\n- The Special Academic Working Party on Scientific Computing\n\n- The Special Academic Working Party on Material Sciences and Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/archivage_site/en/comite.htm|title=Academic Standing Committees and Working Parties|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Medals, awards and prizes ==\n\nEach year, the Academy of Sciences distributes about 80 prizes. These include:\n\n* the [[Grande M\u00e9daille]], awarded annually, in rotation, in the relevant disciplines of each division of the Academy, to a French or foreign scholar who has contributed to the development of science in a decisive way.\n* the [[Lalande Prize]], awarded from 1802 through 1970, for outstanding achievement in astronomy\n* the [[Valz Prize]], awarded from 1877 through 1970, to honor advances in astronomy\n* the [[Richard Lounsbery Award]], jointly with the [[United States National Academy of Sciences|National Academy of Sciences]]\n* the Prix [[Jacques Herbrand]], for mathematics and physics\n* the Prix Paul Pascal, for chemistry\n* the [[Louis Bachelier Prize]] for major contributions to mathematical modeling in finance <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/gp_natixis.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-08-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141026191221/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/gp_natixis.htm |archivedate=26 October 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* the Prix Michel Mon{{color|#808080|t}}petit for computer science and applied mathematics, awarded since 1977<ref>[[:fr:Prix Monpetit|French wikipedia article]]; both \"[http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureats_prixthem2011.pdf Monpetit] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110902033652/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureats_prixthem2011.pdf |date=2 September 2011 }}\" and \"[http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureat_montpetit.pdf Mon'''t'''petit] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114130029/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureat_montpetit.pdf |date=14 January 2015 }}\" is found in Academy publications.</ref>\n* the [[Leconte Prize]], awarded annually since 1886, to recognize important discoveries in mathematics, physics, chemistry, natural history or medicine\n* the Prix [[Pyotr Chikhachyov|Tchihatcheff]] (Tchihatchef; Chikhachev)\n\n== People of the Academy ==\n\nThe following are incomplete lists of the officers of the Academy.  See also [[:Category:Officers of the French Academy of Sciences]].\n\nFor a list of the Academy's members past and present, see [[:Category:Members of the French Academy of Sciences]]\n\n=== Presidents ===\nSource: [https://www.academie-sciences.fr/fr/Histoire-de-l-Academie-des-sciences/liste-des-presidents-de-l-academie-des-sciences-de-1699-a-nos-jours.html French Academy of Sciences]\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1800 [[Napoleon Bonaparte]]\n*1906 [[Henri Poincar\u00e9]]\n*1952 [[Albert Caquot]]\n*2001\u20132002 [[Hubert Curien]]\n*2003\u20132004 [[\u00c9tienne-\u00c9mile Baulieu]]\n*2005\u20132006 [[\u00c9douard Br\u00e9zin]]\n*2007\u20132008 [[Jules Hoffmann]]\n*2009\u20132010 [[Jean Salen\u00e7on]]\n*2011-2012 [[Alain Carpentier]] <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.academie-sciences.fr/academie/membre/liste_president.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-02-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112092133/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/academie/membre/liste_president.htm |archivedate=12 November 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n*2013\u20132014 [[Philippe Taquet]]\n*2015-2016 [[Bernard Meunier]]\n*2017-2018 [[S\u00e9bastien Candel]]\n}}\n\n=== Treasurers ===\n* ?\u20131788 [[Georges-Louis Leclerc, Comte de Buffon]]\n* 1788\u20131791 [[Mathieu Tillet]]\n\n=== Permanent secretaries ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* Dec 1666 \u2013 Apr 1668 [[Jean-Baptiste Du Hamel]]\n* Apr 1668 \u2013 Dec 1669 [[Jean Gallois]]\n* Jan 1670 \u2013 Jan 1697 [[Jean-Baptiste Du Hamel]]\n* Jan 1697 \u2013 Dec 1740 [[Bernard le Bovier de Fontenelle]] (nominated by king in Jan 1699)\n* Jan 1741 \u2013 Aug 1743 [[Jean-Jacques Dortous de Mairan]]\n* Sep 1743 \u2013 Jul 1776 [[Jean-Paul Grandjean de Fouchy]]\n* Aug 1777 \u2013 Aug 1793 [[Marquis de Condorcet|Nicolas Caritat, marquis de Condorcet]]\n}}\n=== Mathematical Sciences ===<!-- At some point it is actually mathematical and physical science-->\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1801\u20131822 [[Jean Baptiste Joseph Delambre]]\n*1822\u20131830 [[Joseph Fourier]]\n*1830\u20131853 [[Fran\u00e7ois Arago]]\n*1853\u20131874 [[L\u00e9once \u00c9lie de Beaumont]]\n*1874\u20131900 [[Joseph Bertrand]]\n*1900\u20131917 [[Gaston Darboux]]\n*1917\u20131942 [[\u00c9mile Picard]]\n*1942\u20131975 [[Louis de Broglie]]\n*1975\u20131996 Paul Germain\n*Currently: [[Jean Dercourt]]\n*Currently: [[Odile Macchi]]\n}}\n=== Physical Sciences ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1795\u20131803 [[Bernard Germain de Lac\u00e9p\u00e8de]]\n*1803\u20131832 [[Georges Cuvier]]\n*1832\u20131833 [[Pierre-Louis Dulong]]\n*1833\u20131868 [[Pierre Flourens]]\n*1868\u20131884 [[Jean-Baptiste Dumas]]\n*1884\u20131886 [[Jules Jamin]]\n*1886\u20131887 [[Alfred Vulpian]]\n*1887\u20131889 [[Louis Pasteur]]\n*1889\u20131907 [[Marcelin Berthelot]]\n*1907 [[Albert de Lapparent]]\n*1908 [[Henri Becquerel]]\n*1908\u20131914 [[Philippe van Tieghem]]\n*1914\u20131948 [[Alfred Lacroix]]\n}}\n=== Chemistry and Biology ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1948\u20131986 [[Robert Courrier]]\n*1986\u20131991 [[Alfred Jost]]\n*1991\u20132001 [[Fran\u00e7ois Gros]]\n*2001\u20132006 [[Nicole Le Douarin]]\n*2006-2011 [[Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Bach]]\n*currently [[Catherine Br\u00e9chignac]]\n}}\n== See also ==\n* [[French art salons and academies]]\n* [[French Geodesic Mission]]\n*[[History of the metre]]\n*[[Seconds pendulum]]\n* [[:fr:Cat\u00e9gorie:Membre de l'Acad\u00e9mie des sciences (France)|Cat\u00e9gorie:Membre de l'Acad\u00e9mie des sciences (France)]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{citation|last= Crosland|first= Maurice P.|title= Science Under Control: The French Academy of Sciences, 1795\u20131914  |year= 1992\n|publisher= Cambridge University Press|isbn= 0-521-52475-X}}\n* St\u00e9phane Schmitt, \"Studies on animals and the rise of comparative anatomy at and around the Parisian Royal Academy of Sciences in the eighteenth century,\" Science in Context 29 (1), 2016, p. 11-54. \n*{{citation|title=Royal Funding of the Parisian Acad\u00e9mie Royale Des Sciences During the 1690s|first=Alice|last=Stroup|publisher=DIANE Publishing|year=1987|isbn=0-87169-774-2|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/royalfundingofpa0000stro}}\n*{{citation|title=Science and Social Status: The Members of the Academie Des Sciences 1666\u20131750|first=David J.|last= Sturdy|publisher=Boydell & Brewer |year=1995|isbn=0-85115-395-X}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Acad\u00e9mie des sciences (France)}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.academie-sciences.fr}} {{in lang|fr}} \u2013 [http://www.academie-sciences.fr/en English-language version]\n* [http://www.academie-sciences.fr/academie/membre.htm Complete listing of current members]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060425224502/http://www.scholarly-societies.org/history/1666as.html Notes on the Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences from the Scholarly Societies project] (includes information on the society journals)\n* [http://gallica.bnf.fr Search the Proceedings of the Acad\u00e9mie des sciences in the French National Library (search item: Comptes Rendus)]\n* [http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb34394200t/date ''Comptes rendus de l'Acad\u00e9mie des sciences. S\u00e9rie 1, Math\u00e9matique''] in [[Gallica]], the digital library of the [[BnF]].\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}\n\n{{International Council for Science}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:French Academy of Sciences| ]]\n[[Category:National academies of sciences|France]]\n[[Category:Institut de France|Sciences]]\n[[Category:Members of the Institut de France]]\n[[Category:1666 establishments in France]]\n[[Category:Lists of members of learned societies]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in the 1660s]]\n[[Category:Scientific organizations established in 1666]]\n[[Category:Members of the International Council for Science]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Acad\u00e9mie des sciences, founded in 1666 by Louis XIV}}\n{{For|the National Academy of Medicine|Acad\u00e9mie Nationale de M\u00e9decine}}\n{{refimprove|date=February 2013}}\n[[File:Colbert Presenting the Members of the Royal Academy of Sciences to Louis XIV in 1667.PNG|thumb|right|''Colbert Presenting the Members of the Royal Academy of Sciences to Louis XIV in 1667'', by [[Henri Testelin]]; in the background appears the new [[Paris Observatory]]]]\n\nThe '''French Academy of Sciences''' (French: ''Acad\u00e9mie des sciences'') is a [[learned society]], founded in 1666 by [[Louis XIV of France|Louis XIV]] at the suggestion of [[Jean-Baptiste Colbert]], to encourage and protect the spirit of French [[Scientific method|scientific research]]. It was at the forefront of scientific developments in Europe in the 17th and 18th centuries, and is one of the earliest [[Academy of Sciences|Academies of Sciences]].\n\nCurrently headed by [[S\u00e9bastien Candel]]{{Fix|name={{{name|out of date?}}}|link=Wikipedia:Updating information|text=out of date?}} (President of the Academy), it is one of the five Academies of the [[Institut de France]].<ref name=\"institut\">{{cite web |title=Les Acad\u00e9mies |url=http://www.institut-de-france.fr/fr/une-institution/les-acad\u00e9mies |website=Institut de France |accessdate=4 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n[[Image:Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences 1698.jpg|thumb|left|240px|<center>A heroic depiction of the activities of the Academy from 1698</center>]]\nThe Academy of Sciences traces its origin to Colbert's plan to create a general academy. He chose a small group of scholars who met on 22 December 1666 in the King's library, near the present-day [[Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France|Biblioth\u00e8que Nationals]], and thereafter held twice-weekly working meetings there in the two rooms assigned to the group.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Watson|first=E.|date=1939|title=The Early Days of the Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences as Portrayed in the Engravings of S\u00e9bastien Le Clerc|url=|journal=Osiris|volume=7|pages=556\u2013587|doi=10.1086/368508|via=JSTOR}}</ref> The first 30 years of the Academy's existence were relatively informal, since no statutes had as yet been laid down for the institution.  In contrast to [[Royal Society|its British counterpart]], the Academy was founded as an organ of government. In Paris, there weren't many membership openings, to fill positions there were tenacious elections.<ref name=\":0\" /> The Academy was expected to remain apolitical, and to avoid discussion of religious and social issues.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hahn |first1=Roger |title=Anatomy of a Scientific Institution: The Paris Academy of Sciences, 1666-1803 |date=1971 |publisher=University of California Press |location=Berkeley, California |isbn=0-520-01818-4 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/1 1-34] |url=https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/1 }}</ref> The election process was at least a 6 stage process with rules and regulations that allowed for chosen candidates to canvas other members and for current members to consider postponing certain stages of the process if the need would arise.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|date=1978|title=The French Academy of Sciences in the Nineteenth Century|url=|journal=Minerva|volume=16|pages=78-79|via=JSTOR}}</ref>\n[[File:S\u00e9bastien Leclerc I, Louis XIV Visiting the Royal Academy of Sciences, 1671.jpg|thumb|right|[[Louis XIV]] Visiting the Royal Academy of Sciences, (S\u00e9bastien Leclerc I, France, 1671)]]\nOn 20 January 1699, Louis XIV gave the Company its first rules. The Academy received the name of '''Royal Academy of Sciences''' and was installed in the [[Louvre]] in Paris. Following this reform, the Academy began publishing a volume each year with information on all the work done by its members and obituaries for members who had died. This reform also codified the method by which members of the Academy could receive pensions for their work.<ref>{{cite book|editor1-last=Moak|editor1-first=David|title=The Encyclopedia of Diderot & d'Alembert Collaborative Translation Project.|date=2007|publisher=Michigan Publishing, University of Michigan LIbrary|location=Ann Arbor|pages=54\u201355|hdl=2027/spo.did2222.0000.874}}</ref>  The academy was originally organized by the royal reform hierarchically into the following groups: Pensionaires, Pupils, Honoraires, and Associ\u00e9s. The reform also added new groups not previously recognized, such as V\u00e9t\u00e9ran. Some of these role's member limits were expanded and some roles even removed or combined throughout the course of academy's history.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=84|via=JSTOR}}</ref> Membership in the academy only exceeded 100 officially recognized full members in 1976, 310 years after the academy's inception in 1666.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=86|via=JSTOR}}</ref> On 8 August 1793, the [[National Convention]] abolished all the academies. On 22 August 1795, a '''National Institute of Sciences and Arts''' was put in place, bringing together the old academies of the sciences, literature and arts, among them the [[Acad\u00e9mie fran\u00e7aise]] and the Acad\u00e9mie des sciences. Also in 1795, The Academy determined these 10 titles to be their newly accepted branches of scientific study:\n\n# Mathematics\n# Mechanics\n# Astronomy\n# Physics\n# Chemistry\n# Minerolgy\n# Botony\n# Agriculture\n# Anatomy and Zoology\n# Medicine and Surgery. <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|date=Apr 2007|title=The French Academy of Sciences As a Patron of the Medical  Sciences in the Early Nineteenth Century|url=|journal=Annals of Science|volume=|pages=|via=Academic Search Premier}}</ref>\n\nThe last two sections are bundled since there were many good candidates fit to be elected for those practices, and the competition was stiff. Some individuals like [[Fran\u00e7ois Magendie|Francois Magendie]] had made stellar advancements in their selected fields of study, that warranted a possible addition of new fields. However, even someone like Magendie that had made breakthroughs in [[Physiology]] and impressed the Academy with his hands-on experimentation, could not get his study into its own category.<ref name=\":0\" /> Despite Magendie being one of the leading innovators of his time, it was still a battle for him to become an official member of the Academy, a feat he would later accomplish in 1821.<ref name=\":0\" /> He further improved the reverence of the academy when he produced the widely known \"[[Bell\u2013Magendie law|Bell-Magendie Law]]\". \u00a0\n\nFrom 1795 until 1914, the first world war, the French Academy of Science was the most prevalent organization of French science.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite journal|last=Alter|first=Peter|date=June 1995|title=Science under Control. The French Academy of Sciences|url=|journal=The English Historical Review|volume=110|pages=783|via=}}</ref> Almost all the old members of the previously abolished Acad\u00e9mie were formally re-elected and retook their ancient seats. Among the exceptions was [[Dominique, comte de Cassini]], who refused to take his seat. Membership in the Academy was not restricted to scientists: in 1798 [[Napoleon Bonaparte]] was elected a member of the Academy and three years later a president in connection with his [[Napoleonic Campaign in Egypt|Egyptian expedition]], which had a scientific component.<ref name=\"alder\">{{citation\n|first=Ken\n|last=Alder\n|title=The Measure of All Things \u2013 The Seven-Year Odyssey and Hidden Error that Transformed the World\n|publisher=[[Free Press (publisher)|The Free Press]]\n|year=2002\n|isbn=0-7432-1675-X\n|url-access=registration\n|url=https://archive.org/details/measureofallthin00alde\n}}</ref> In 1816, the again renamed \"Royal Academy of Sciences\" became autonomous, while forming part of the [[Institute of France]]; the head of State became its patron. In the [[French Second Republic|Second Republic]], the name returned to Acad\u00e9mie des sciences. During this period, the Academy was funded by and accountable to the [[Minister of National Education (France)|Ministry of Public Instruction]].<ref>{{harvnb|Crosland|1992}}</ref>\nThe Academy came to control French patent laws in the course of the eighteenth century, acting as the liaison of artisans' knowledge to the public domain. As a result, [[academician]]s dominated technological activities in France.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hahn |first1=Roger |title=The Anatomy of a Scientific Institution: The Paris Academy of Sciences, 1666-1803 |date=1971 |publisher=University of California Press |location=Berkeley, California |isbn=0-520-01818-4 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/187 187-189] |url=https://archive.org/details/anatomyofscienti0000hahn/page/187 }}</ref>\nThe Academy proceedings were published under the name ''[[Comptes rendus de l'Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences]]'' (1835\u20131965). The ''Comptes rendus'' is now a journal series with seven titles. The publications can be found on site of the [[Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France|French National Library]].\n\nIn 1818 the French Academy of Sciences launched a competition to explain the properties of light. The civil engineer [[Augustin-Jean Fresnel]] entered this competition by submitting a new [[wave theory of light]].<ref name=\"fresnel1868\">{{Citation \n| last = Fresnel | first = A.J.\n| year =1868\n| title = OEuvres Completes 1\n| publisher = Imprimerie imp\u00e9riale\n| location = Paris\n| url = https://books.google.com/books/about/%C5%92uvres_compl%C3%A8tes_d_Augustin_Fresnel_Th.html?id=3QgAAAAAMAAJ\n}}</ref> [[Sim\u00e9on Denis Poisson]], one of the members of the judging committee, studied Fresnel's theory in detail. Being a supporter of the particle-theory of light, he looked for a way to disprove it. Poisson thought that he had found a flaw when he demonstrate that Fresnel's theory predicts that an on-axis bright spot would exist in the shadow of a circular obstacle, where there should be complete darkness according to the particle-theory of light. The [[Poisson spot]] is not easily observed in every-day situations, so it was only natural for Poisson to interpret it as an absurd result and that it should disprove Fresnel's theory. However, the head of the committee, [[Fran\u00e7ois Arago|Dominique-Fran\u00e7ois-Jean Arago]], and who incidentally later became Prime Minister of France, decided to perform the experiment in more detail. He molded a 2-mm metallic disk to a glass plate with wax.<ref name=\"fresnel1868_arago\">{{Citation \n| last = Fresnel | first = A.J.\n| year =1868\n| title = OEuvres Completes 1\n| publisher = Imprimerie imp\u00e9riale\n| location = Paris\n| page = 369\n| url = https://books.google.com/books/about/%C5%92uvres_compl%C3%A8tes_d_Augustin_Fresnel_Th.html?id=3QgAAAAAMAAJ\n}}</ref> To everyone's surprise he succeeded in observing the predicted spot, which convinced most scientists of the wave-nature of light.\n[[File:Acta Eruditorum - I orologi, 1737 \u2013 BEIC 13458392.jpg|thumb|Illustration from [[Acta Eruditorum]] (1737) where was published ''Machines et inventions approuv\u00e9es par l'Academie Royale des Sciences'']]\nFor three centuries women were not allowed as members of the Academy. This meant that many women scientists were excluded, including two-time Nobel Prize winner [[Marie Curie]], Nobel winner [[Ir\u00e8ne Joliot-Curie]], mathematician [[Sophie Germain]], and many other deserving women scientists. The first woman admitted as a correspondent member was a student of Curie's, [[Marguerite Perey]], in 1962.  The first female full member was [[Yvonne Choquet-Bruhat]] in 1979. {{Citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n\nMembership in the academy is highly geared towards representing common [[Demographics of France|French populace demographics]]. French population increases and changes in the early 21st century lead to the academy expanding reference population sizes by reform in the early 2002.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=86|via=JSTOR}}</ref>\n\nThe overwhelming majority of members leave the academy posthumously, with a few exceptions of removals, transfers, and resignations. The last member to be removed from the academy was in 1944. Removal from the academy was often for not preforming to standards, not preforming at all, leaving the country, or political reasons. In some rare occasions, a member has been elected twice and subsequently removed twice. This is the case for [[Marie-Adolphe Carnot]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Leridon|first=Henri|date=2004|title=The Demography of a Learned Society: The Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences (Institut de France), 1666-2030|url=|journal=Population|volume=59|pages=90|via=JSTOR}}</ref>\n\n== Government Interference ==\nThe most direct involvement of the government in the affairs of the institute came in the initial nomination of members in 1795. But as the members nominated constituted only one third of the membership and most of these had previously been elected as members of the respective Academies under the old regime, few objections were raised. Moreover, these nominated members were then completely free to nominate the remaining members of the institute. Members expected to remain such for life, but interference occurred in a few cases where the government suddenly terminated membership for political reasons. The other main interference came when the government refused to accept the result of Academy elections.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|title=Science Under Control The French Academy of Sciences 1795-1914|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1992|isbn=0521413737|location=Great Britain|pages=303}}</ref> The academies control by the government was apparent in 1803, when Bonaparte decided on a general reorganization. His principal concern was not the First class but the Second, which included political scientists who were potential critics of his government. Bonaparte abolished the second class completely and, after a few expulsions, redistributed its remaining members, together with those of the Third class, into a new Second class concerned with literature and a new Third class devoted to the fine arts. Still this relationship between the Academy and the government wasn't a one way affair, as members expected to receive their payment of an honorarium.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Crosland|first=Maurice|title=Science Under Control The French Academy of Sciences 1795-1914|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1992|isbn=0521413737|location=Great Britain|pages=302}}</ref>\n\n== Decline of the Academy ==\nAlthough the Academy still exists today, after World war one, the reputation and status of the Academy was largely questioned.<ref name=\":1\" /> One factor of decline was the development from a meritocracy to gerontocracy, in other words; a shift from people with scientific ability leading the Academy to people who had been there longer leading it.<ref name=\":1\" /> It became known as a sort of \u201chall of fame\u201d that lost control, real and symbolic, of the professional scientific diversity in France at the time.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== The Academy today ==\n[[Image:Institut France.jpg|thumb|right|<center>The [[Institut de France]] in Paris where the Academy is housed</center>]]\nToday the Academy is one of five academies comprising the [[Institut de France]]. Its members are elected for life. Currently there are 150 full members, 300 corresponding members, and 120 foreign associates. They are divided into two scientific groups: the [[Mathematics|Mathematical]] and [[Physics|Physical]] sciences and their applications and the [[Chemistry|Chemical]], [[Biology|Biological]], Geological and Medical sciences and their applications. The Academy currently has five missions that its pursuing. These being the encouraging of the scientific life, promoting the teaching of science, transmitting knowledge between scientific communities, fostering international collaborations, and ensuring a dual role of expertise and advise.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/About-us/five-basic-missions-in-the-academy-s-remit.html|title=Five basic missions in the Academy's remit|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The French Academy of Science originally focused its development efforts into creating a true co-development Euro-African program beginning in 1997. Since then they have broadened their scope of action to other regions of the world. The standing committee COPED is in charge of the international development projects undertaken by the French Academy of Science and their associates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/Overview/actions-targeted-towards-development.html|title=Actions Targeted Towards Development|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> The current president of COPED is [[Pierre Auger (biologist)|Pierre Auger]], the vice president is [[Michel Delseny]], and the honorary president is [[Fran\u00e7ois Gros|Francois Gros]]. All of which are current members of the French Academy of Science. COPED has hosted several workshops or colloquia in Paris, involving representatives from African academies, universities or Research centers, addressing a variety of themes and challenges dealing with African development and covering a large field spectrum. Specifically higher education in sciences, and research practices in basic and applied sciences that deal with various aspects relevant to development (renewable energy, infectious diseases, animal pathologies,food resources,access to safe water,agriculture,urban health,etc).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/Actions-targeted-towards-development/standing-committee-for-developing-countries-coped.html|title=Standing Committee for Developing Countries|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Current Committees and Working Parties ==\nThe Academic Standing Committees and Working Parties prepare the advice notes, policy statements and the Academic Reports. Some have a statutory remit, such as the Select Committee, the Committee for International Affairs and the Committee for Scientists' Rights, some are created ad hoc by the Academy and approved formally by vote in a Members only session.\n\nToday the academies standing committees and working parties include:\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee in charge of the Biennial Report on Science and Technology\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Science, Ethics and Society\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for the Environment\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Space Research\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Science and Metrology\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for the Science History and Epistemology\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Science and Safety Issues[[File:Pierre auger.jpg|thumb|[[Pierre Auger (biologist)|Pierre Auger]] the current president of COPED<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/en/Liste-des-membres-de-l-Academie-des-sciences-/-A/pierre-auger.html|title=Pierre Auger|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>]]- The Academic Standing Committee for Science Education and Training\n\n- The Academic Standing La main \u00e0 la p\u00e2te Committee\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for the Defense of Scientists' Rights (CODHOS)\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for International Affairs (CORI)\n\n- The French Committee for International Scientific Unions (COFUSI)\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Scientific and Technological International Relations (CARIST)\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Developing Countries (COPED)\n\n- The Inter-academic Group for Development (GID) - Cf. for further reading\n\n- The Academic Standing Commission for Sealed Deposits\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Terminology and Neologisms\n\n- The Antoine Lavoisier Standing Committee\n\n- The Academic Standing Committee for Prospects in Energy Procurement\n\n- The Special Academic Working Party on Scientific Computing\n\n- The Special Academic Working Party on Material Sciences and Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.academie-sciences.fr/archivage_site/en/comite.htm|title=Academic Standing Committees and Working Parties|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Medals, awards and prizes ==\n\nEach year, the Academy of Sciences distributes about 80 prizes. These include:\n\n* the [[Grande M\u00e9daille]], awarded annually, in rotation, in the relevant disciplines of each division of the Academy, to a French or foreign scholar who has contributed to the development of science in a decisive way.\n* the [[Lalande Prize]], awarded from 1802 through 1970, for outstanding achievement in astronomy\n* the [[Valz Prize]], awarded from 1877 through 1970, to honor advances in astronomy\n* the [[Richard Lounsbery Award]], jointly with the [[United States National Academy of Sciences|National Academy of Sciences]]\n* the Prix [[Jacques Herbrand]], for mathematics and physics\n* the Prix Paul Pascal, for chemistry\n* the [[Louis Bachelier Prize]] for major contributions to mathematical modeling in finance <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/gp_natixis.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-08-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141026191221/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/gp_natixis.htm |archivedate=26 October 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n* the Prix Michel Mon{{color|#808080|t}}petit for computer science and applied mathematics, awarded since 1977<ref>[[:fr:Prix Monpetit|French wikipedia article]]; both \"[http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureats_prixthem2011.pdf Monpetit] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110902033652/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureats_prixthem2011.pdf |date=2 September 2011 }}\" and \"[http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureat_montpetit.pdf Mon'''t'''petit] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150114130029/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/activite/prix/laureat_montpetit.pdf |date=14 January 2015 }}\" is found in Academy publications.</ref>\n* the [[Leconte Prize]], awarded annually since 1886, to recognize important discoveries in mathematics, physics, chemistry, natural history or medicine\n* the Prix [[Pyotr Chikhachyov|Tchihatcheff]] (Tchihatchef; Chikhachev)\n\n== People of the Academy ==\n\nThe following are incomplete lists of the officers of the Academy.  See also [[:Category:Officers of the French Academy of Sciences]].\n\nFor a list of the Academy's members past and present, see [[:Category:Members of the French Academy of Sciences]]\n\n=== Presidents ===\nSource: [https://www.academie-sciences.fr/fr/Histoire-de-l-Academie-des-sciences/liste-des-presidents-de-l-academie-des-sciences-de-1699-a-nos-jours.html French Academy of Sciences]\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1800 [[Napoleon Bonaparte]]\n*1906 [[Henri Poincar\u00e9]]\n*1952 [[Albert Caquot]]\n*2001\u20132002 [[Hubert Curien]]\n*2003\u20132004 [[\u00c9tienne-\u00c9mile Baulieu]]\n*2005\u20132006 [[\u00c9douard Br\u00e9zin]]\n*2007\u20132008 [[Jules Hoffmann]]\n*2009\u20132010 [[Jean Salen\u00e7on]]\n*2011-2012 [[Alain Carpentier]] <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.academie-sciences.fr/academie/membre/liste_president.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-02-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141112092133/http://www.academie-sciences.fr/academie/membre/liste_president.htm |archivedate=12 November 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n*2013\u20132014 [[Philippe Taquet]]\n*2015-2016 [[Bernard Meunier]]\n*2017-2018 [[S\u00e9bastien Candel]]\n}}\n\n=== Treasurers ===\n* ?\u20131788 [[Georges-Louis Leclerc, Comte de Buffon]]\n* 1788\u20131791 [[Mathieu Tillet]]\n\n=== Permanent secretaries ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* Dec 1666 \u2013 Apr 1668 [[Jean-Baptiste Du Hamel]]\n* Apr 1668 \u2013 Dec 1669 [[Jean Gallois]]\n* Jan 1670 \u2013 Jan 1697 [[Jean-Baptiste Du Hamel]]\n* Jan 1697 \u2013 Dec 1740 [[Bernard le Bovier de Fontenelle]] (nominated by king in Jan 1699)\n* Jan 1741 \u2013 Aug 1743 [[Jean-Jacques Dortous de Mairan]]\n* Sep 1743 \u2013 Jul 1776 [[Jean-Paul Grandjean de Fouchy]]\n* Aug 1777 \u2013 Aug 1793 [[Marquis de Condorcet|Nicolas Caritat, marquis de Condorcet]]\n}}\n=== Mathematical Sciences ===<!-- At some point it is actually mathematical and physical science-->\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1801\u20131822 [[Jean Baptiste Joseph Delambre]]\n*1822\u20131830 [[Joseph Fourier]]\n*1830\u20131853 [[Fran\u00e7ois Arago]]\n*1853\u20131874 [[L\u00e9once \u00c9lie de Beaumont]]\n*1874\u20131900 [[Joseph Bertrand]]\n*1900\u20131917 [[Gaston Darboux]]\n*1917\u20131942 [[\u00c9mile Picard]]\n*1942\u20131975 [[Louis de Broglie]]\n*1975\u20131996 Paul Germain\n*Currently: [[Jean Dercourt]]\n*Currently: [[Odile Macchi]]\n}}\n=== Physical Sciences ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1795\u20131803 [[Bernard Germain de Lac\u00e9p\u00e8de]]\n*1803\u20131832 [[Georges Cuvier]]\n*1832\u20131833 [[Pierre-Louis Dulong]]\n*1833\u20131868 [[Pierre Flourens]]\n*1868\u20131884 [[Jean-Baptiste Dumas]]\n*1884\u20131886 [[Jules Jamin]]\n*1886\u20131887 [[Alfred Vulpian]]\n*1887\u20131889 [[Louis Pasteur]]\n*1889\u20131907 [[Marcelin Berthelot]]\n*1907 [[Albert de Lapparent]]\n*1908 [[Henri Becquerel]]\n*1908\u20131914 [[Philippe van Tieghem]]\n*1914\u20131948 [[Alfred Lacroix]]\n}}\n=== Chemistry and Biology ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n*1948\u20131986 [[Robert Courrier]]\n*1986\u20131991 [[Alfred Jost]]\n*1991\u20132001 [[Fran\u00e7ois Gros]]\n*2001\u20132006 [[Nicole Le Douarin]]\n*2006-2011 [[Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Bach]]\n*currently [[Catherine Br\u00e9chignac]]\n}}\n== See also ==\n* [[French art salons and academies]]\n* [[French Geodesic Mission]]\n*[[History of the metre]]\n*[[Seconds pendulum]]\n* [[:fr:Cat\u00e9gorie:Membre de l'Acad\u00e9mie des sciences (France)|Cat\u00e9gorie:Membre de l'Acad\u00e9mie des sciences (France)]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{citation|last= Crosland|first= Maurice P.|title= Science Under Control: The French Academy of Sciences, 1795\u20131914  |year= 1992\n|publisher= Cambridge University Press|isbn= 0-521-52475-X}}\n* St\u00e9phane Schmitt, \"Studies on animals and the rise of comparative anatomy at and around the Parisian Royal Academy of Sciences in the eighteenth century,\" Science in Context 29 (1), 2016, p. 11-54. \n*{{citation|title=Royal Funding of the Parisian Acad\u00e9mie Royale Des Sciences During the 1690s|first=Alice|last=Stroup|publisher=DIANE Publishing|year=1987|isbn=0-87169-774-2|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/royalfundingofpa0000stro}}\n*{{citation|title=Science and Social Status: The Members of the Academie Des Sciences 1666\u20131750|first=David J.|last= Sturdy|publisher=Boydell & Brewer |year=1995|isbn=0-85115-395-X}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Acad\u00e9mie des sciences (France)}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.academie-sciences.fr}} {{in lang|fr}} \u2013 [http://www.academie-sciences.fr/en English-language version]\n* [http://www.academie-sciences.fr/academie/membre.htm Complete listing of current members]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060425224502/http://www.scholarly-societies.org/history/1666as.html Notes on the Acad\u00e9mie des Sciences from the Scholarly Societies project] (includes information on the society journals)\n* [http://gallica.bnf.fr Search the Proceedings of the Acad\u00e9mie des sciences in the French National Library (search item: Comptes Rendus)]\n* [http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb34394200t/date ''Comptes rendus de l'Acad\u00e9mie des sciences. S\u00e9rie 1, Math\u00e9matique''] in [[Gallica]], the digital library of the [[BnF]].\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}\n\n{{International Council for Science}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:French Academy of Sciences| ]]\n[[Category:National academies of sciences|France]]\n[[Category:Institut de France|Sciences]]\n[[Category:Members of the Institut de France]]\n[[Category:1666 establishments in France]]\n[[Category:Lists of members of learned societies]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in the 1660s]]\n[[Category:Scientific organizations established in 1666]]\n[[Category:Members of the International Council for Science]]\n", "name_user": "Mjtth9", "label": "safe", "comment": "added some info and  alternate source on magendie", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Academy_of_Sciences"}
